UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='They will be reeling from this blow for years! Well done, $N! You have earned not only my respect but also this reward.' WHERE `entry`=6148;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Chest opens to reveal Rackmore\'s treasure!' WHERE `entry`=6161;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You bring honor to me for following through with your word. My husband died in battle--he would have been proud of that. But I could not rest until I knew that the creature that has forced me to live my life alone paid for what it had done.$B$BThank you again, $N.' WHERE `entry`=6162;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I wonder... did it beg for mercy? Could it know what mercy is?$B$B<Nathanos spits.>$B$BI will hang this beast\'s head upon my wall.$B$BYou have earned a spot amongst one of my champions, $N.$B$B<Nathanos salutes.>' WHERE `entry`=6163;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='There it is! And oh my! I forgot how full it was!$B$BThis is a glorious day, $N! Stupendous! Insanely good, I say!' WHERE `entry`=6164;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have to get this note to Stormwind? That\'s not a problem, you can take one of my gryphons!' WHERE `entry`=6181;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='After some reports of unusual Forsaken activity in the Eastern Plaguelands, SI:7 agents were dispatched to investigate. The results of that investigation are unsettling.' WHERE `entry`=6182;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Mathias nods.>$B$BI had faith that Bolvar would send me men and women of honor - the most dedicated soldiers of the Alliance.' WHERE `entry`=6183;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The first mission will be straight up, $N. You go in, you come out. Recon...' WHERE `entry`=6184;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Rutger. Fredo. Turyen. All... dead...$B$B<Flint clutches the insignias tightly.>$B$BWhere were they? Did you discover any more information about this bastard, the Blightcaller?' WHERE `entry`=6185;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='An... Any luck??' WHERE `entry`=6185;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='No. It... NO! How? An agent of the Forsaken? The CHAMPION of the Banshee Queen???$B$B<Highlord Bolvar Fordragon slumps in defeat.>' WHERE `entry`=6186;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is a tragedy. I think... I believe that our kind is cursed, $N. We are cursed to lose our greatest warriors; our most noble heroes; our most gifted scholars.$B$BWe are indebted to you and I assure you, $N, wherever Nathanos Marris is now, he smiles down upon you.' WHERE `entry`=6187;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for what you have done. Please continue to help us, $N. We have very few allies on which to call upon.' WHERE `entry`=6241;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A crate for Westfall, eh? Have you been to Westall before? If so, then it\'s no problem, my friend. I have plenty of gryphons trained to fly that route!' WHERE `entry`=6261;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, a note from Quartermaster Lewis? I\'m not surprised he needs more gear. Sentinel Hill is far away, in a land Stormwind has all but forgotten.$B$BWell thank you, $N. Here\'s some money to cover your travel costs.' WHERE `entry`=6281;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is most excellent news! Tell me again how you cast fear into the cold hearts of those vile harpies. The Bloodfuries have been dealt a serious blow!' WHERE `entry`=6282;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Already I feel the anger leave me. What will I do with my time? Knowing evil moves near my land kept my thoughts moving, though now they are silent. Perhaps this is a good thing... maybe now I can focus on the good, as all Tauren should.$B$BPlease accept this as a reward for your troubles.' WHERE `entry`=6283;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good hunting, $N! Besseleth is an old predator in these parts... I will miss her not. Take this reward as a token for being the forest champion.$B$B<Maggran rubs the wound caused by Besseleth.>$B$BPerhaps now many more will travel to Sun Rock Retreat without fearing what lurks in the dark.' WHERE `entry`=6284;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Great, you brought the armor! We\'ll get this divvied to those who need it immediately.$B$BThank you, $N. Your efforts have been a great help to us. And now that you\'re no stranger to gryphons, I hope you\'ll come and lend your aid to Sentinel Hill often!' WHERE `entry`=6285;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah? $N, you have the Gaea seeds. Watch and you shall see the power that these seeds will do for the land. Only those pure and true can heal the land?$B$B<Tammra begins to chant.>' WHERE `entry`=6301;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Executor Zygand asked me to take stock of our equipment here in Brill. With the Scourge, and worse, lurking in the woods, he doesn\'t want the Deathguards to lack gear they might need.$B$BI found that we are, in general, well stocked, but we do need more weapons to replace those lost in the field.$B$BHere is a requisition order of what is needed, for the weapon dealer Gordon Wendham in the Undercity. Take the order to Bat Handler Anette and speak with her about transport to the Undercity.',`objectives_loc6`='Bring Morris\'s Order to Bat Handler Anette.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, an order for supplies. You will want to take this to the Undercity, no doubt. And quickly, for Brill must not be left under stocked.' WHERE `entry`=6321;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This crate must reach the Sepulcher in Silverpine? That is easily done; our bats fly there daily.' WHERE `entry`=6322;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='An order from the Sepulcher? Very well. It is an honor to serve those who serve our Dark Lady.' WHERE `entry`=6323;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='The bat master in Brill is Bat Handler Anette. If you have already met her, then I can give you a bat to fly back to her.$B$BOur bats will always fly to the Undercity, but to travel to more remote locales their rider must first visit the area and speak with its bat master.$B$BYou have met Anette in Brill, so you may now fly bats there. Speak with me again when you are ready.',`objectives_loc6`='Buy a bat ride to Brill from the bat master Michael Garrett, then bring Gordon\'s Crate to Deathguard Morris in Brill.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good work, $N. These weapons will ensure our Deathguards don\'t get caught unprepared.$B$BYou have done a valuable service for our Dark Lady.' WHERE `entry`=6324;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Everyone in Dolanaar is so proud of Sister Aquinne. I\'m certain she\'ll be pleased to receive this thoughtful gift from Nyoma.$B$BWhen you\'re ready to travel to Darnassus, just speak to me again and for a few coins, you can hire a hippogryph to take you there. I\'m told Sister Aquinne enjoys the solitude of a small plaza just south of the hippogryph master in Darnassus. Look for her there after you arrive.',`objectives_loc6`='Speak to Fidelio to purchase a flight to Darnassus, then bring the Dolanaar Recipe Book to Sister Aquinne in Darnassus.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Something for me? I wonder who sent it...' WHERE `entry`=6341;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='This is wonderful! It\'s just the kind of thing I need to remind me of home while I continue my studies in the Temple of the Moon. I\'ll try out one of the recipes tonight. I can\'t wait!$B$BWould you take this short note of thanks back to Nyoma? You can hire a hippogryph to take you back to Dolanaar. Just visit our hippogryph master, Leora, when you\'re ready to leave. She\'ll help you get a ride back to Dolanaar.',`objectives_loc6`='Bring Sister Aquinne\'s Note to Leora, the hippogryph master in Darnassus.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Do you need a ride back to Dolanaar?' WHERE `entry`=6342;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='It will be easy to get you a flight back to Dolanaar. Since you already know Fidelio in Dolanaar, you\'ll be able to fly back there without any problems.$B$BWhenever you arrive in a new town, you should remember to speak to the flight master so that you can fly to and from the new location.$B$BSpeak with me when you\'re ready to hire a hippogryph to return to Dolanaar.',`objectives_loc6`='Speak to Leora to hire a hippogryph to take you back to Dolanaar. Once you\'ve arrived in Dolanaar, take Sister Aquinne\'s Note to Nyoma.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='It sounds like she loved it. Thank you for bringing the book to Sister Aquinne, $N. One of these days, I intend to take her up on her invitation to visit her in Darnassus.' WHERE `entry`=6343;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='A friend of mine, Sister Aquinne, is training to be a priestess of the moon in Darnassus. She left Dolanaar to study in the temple last year. Her letters say she is doing well and learning much, but she misses home and her old friends. I\'ve put together a book of her favorite recipes from Dolanaar.$B$BIf you have time, would you take them to her in Darnassus? You can rent a hippogryph from Fidelio. He\'s in the center of town, just across from the inn.',`objectives_loc6`='Bring the Dolanaar Recipe Book to Fidelio in Dolanaar.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='That\'s very thoughtful of Nyoma. For a few coins, I can arrange quick transportation to the capital by hippogryph.' WHERE `entry`=6344;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='If you must take these hides to Thunder Bluff, then you are speaking to the right orc!' WHERE `entry`=6361;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, a new bundle of hides. I will get to work on these immediately!$B$BThank you, brother. You have done me a great service. Here are some coins to pay for your time and travel costs.' WHERE `entry`=6362;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You need to take this to the Crossroads, eh? That\'s not a problem. If you\'ve already been there and spoken to Devrak, then you can take one of my wind riders back to him.' WHERE `entry`=6363;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='In order to fly to a town, you must have already been there and spoken with the wind rider master of that town. You have been to the Bloodhoof Village and spoken to their wind rider master Tak, so for a small fee you can take a wind rider to him from here.$B$BSpeak with me again when you are ready. Once at Bloodhoof Village, you can then deliver the leather goods to Varg Whisperwind.',`objectives_loc6`='Buy a wind rider to Bloodhoof Village from the wind rider master Tal, then bring Ahanu\'s Leather Goods to Varg Whisperwind.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ahanu sent me finished products?  Very good. There are many hunters and adventurers in Bloodhoof Village now and business is lively. I am sure I\'ll sell these goods very soon. Thank you for all your efforts, $N. I am in your debt.' WHERE `entry`=6364;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have to get this meat to Orgrimmar? That is no problem. For a small fee, my wind rider can take you there.' WHERE `entry`=6365;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is great victory for the land. In time, other things will come to pass: the Venture Co. will pack up their buzz saws and axes, the angry fire spirits will calm, and the harpies will be pushed out by the land.$B$BOnly then $N, will Stonetalon be truly at peace.$B$BYou have done well $C; take one of these items as thanks for the new life you have created here today.' WHERE `entry`=6381;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Welcome to the new frontier, $N. Ashenvale is a land of opportunity, one where a young $C like yourself is able to find boundless chances to prove their mettle. Look around the outpost here, and be sure to travel out to the Zoram Strand, as the Horde has another outpost there as well.$B$BYour presence here tells me that you\'ve come to learn more about the hunt. Listen close, and I will gladly share with you what you need to know.' WHERE `entry`=6382;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='There are three legendary creatures that make up the Ashenvale Hunt; you may seek them and test yourself against their cunning and might. In the process, you will hopefully learn something about yourself. The creatures are: the bear Ursangous, the nightsaber cat Shadumbra, and the hippogryph Sharptalon.$B$BThe creatures of the Ashenvale Hunt are powerful, and you may find that you\'ll need aid in bringing them down. If you should best them, bring me proof of your deed.' WHERE `entry`=6383;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh, wonderful! Those are fine cuts! These are from Zargh, are they? That orc sure knows his way into a lady\'s heart...$B$BOh, I can\'t wait to cook it. But not too much! Meat is best served rare, don\'t you think?' WHERE `entry`=6384;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have to get this to the Crossroads in the Barrens? Yes, I can get you there...' WHERE `entry`=6385;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='My wind riders are trained to fly to many different places, as long as you have already been to that place and spoken with the wind rider master there.$B$BYou have been to Razor Hill and spoken to their wind rider master Burok, so now you can fly directly to him from here. Once you\'re at Razor Hill, you can deliver Gryshka\'s letter to Grimtak.$B$BSpeak with me when you are ready to go.',`objectives_loc6`='Buy a wind rider to Razor Hill from the wind rider master Doras, then bring Gryshka\'s Letter to Grimtak at Razor Hill.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hah! I guess she liked it! Nothing brings red to a lady\'s cheeks like a big, juicy steak!$B$BThank you, $N. You\'ve done me a great service. Here is some money for your trouble, and don\'t be surprised if I invite you to my wedding!' WHERE `entry`=6386;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have to get this to Ironforge, eh? For a small fee I can put you on the back of one of my gryphons, and it\'ll take you there. How does that sound?' WHERE `entry`=6387;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have to get these to Thelsamar, eh? That won\'t be a problem. As long as you\'ve already been to Thelsamar and spoken to Thorgrum Borrelson, then you can take one of my gryphons back to him.' WHERE `entry`=6388;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Haha! Thank you, $N! You\'ve done it! My father\'s spirit can now rest and I can live in peace.$B$BThank you again. If there is anything I can do for you, please, just ask.' WHERE `entry`=6389;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, $N. Here, take this coin. I\'m sorry it\'s not more, but try to take some joy in helping destroy the Scarlet Crusade\'s efforts!' WHERE `entry`=6390;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, the lastest list of Brock\'s best pupils. I have a batch of honorary picks ready to go. I just need to chisel in the names of the students...' WHERE `entry`=6391;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='For a small fee you can buy a gryphon ride to Kharanos... as long as you\'ve already been there. Gryphons will only fly you to places you\'ve already been, so be sure to speak with every gryphon master you see so you can fly to him later.$B$BYou\'ve already been to Brolan, the gryphon master of Kharanos, so now you can return to him. And once in Kharanos, you can deliver the picks to Gremlock Pilsnor.$B$BSpeak with me when you\'re ready to go.',`objectives_loc6`='Buy a gryphon to Kharanos from the gryphon master Gryth Thurden, then bring the Honorary Cleavers to Gremlock Pilsnor in Kharanos.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='You brought the cleaver. Great!  I\'ll get these to my students. I\'m sure they\'re eager to use them on some fresh boar meat. Thank you for your help, $N. I am in your debt, but I hope this money will at least cover your travel costs.' WHERE `entry`=6392;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The water spirits within me bubble with the excitement. $N, you have given me a glorious victory to report to the Tribunal of the Tides.$B$BFor your efforts, I reward you with a choice of my prized possessions.' WHERE `entry`=6393;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Great, you got it! Thanks a lot, $N. This is my favorite pick! Now if my peons ever finish chopping down these trees, maybe we can find a nice cave to mine!' WHERE `entry`=6394;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have done a good deed today, $N. Although our struggle against the Scourge continues, let us hope that Marla and Samuel will find peace together in their final resting place.' WHERE `entry`=6395;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='My goodness, my niece Kaya is alive! That is good news indeed. Thank you, $N.' WHERE `entry`=6401;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Before we begin, I ask that you first gather an army. We face a dragon, after all!' WHERE `entry`=6402;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Bolvar holds the shattered medallion.>$B$BThe magic held within must be reignited. The dragon\'s eye must be attuned.$B$BWindsor\'s sacrifice has freed our Kingdom, but the threat of Onyxia and her kin is ever looming.$B$BThis medallion is what held my mind and body captive. It is also what gave me access to Onyxia\'s own mind - to her secrets. Albeit the visions are muddled now, some things I do remember.' WHERE `entry`=6403;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='I... I... I was powerless.' WHERE `entry`=6403;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah... Yes! That\'s it; the Resonite crystals have a trace of Earthen magic. The Kobolds must have dug deep uncovering an Earthen.$B$BLegend states that the Earthen are creatures created by the Titans. They were used to create the land our feet walk on. This most definitely is a threat that cannot be ignored.$B$B<Mor\'rogal shakes his head.>$B$BPerhaps I can enchant these ore samples to use against this Kobold plot.' WHERE `entry`=6421;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='What news have you discovered from Boulderslide Ravine? I recall some legend that deals with Resonite... I just cannot place my hoof on it. Perhaps knowing what lies at the bottom of the cave will illuminate their devious intentions.' WHERE `entry`=6421;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These are perfect, $N! Thanks for helping me out!$B$BOh, and this is for your time...' WHERE `entry`=6441;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We could use more of your kind around here, $N. Thank you for your help.' WHERE `entry`=6442;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Sweet, mon! Good news, perhaps we will have fewer unwanted dinner gusts tonight.$B$BAs I said earlier, we are in your debt... maybe you would care for one of these for your deed?' WHERE `entry`=6461;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You found them! Thank you! Thank you, $N! You do not know how great a thing you have done for me.$B$BA troll without his charm is like an orc without his battle scars...$B$BWorthless.' WHERE `entry`=6462;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You bear good news, $C! I fear the possibilities of what an Earthen would mean to Kalimdor.$B$BSlaying Goggeroc was a task for no one less then a hero. You have done well; all of Stonetalon and Kalimdor are indebted to you, noble $C.$B$BAccept this as your reward most honored one.' WHERE `entry`=6481;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You found my brother!  He was captured by the Thistlefurs?  That is terrible news to hear, for although many Furbolgs are noble creatures, the Thistlefurs are corrupt.$B$BThank you for rescuing my brother, $N. I do not want to think of how they treated poor Ruul. He will likely sleep long after this ordeal...' WHERE `entry`=6482;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Have you seen my brother Ruul? He walked into the forest days ago and has not returned...' WHERE `entry`=6482;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I should have known - a piece of the black dragon brood mother, Onyxia. How revolting...' WHERE `entry`=6501;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This amulet will grant you the access that you seek. The lair of Onyxia can be found in Dustwallow Marsh. As long as you hold the amulet, her wards cannot prevent you from entering.$B$BThe Blue Flight wishes you luck, $N.' WHERE `entry`=6502;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Very good, $N. Your hunting skills are impressive...$B$BThe loss of those outrunners help blind the Alliance, and when they lack intelligence they are less likely to launch attacks.' WHERE `entry`=6503;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Reading isn\'t my strong point... but now I\'ll be able to get back to work! Thanks, $N!' WHERE `entry`=6504;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good. Well done, $C.$B$BNow that Malcin is dead, we can at least know that the Scourges advances will be halted. The Dark Lady thanks you for your efforts and wishes to reward you with a gift.$B$BAlthough we do not know the extent of the Scourges influence within the Downs, I am sure we will discover their plots soon enough.' WHERE `entry`=6521;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I recognize the insignia on this scroll, $N. You found this on that crone who reigns over Razorfen Kraul? Interesting.$B$BThe Scourge aren\'t content with one continent it seems. This Ambassador Malcin--the one who wrote the note--is one of the Scourge\'s plagued servants, a human diplomat to the kingdom of Lordaeron before things... changed.$B$BIf the Scourge are trying to gain a foothold in Kalimdor, then it is up to us to act.' WHERE `entry`=6522;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Kaya is alive! $N, I have you to thank for rescuing her.' WHERE `entry`=6523;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ashenvale is a divided land, but our most recent efforts have been very successful. We not only have an outpost at the Zoram Strand, but another just north of here called Splintertree.' WHERE `entry`=6541;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ashenvale is a divided land, but our most recent efforts have been very successful. We not only have an outpost at the Zoram Strand, but another just north of here called Splintertree.' WHERE `entry`=6542;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I can see that you are one that can be counted on. These updates are crucial to our plans to further our presence in Ashenvale. We can now plan our next move.' WHERE `entry`=6543;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So Torek\'s attack was successful! Well done, $N. Night elves are decent foes. A little skinny, but strong and fierce! I\'m sure the battle was something to see...$B$BAnd I hope you gained a scar or two!' WHERE `entry`=6544;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Torek was sent on a mission against Silverwing Outpost. Was the attack successful?' WHERE `entry`=6544;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well, my update will explain all of this to Kadrak. You must return this to him as quickly as possible.' WHERE `entry`=6545;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Take my update to Kadrak. Swiftly, $N.' WHERE `entry`=6546;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Let Kadrak know of the success we have had here holding off the night elves. Our plans are going well.' WHERE `entry`=6547;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='$N, I thank you... but I will never forget what the Grimtotem have done to my village.' WHERE `entry`=6548;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Kelris has eluded the Argent Dawn for some time.$B$BFor some time they considered him dead or missing.$B$BBy ending his reign you have spared the lives of many innocent people, $N.$B$BEarthmother be praised! To sacrifice another to a servant of an Old God for personal gain is beyond disgusting!$B$BYou have done a great thing this day. Kelris was a creature of evil and sought to bring the world back to a time of chaos by worshipping such creatures as the Old Gods. Thank you, $N.' WHERE `entry`=6561;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Tsunaman sent you? Excellent. Then we have matters to discuss.' WHERE `entry`=6562;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. These are the crystals I spoke of. Intriguings...$B$BI can feel the power within them. The spirits of water cling to them. Whatever the naga were going to use these for... well, let us be glad they are no longer in their hands.' WHERE `entry`=6563;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is interesting indeed. I am glad you have brought it to my attention.$B$BNow we have a name for our troubles... Lorgus Jett.' WHERE `entry`=6564;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Very good!! Thank you, $N. We may not have stopped the Twilight\'s Hammer completely, but at least you have staved off another of their plans to return the Old Gods to power.$B$BWho knows what other plans they have manifesting, but we can rest easy for now.' WHERE `entry`=6565;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Are you prepared to take on this task?' WHERE `entry`=6566;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Patience, $N. Pay attention!' WHERE `entry`=6566;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='There is but one way into the dragon\'s lair, $R.$B$BYou see, only the strongest of the Black Dragonflight are allowed entry into the lair of the brood mother. Many trials must be passed and the key to enter ceremoniously enchanted by General Drakkisath himself!$B$BSince you are not of black dragonkin, you may have some difficulty in obtaining passage.$B$B<Rexxar grins.>' WHERE `entry`=6567;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Myranda holds the note, pauses, then smiles.>$B$BHow is he? Rexxar, I mean. Oh, come now, do not look so confused. The letter was left intentionally blank. It carried with it the intentions and thoughts of its creator. Judging from its contents, it is no wonder Rexxar left it as such. Imagine if you were captured or slain and this information discovered!$B$BOh, nevermind! Myranda will help you, $R. I owe the Warchief a favor or two.$B$B<Myranda smiles.>' WHERE `entry`=6568;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Let Myranda have a look, $R.$B$BOh yes, these will do nicely.$B$BWith these reagents, Myranda will create for you a medallion that will grant an illusion capable of fooling the black dragonflight\'s gatekeeper.' WHERE `entry`=6569;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Have we run so low on able soldiers that Nefarian is sending me whelps? You will never pass my tests, broodling.' WHERE `entry`=6570;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent, $N. You\'ve saved me a lot of work!$B$BBut don\'t think that I\'m not grateful!' WHERE `entry`=6571;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is perfect -- just the thing! Well, here\'s the shipment.' WHERE `entry`=6581;
