UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='With many of the owlkin now inoculated. we can focus on getting out of here and not have to worry about wiping out the owlkin population in the area.$B$BHere. choose from these. You\'ve done good work. and you deserve to be rewarded!' WHERE `entry`=9303;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='How tragic. These words, clearly meant for someone the soldier loved, never made it to their destination. The events detailed happened years ago; I\'m not sure if the intended recipient still lives.$B$BThere is hope yet, however. With the names and information he gives, I might be able to locate the family! It will take some research, but the librarian in Stormwind owes me a favor...$B$BThank you for bringing this to me. With your help, we may be able to grant someone peace of mind at last.' WHERE `entry`=9304;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Let me take a look at those.$B$BYes, I think that these will do nicely; good job, $N. The emitter is rather complex so it may take some time to finish the repairs. I\'ll let you know when it\'s ready.$B$BIn the meantime, you might see if Vindicator Aldar has anything he could use you for.' WHERE `entry`=9305;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Help... blood elves! They... ambushed... me. Don\'t have... long.' WHERE `entry`=9309;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You say this was taken from a wight attacking the city?$B$BWe have received word of the necropolis base camps that are being summoned by the Scourge. I suspect they were trying to create one in the Undercity. We will have to be vigilant in the future.' WHERE `entry`=9310;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I thank you for dealing with the blood elf surveyor. Surely she was their leader. Rest assured, we will deal with whatever remnant of them is still nearby.$B$BPlease, take one of these weapons as a sign of my gratitude.' WHERE `entry`=9311;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I got it. I got it! I think I managed to fix the emitter! Here, I\'ll just activate this last crystal and that should do it.$B$BTake a look at the emitter, $N. It looks like it\'s beginning to work... someone is appearing!' WHERE `entry`=9312;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, good to see you again! I\'m glad that we were both able to get our emitters fixed or we might never have found one another. And don\'t worry, we\'ll see to it that Ammen Vale gets help and supplies.$B$BSpeaking of assistance, now that you\'re here, go around and introduce yourself to the others. I know that there\'s plenty to do.' WHERE `entry`=9313;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh, you must be one of the survivors we\'ve been hearing about!$B$BI\'m glad that you came. Don\'t worry, we will send someone to see to Aeun\'s injured leg.$B$BI\'m most interested in hearing all about your harrowing story of survival. You\'re a brave one to have made it all the way here.' WHERE `entry`=9314;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I apologize for the shoddy intelligence. $C. Had I known of this Anok\'suten ahead of time, I surely would have told you.$B$BWe\'re spread too thin and things are slipping through the cracks!' WHERE `entry`=9315;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have proven that you are not entirely useless, mortal.' WHERE `entry`=9319;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Have you found your way through the dark?' WHERE `entry`=9319;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Your spirit glows with the warmth of the Kalimdor fires, friend. Is the heat not invigorating? Once the power fades from you, perhaps these will help rekindle the feeling.' WHERE `entry`=9322;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, here you are. A little wearier, a bit dustier, but enlightened! The heat touches us all during this season and unites us; your very being glows with the power of the fires you touched. Ah, but these days enlightenment is taken as a rather poor reward for being sent on a task, I suppose. Take these, then, and enjoy the celebration.' WHERE `entry`=9323;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What\'s this? Unless I\'m mistaken, this flame has been taken from the heart of Orgrimmar itself! The fierce hearts of the orcs and trolls are reflected in its searing heat. What a fine addition to our collection--how brave you are, stealing into the enemy\'s lair to retrieve the sacred flame!' WHERE `entry`=9324;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Unless I miss my guess, this fire has been taken from the cliffs of Thunder Bluff! How it sings with the power of the spirits! You are quite the thief, $N. Take this as just payment for your skill. Now, if only we had the flames of all three cities...' WHERE `entry`=9325;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hm... what a strange fire! It is subdued, nearly smoldering, but the heat is intense. And you received this from the Undercity, you say? Fascinating. With the flames of all three cities, who knows what we could accomplish?' WHERE `entry`=9326;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We Forsaken are here because of a common enemy with the blood elves: Dar\'Khan! He has returned and now commands the Scourge that are invading this land from his steadfast, Deatholme, to the south.$B$BLady Sylvanas Windrunner, who originally hails from these lands, and used to be an elf, has a history with Dar\'Khan and wants him dead!$B$BWe will defeat him, $C, and you will help us do it!' WHERE `entry`=9327;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Now that\'s one face I was not expecting to see so soon.$B$BThis is quite the good news, $N, in more ways than you can imagine.' WHERE `entry`=9328;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We Forsaken are here because of a common enemy with the blood elves: Dar\'Khan! He has returned and now commands the Scourge that are invading this land from his steadfast, Deatholme, to the south.$B$BLady Sylvanas Windrunner, who originally hails from these lands, and used to be an elf, has a history with Dar\'Khan and wants him dead!$B$BWe will defeat him, $C, and you will help us do it!' WHERE `entry`=9329;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='And this brightly-burning fire... you say it came from Stormwind? Remarkable! That must have been quite an adventure! I\'ll pay you for this, of course. If you find anything else like this, be sure to speak with me again.' WHERE `entry`=9330;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This hearty flame must be from the halls of Ironforge; it\'s as stalwart as the dwarves themselves. A fine catch, $N. If I had the fires of the other cities... ah, but never mind. Here is your payment.' WHERE `entry`=9331;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This fire aches of ancient sorrow, $N. You pulled this from the roots of Teldrassil, you say? Fascinating! Here is a reward for your skill. Return to me should you find anything else like this; I may have a use for it.' WHERE `entry`=9332;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You honor us, $N. With your continued efforts we will overcome all obstacles.' WHERE `entry`=9338;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='This flame, stolen from the heart of Stormwind itself, floods you with warmth. This raw power is foreign to you, but the (NAME) might know more...',`objectives_loc6`='Return the Flame of Stormwind to (NAME).',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve proven yourself, today, $N.$B$BWhile I have little else to give you, I do have this crown; a fitting gift for a conqueror. May it light your way.' WHERE `entry`=9339;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good job, $N. That should teach the rock flayers to stay far away from us.' WHERE `entry`=9340;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for your help, $N. Got anything up your sleeve to make the peons earn their keep?' WHERE `entry`=9342;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These should do the job. I\'m going to prepare the salve and finish my splint before making my way back to Thrallmar. Why do I have the feeling that I know what Far Seer Regulkut will say when she sees me?$B$B<Grelag sighs half-heartedly.>$B$BThank you for your help, $N. I have some of the spineleaf left over. You\'re welcome to take it with you. Who can tell when it will prove useful?' WHERE `entry`=9345;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='In order to have great cuisine, you need to have great ingredients. And these eggs look great!$B$BI\'ve just finished cleaning off my frying pan, so you\'re more than welcome to join me for a meal!' WHERE `entry`=9349;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is perfect! In fact, I think it\'s going to work so well, I might just have to redesign the engine to take advantage of all this extra power. If, I mean, when we get out of here, I\'ll have to show my design to everyone back at Area 52!' WHERE `entry`=9351;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Night elves? Here? Those rats!$B$BDo you suppose they had anything to do with the malfunction in my sanctum? If you have any information, you\'d better take it to Captain Sunbrand at once!' WHERE `entry`=9352;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. We shouldn\'t be too quick to congratulate ourselves, though. I\'m certain we haven\'t seen the last of those worms. If they show their hideous heads around these parts again, the Sons\'ll be ready for them!' WHERE `entry`=9355;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ravager Eggs. Bam!$B$BHellboar Bacon. Bam!$B$BBuzzard Wings. Bam!  Bam!$B$BWhat a great meal. You\'ve really got to try it.' WHERE `entry`=9356;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re here to help us? Why didn\'t you say so earlier? We can always use a hand!' WHERE `entry`=9358;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re here to help? Excellent!$B$BThe battle against the Amani trolls has taken its toll on us and capable fighters such as yourself are always welcome.' WHERE `entry`=9359;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The trolls have been keeping us pinned here while planning an attack on Fairbreeze Village. We were not expecting this at all.' WHERE `entry`=9360;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hmm...$B$BThis looks edible, if spiced properly. Just don\'t tell Screed where his breakfast came from, ok?' WHERE `entry`=9361;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I must say, this shell has a strange aura. It seems only fitting that part of your reward for retrieving it would be to test its magical capabilities...' WHERE `entry`=9362;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The information you\'ve brought is of vital importance, $N. Now that we know of the trolls\' plans we can prepare for an attack.$B$BWe won\'t be caught with our guard down.' WHERE `entry`=9363;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Splendid! Splendid!$B$BNow we are able to reform this magic into a new spell. Behold!' WHERE `entry`=9364;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='This flame, stolen from the heart of Stormwind itself, floods you with warmth. This raw power is foreign to you, but the (NAME) might know more...',`objectives_loc6`='Return the Flame of Stormwind to (NAME).',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve proven yourself, today, $N.$B$BWhile I have little else to give you, I do have this crown; a fitting gift for a conqueror. May it light your way.' WHERE `entry`=9365;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The energy contained in these samples is tremendous, $N. Now we just need to ensure that our access to this felblood continues uninterrupted.' WHERE `entry`=9366;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent! It seems we\'ve appointed dutiful Flamekeepers this year if the bonfires are as well-kept as you claim. Thank you for inspecting them for me; here, take this as a small token of my esteem.' WHERE `entry`=9367;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent work, $N. With the shadows destroyed, it can only be a matter of time before the Lich King decides to recall his necropolises and leave us in peace.' WHERE `entry`=9368;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Regrettable that those creatures had to die so that we might live - indiscriminate killing is not the draenei way. However, the blood you gathered will replenish our healing crystals, so their deaths will not be in vain.' WHERE `entry`=9369;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That\'ll show those holy fanatics to mind their own business.' WHERE `entry`=9370;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh, thank goodness you\'ve come. We have much to do.' WHERE `entry`=9371;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. These blood samples will prove helpful in my research and in the Expedition\'s wider studies of Outland\'s creatures.$B$BIf I could isolate what causes these creatures to change continuously, perhaps I could concoct an antidote.' WHERE `entry`=9372;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for bringing this to me, $C. I was wondering why I hadn\'t heard from the Expedition in so long. I wonder how long ago this message was dispatched and what befell its carrier.$B$BHere\'s a bit of coin for your trouble.' WHERE `entry`=9373;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='My husband\'s journal... it\'s not about research at all!$B$BHow could I\'ve been such a fool?  "Magical properties of fel-infused slime forms," he really had me going there.' WHERE `entry`=9374;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Taleris shouts to several of the blood elves at the outpost.>$B$BGet her inside and see to her wounds!$B$B<Taleris turns back to you.>$B$BShe\'s fortunate that you found her when you did, $C. I don\'t think she\'d have lasted much longer out there.$B$BCan you make out what she was saying?' WHERE `entry`=9375;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for returning this, $N. I\'m not sure what significance it holds for the wounded pilgrim, but she refuses to let anyone get near her until it\'s in her hands again.' WHERE `entry`=9376;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These should do the job. I was concerned that the rangers might be short on arrows for a while, but that\'s one less thing I have to worry about. Thank you for your help, $C.' WHERE `entry`=9381;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well, $N. It seems the containment crystal is holding for now, but how long it will last remains a mystery. We\'ll keep an eye on it and prepare more of the crystals in the meantime.' WHERE `entry`=9383;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. That should teach those beasts who\'s boss!' WHERE `entry`=9385;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have proven that you are not entirely useless, mortal.' WHERE `entry`=9386;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Have you found your way through the dark?' WHERE `entry`=9386;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve been most helpful, $N. Now let\'s see what we can learn from our blue friend.' WHERE `entry`=9387;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ahhh, so they do still burn. I am glad; it would not do for those fires to burn out before their time. You have done well, $N. Take this with my blessing.' WHERE `entry`=9388;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you\'ve returned, and you\'ve seen to the emerald flames of the continent. What do you think, mm? A rare and wonderful sight, to be certain. I am aware, however, that tangible rewards are better appreciated... so please, take this for your trouble.' WHERE `entry`=9389;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve found the body of a young draenei $C. He appears to have been slain by a blow to his back.' WHERE `entry`=9390;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Great Fissure, though still dangerous, will prove to be a useful path for our pilgrims.$B$BWith the Alliance watching all the roads in and out of Falcon Watch this is the manner of desperate act that is required of us.' WHERE `entry`=9391;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I\'ve heard your name whispered from the shadows, $N. It\'s said that you\'re looking for someone experienced to show you the ropes - someone like me. I can do that, but it\'ll cost you a small cut of your take every time I\'ve got something to teach you. So yes, I will train you in what it means to be a rogue.$B$BBut remember, if you ever get caught stealing something, this conversation never took place. Now get out there and show me what you\'re made of!' WHERE `entry`=9392;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='$N, are your eyes keen as a hawk\'s, your motions as fluid as a monkey\'s, or your speed that of a cheetah?  Mine are, and yours can be too with the proper training. The way of the hunter is one of mastery over the beasts of the world, an unparalleled precision in marksmanship, and the knowledge of how to survive in situations where others would perish.$B$BIf these are the things that you seek to learn, then I will train you - for a small fee, of course. Shall we begin?' WHERE `entry`=9393;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Who are you? You\'re not one of the magister\'s apprentices, that\'s for certain!$B$BSent here to help me clean up this mess, no doubt!' WHERE `entry`=9394;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, good of Magistrix Dawnstrider to finally respond to my simple requests. I should take up the matter of her attitude with the regent lord in Silvermoon. She\'s quite rude!$B$BNothing for you to concern yourself with though. Now that you\'re here, maybe I\'ll finally be able to get those party supplies that I\'ve been waiting for?' WHERE `entry`=9395;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good work, $N. Outland\'s secrets will not stay hidden from us for very long.$B$BIt\'s our destiny to become the masters of this world.' WHERE `entry`=9396;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did it!  You caught a female hatchling!$B$BShe\'s precious. You have my thanks, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9397;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well, $N. It is always unfortunate to have to resort to taking a life, even when it\'s that of a dangerous beast such as the rock flayer.$B$BYou have my thanks for carrying out this grim task.' WHERE `entry`=9398;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did it!  I\'m in your debt, $N. Look at all the Dreghoods that are showing up.$B$BUnder my guidance they\'ll learn all about the old ways, you\'ll see.' WHERE `entry`=9399;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The corpse matches the description of Krun Spinebreaker, Hellfire Citadel\'s assassin. As you turn the body over, you notice a stone axe protruding from his back.' WHERE `entry`=9400;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='He was killed by this weapon?  It can\'t be!$B$BHave we... found them?' WHERE `entry`=9401;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh, well done... I told you to jump in a pond, and you did. I can only imagine what you\'d do if one of your good friends asked it of you.$B$BIf you want a reward for your efforts, it is this: never lift a finger without first knowing what\'s in it for you. The $C\'s mind is his greatest weapon. Remember that and try to use yours a bit more.' WHERE `entry`=9402;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Let\'s see what you\'ve brought me...$B$B<He holds the phial up to the light and examines it closely.>$B$BYes, this will do. Well done, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9403;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done as I\'ve asked, $N, and you may take your reward now.' WHERE `entry`=9404;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I understand Nazgrel\'s request, $C. Say no more.' WHERE `entry`=9405;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re certain of this?  True orcs... here in Hellfire!  This is big news, $N.$B$BWe must inform the warchief at once.' WHERE `entry`=9406;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Our Expedition made it safely through the Portal and set up a new base called Thrallmar. Yet as you can see. the Burning Legion moved in and cut us off from our brothers. Clearly, the demons hope to retake the Dark Portal and prevent us from gathering reinforcements from Azeroth.' WHERE `entry`=9407;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good work!  This will do nicely to replenish our depleted healing crystals.$B$BBut now that you\'re here, I think I have another use for you, if you\'re willing?' WHERE `entry`=9409;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Who are you to walk in here unannounced?  I ordered my men to stay their hand only because Ryga sensed that the spirits were with you.$B$BSpeak freely, but choose your words wisely. We rarely trust strangers this close to the Citadel.' WHERE `entry`=9410;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Alliance needs every able body they can get. The Horde has been receiving a steady supply of reinforcements from the northern part of the continent, and it\'s been a struggle to keep up.$B$BLet me explain the situation to you.' WHERE `entry`=9415;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s good that you\'re here, but there\'s no time to waste making small talk. You need instructions, and then you need to get out there.$B$BListen up.' WHERE `entry`=9416;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Great job, $N! I hereby proclaim you an honorary Longbeard.$B$BStick around and have a drink with us, won\'t you?' WHERE `entry`=9417;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='With this orb I regain my liberty. Take your reward, mortal, so that our debt may be settled.' WHERE `entry`=9418;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank the Light you were successful.$B$BNow if we could only have started this sooner, our need would not be so desperate. We must keep the bounty of the desert from falling into the hands of the Horde.' WHERE `entry`=9419;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did your part. I guess a deal is a deal! $B$BHere you go. friend. Treat it well.' WHERE `entry`=9420;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I am Firmanvaar and you are wise to seek me out. It is my calling to provide instruction to $C, especially those who are just beginning to learn.$B$BShamanism is only now being relearned amongst the $R, $N. You are brave to follow its path as it is not popular amongst your kind.$B$BI will be here when you feel you are ready for further training.' WHERE `entry`=9421;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well, $N. These resources will be added to our stockpiles, and every bit is to our gain and our enemy\'s loss.' WHERE `entry`=9422;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Sedai, dear brother...$B$BThose cowardly orcs! He was unarmed, how could they?$B$BLeave me be, $N. I thank you for your assistance but I wish to be alone with my thoughts now.' WHERE `entry`=9423;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Yes... revenge! You did good.$B$BYou take this now. It was a gift from Sedai. It only makes Makuru sad to see it.' WHERE `entry`=9424;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='My, my! Another of my brothers arrives to pitch in. Good! There is much to be done in support of our new Forsaken friends, $C. Ask around to see who you can help out.$B$BI know that you will support them to your utmost ability!' WHERE `entry`=9425;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Yes. I feel the fel presence in the pools weakening.$B$BYou\'ve done well, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9426;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The essence of Aggonar lived on in the form of his foul offspring Aggonis. With your success in defeating the demon, we can begin to work towards restoring the pools to their former purity.$B$BYou have our thanks, $N. Your work will have a deep impact in this world.' WHERE `entry`=9427;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The ambassador sent word ahead, so I\'ve been expecting you.$B$BThe ambassador simply wants you to do as much as you can to help out around here. She said something about making sure to cement our relationship with the rest of the Horde.$B$BAsk around - there are others in need of help further back in the Post. And I hear that there\'s another Horde outpost called Zoram\'gar Outpost on the coast all the way to the west.' WHERE `entry`=9428;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Greetings, $C. I trust that you\'re journey here was uneventful?$B$BThese poor souls are beset upon all sides by the creatures of the night. It is our wish that you lend them what aid you can in pushing back the darkness.$B$BTravel about the town and get to know its inhabitants. Please, $N, help them in any way that you can.' WHERE `entry`=9429;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re very fortunate. Just as I had hoped, you\'ve found a special relic among these other ones.' WHERE `entry`=9430;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What? She didn\'t mention the moonwell? That\'s what she had in mind all along. I admit the whole thing\'s a bit wacky, but who am I to turn away a client, especially when she\'s the only one I\'ve got?$B$BMaybe trying to sneak into a night elf settlement and steal water from their moonwell isn\'t the most prudent thing I\'ve ever helped a customer do, but her money is as gold as anyone else\'s!' WHERE `entry`=9431;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Always good to see a semi-familiar face. You must be $N. Emissary Valustraa sent me word to expect you.$B$BThe people of Ashenvale need our assistance, $C. Speak with the citizens of Astranaar to see how you can help.' WHERE `entry`=9432;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That worked better than I expected! Chalk up another one for good old goblin ingenuity!$B$BThe only problem is that it\'s hopelessly covered in dust! It\'s going to take me forever to get this thing cleaned up and replaced in its crate.$B$BOf course, time is the one thing I have in ample supply.' WHERE `entry`=9433;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent, it appears everything is here. Now, all I have to do is mix everything together and give it a try. If this tonic does what my research indicates it should do, I may have discovered a way to lessen the effects of my people\'s magic addiction.$B$BYou\'re about to witness history in the making, $N. Just think, without your help, this wouldn\'t have been possible.' WHERE `entry`=9434;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank the Light! From the tone of the foreman\'s letter, it sounded as if that box of crystals contained the only known samples from the mine. If we had lost them, $N, we may never have seen another like them.$B$BI can\'t thank you enough for your help.' WHERE `entry`=9435;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done. Now, this is curious...$B$BThe inscription on this totem is in a language no troll could ever hope to learn, but one that is known to us. It names the bearer as an ally of a water elemental named Naias and marks him as one worthy to channel his power.$B$BThis is most unexpected, but not entirely bad, $N. With your help, I\'d like to pursue this further.' WHERE `entry`=9436;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N! As soon as Ithania has had time to rest and my preparations are complete, we\'ll depart this sodden wasteland and head back to civilization.' WHERE `entry`=9437;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<You watch Thrall\'s jaw slacken as he begins to read the message from Nazgrel.>$B$BMy people... we must reach them. We must reach Nagrand as soon as possible!' WHERE `entry`=9438;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re a miracle worker, $N! I tell you, I\'ve never been so eager for a change of clothes in my life.$B$BAnd my rapier! I felt positively naked without my blade.$B$BYou are to be commended and rewarded for your efforts. Never let it be said that Sarophas failed to acknowledge the little people who\'ve helped him along the way!' WHERE `entry`=9439;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh, excellent! I can\'t wait to measure the effects from this latest batch!$B$BWell, you did an admirable job, sweetie. Wish I could give you more than this for the entertainment you\'ve provided, but you know how it is. There\'s not much money to be made out here in the swamp.$B$BI\'m sure it was worth it just for the fun!' WHERE `entry`=9440;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It means very much to us that you come to aid us in our time of need. We\'ll not easily forget you nor he who sends you.$B$BYou have our thanks.' WHERE `entry`=9441;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Gorkan said good things about you. They\'re all turning out to be true.$B$BThanks for your help.' WHERE `entry`=9442;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The first step is complete. Hand me the Mark of the Lightbringer and I will transform it into something more suitable.$B$BThen my revenge will begin in earnest, $C!' WHERE `entry`=9443;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Forgives me?  He FORGIVES ME?!!!$B$BI don\'t care what that old ghost had to say - it was his fault!  Everything that\'s happened to Quel\'Thalas was a result of his incompetence!$B$BIt is clear that the defiling did not work. Go, be gone from my sight!  I must think this through.' WHERE `entry`=9444;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Lightbringer appeared before you? That is amazing! And you made it all possible through your selfless help to the anchorite.$B$BIf even half of the stories are to be believed, Uther was a great man. And, like him, you are a true hero to all of the good people of Azeroth, $N!' WHERE `entry`=9446;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Aren\'t you supposed to be walking to Uther\'s Tomb with Anchorite Truuen?' WHERE `entry`=9446;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='May the spirits bless you, $N. The Mag\'har are in your debt.' WHERE `entry`=9447;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is done then. I thank you for showing your compassion. Once corrupted by whatever Cersei was feeding them, there is nothing else that could be done.$B$BThey are now at peace and hopefully my studies of the others will bear fruit so that they can be rehabilitated.' WHERE `entry`=9448;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You are bold to seek my wisdom after what your people have done to these islands, stranger! Still, there is much to be said for your bravery, so I will impart to you some knowledge.$B$BThe earth beneath your feet forms the foundation for all things. The sky, the waters, even great fire - all rest upon its shoulders. While those others often form chaotic tempests, the earth abides. It grants strength and fortitude to the core of your being.' WHERE `entry`=9449;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have done well. By thinning out the restless spirits you have helped to heal the imbalance between the elements, which your people inadvertently caused.$B$BThroughout your journey as a $C you must keep this in mind when calling upon our power. The balance must be preserved.' WHERE `entry`=9450;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have done well, $N. In helping to restore the balance of the elements at the grove, you have also created a balance between the earth element of this world and the $R. Perhaps this will help to bring understanding to those amongst us who do not approve of our ways?$B$BI will create for you a totem through which you will be able to call on the power of earth to do your bidding. And with time, more of the mysteries of earth will be revealed to you.$B$BNow, take your totem, $C.' WHERE `entry`=9451;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I hope the murlocs didn\'t cause too much trouble, $N. I owe you a great debt of gratitude for all that you\'ve done.$B$BPerhaps I could teach you how to fish? I\'ll even supply the fishing pole and a bauble.' WHERE `entry`=9452;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Poor Diktynna... That murloc gave her quite a scare.$B$B<Acteon sighs.>$B$BHopefully she will recover from the injuries soon...$B$BSo I presume you\'re looking for work. Well there\'s plenty of that to be found at Azure Watch!' WHERE `entry`=9453;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N, well done!$B$BHere, I cooked up some tenderloins while you were gone. Maybe you\'d like the recipe, too?' WHERE `entry`=9454;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='How did such a thing end up in the stomach of a nightstalker? Could the debris from the crash have contaminated more beasts?' WHERE `entry`=9455;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I just hope it\'s not too late...' WHERE `entry`=9456;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I can feel the raw power contained in this gem, $N. I\'ll send it to Silvermoon for our magisters to study further, but I am sure it will prove useful in our struggle against the Amani.$B$BYour help has been invaluable in procuring this gem, and I will see to it that the Farstriders know the name of the $R who made this find possible.' WHERE `entry`=9457;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent!  Such a personal item carries a strong scent of the intruders--enough to guide Whisper into their ranks...' WHERE `entry`=9460;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hello, $N, I have been expecting you. I trust this day finds you well?' WHERE `entry`=9461;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Just in time, $N. I hope you are ready to continue your training. This next task will be a difficult one.' WHERE `entry`=9462;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Let us hope that this ointment will strengthen her spirit!' WHERE `entry`=9463;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I trust that the burning I see behind your eyes is from a desire to grow and understand?  Good!$B$BTuluun has sent you here because he sees your potential to both learn and help with a problem that the crash of your Exodar has caused.$B$BWe shall see.' WHERE `entry`=9464;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='See how its fire never goes out?  That is the work of Hauteur. It is a symbol of his arrogance. Flame is meant to consume that which it burns and then itself die, to be reborn anew another time.$B$BI would help you douse the torch, but it must stay lit for you to deal with Hauteur. We will let it burn a little while longer.' WHERE `entry`=9465;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re a brave $C, $N. That savage beast took many of my best hunters\' lives.$B$BTake this reward, you\'ve earned it.' WHERE `entry`=9466;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is a valuable lesson that you learn here today. It is the story of endings and new beginnings.$B$BWhen first we spoke I told you that fire was not just destruction, but also a renewing force of the elements. Through your actions you have both destroyed and saved Hauteur, for he shall be reborn from his ashes.' WHERE `entry`=9467;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have passed through the cleansing fire of destruction and been renewed, $N. This is not unlike the tribulation the $R people are currently undergoing. And through saving Hauteur from himself, you have secured your connection to the elemental fire of this world.' WHERE `entry`=9468;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Featherbeard\'s journal appears to have a large number of recent entries. Leafing back to the beginning of the latest ones, you begin searching for clues about where he might have gone.' WHERE `entry`=9469;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. The Wildhammers will be heartened to know that they don\'t stand against the Witherbark trolls alone. Showing them that the Alliance can prove a reliable partner in protecting the gryphons should lend more weight to our proposition.' WHERE `entry`=9470;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Ambassador Rualeth nods as you give your report.>$B$BYou have done well. The culling of the silvermane will not go unnoticed by the Wildhammer. When I meet with their leaders, I am certain that your deeds will reflect well upon the Alliance. Please accept this coin as a small token of my thanks, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9471;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent!  That little backstabber won\'t be running off with anyone\'s husband any time soon.$B$BHere\'s a little something for your troubles. I trust we can keep this incident between us, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9472;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Watch as the plant works its magic.' WHERE `entry`=9473;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, $C!  The recovery of this holy symbol means a great deal to myself and others that honor the memory of Uther Lightbringer.' WHERE `entry`=9474;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Handing the eggs to the ambassador, you describe the findings at Featherbeard\'s Hovel and Shadra\'Alor.>$B$BThe Witherbark killed Featherbeard?$B$B<Rualeth\'s face contorts in horror at your description of the dwarf\'s death and the implications for Rualeth\'s mission.>$B$BI understand why he felt he had to go in search of the eggs, but I wish he\'d thought to bring others along. His death will no doubt enrage Falstad Wildhammer, triggering retaliation against the trolls, and delaying my audience indefinitely.' WHERE `entry`=9475;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Upon the altar is a heap of bones that appear to have belonged to a dwarven male. No identifying features remain, but you decide to search the body for confirmation that these are the remains of Featherbeard.' WHERE `entry`=9476;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You know, maybe we can become friends after all. Follow me; we don\'t want to have to share this with the others now, do we?' WHERE `entry`=9483;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Withstanding the numerous claws and bites from the dragonhawk is a sign of your tenacity. Do you have the strength to learn more?' WHERE `entry`=9484;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Have you mastered the dragonhawk?' WHERE `entry`=9484;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you see $N, there is nothing left for me to teach you at this time. You already understand what it is to befriend those you once hunted. You need only to choose one of nature\'s allies with traits that match your own.' WHERE `entry`=9485;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Have you mastered the mistbat?' WHERE `entry`=9485;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have shown both strength and tenacity. There remains the final test until you can tame without the use of magic.' WHERE `entry`=9486;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Have you hunted alongside the springpaw?' WHERE `entry`=9486;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Such a waste, using magic to construct beings of physical strength. I always thought that\'s why we allied with the lesser races, after all.$B$BYou were good to destroy them so we can use what remains for a more suitable purpose.' WHERE `entry`=9487;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You really don\'t need to know the intricacies of crafting a magical robe, $N, you just need to know what to bring me.$B$BAnd let me be honest, you brought enough for several robes. The profit I\'ll make should more than cover the costs to make your robe, and even enough to buy myself something nice. Looks like the thanks belong to you!' WHERE `entry`=9488;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Already the rangers speak of your blessings with awe and respect. Now you can see how the Light serves us, allowing us to help others, but only after we have helped ourselves.' WHERE `entry`=9489;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Yes, I remember these sharp claws!$B$BTake this reward, $N. That was a dangerous task you just did. You deserve every bit of this reward.' WHERE `entry`=9490;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is the ring, is it? Not much to look at, but you know what they say about one elves\' trash...$B$BAnd let\'s not forget your payment. Don\'t feel shy about spending it right here sister!' WHERE `entry`=9491;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. With your victory in Hellfire Citadel, we have struck a major blow against the orcs.$B$BI must speak with Field Commander Romus about following up and ensuring that the orcs stay on the defensive. Now that we\'ve been reinforced, we can do far more than simply defend Honor Hold.' WHERE `entry`=9492;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That is excellent news, indeed, $N. With progress to report from Hellfire Citadel, perhaps we can afford to turn our attention to the Fel Horde presence other parts of the peninsula and Outland as a whole.' WHERE `entry`=9493;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done! I can\'t hope to replicate the feats of Grand Warlock Nethekurse, nor should I aspire to, but we would be fools to ignore the power of the fel embers.$B$BHowever, there are those who would forbid the type of research I\'m about to embark upon, and for that reason, I must keep my efforts secret. Please do not speak of this to anyone, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9494;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have done well, $N. In his prime, Kargath Bladefist was a fine warrior, a hero and example to his people.$B$BHis death is a blow to us all, but especially to Warchief Thrall. Whatever happened to him in his final days, we should not forget the orc Kargath once was, nor the lessons to be learned from his downfall.$B$BFor your service to the Horde, $N, you are to be rewarded with your choice from among these weapons.' WHERE `entry`=9495;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent job, $N. With the legionnaires broken, it will be easier to face the Fel Horde on the battlefield, though they remain a formidable enemy.' WHERE `entry`=9496;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Welcome to Falcon Watch, $R. All our Horde allies are welcome here, especially those recommended by Martik.' WHERE `entry`=9498;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Welcome to Falcon Watch, $Gbrother:sister;. Many other blood elves haven\'t been fortunate enough to make it this far.$B$BIt\'s a terrible shame; our work in Outland has just begun.' WHERE `entry`=9499;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We meet again. I have been watching your progress from afar, $C, and I am pleased.$B$BThe time has come for you to commune with the element of water, to learn its mysteries and give yourself over to the water so that you might in turn learn to master it.' WHERE `entry`=9500;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Do not fear, $N. While you are here we will speak using our minds.$B$BI am grateful to Farseer Nobundo for sending you to me. There is a great disturbance that is polluting the waters on and around Bloodmyst Isle. Not even the blind would fail to notice the effect this is having on its creatures and the environment.$B$BYou and I will work together to stop this corruption before it spreads further.' WHERE `entry`=9501;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We meet again. I have been watching your progress from afar, $C, and I am pleased.$B$BThe time has come for you to commune with the element of water, to learn its mysteries and give yourself over to the water so that you might in turn learn to master it.' WHERE `entry`=9502;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, $C. These should be enough so that I can examine this corruption. Then we will have a better idea of how to proceed.' WHERE `entry`=9503;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='It is worse than I feared. The corruption is very potent and if unchecked it could spread to the ocean currents and be carried throughout all of Azeroth!$B$BWe are going to need a sample of the purest water to counter this malignancy. There is a forest on the nearby continent of Kalimdor named Ashenvale. Near its southwestern border is a place called the Ruins of Stardust.$B$BTake this bota bag and fill it with the water from the fountain on the small island at the center of the ruins. Hurry, $N!',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Water parts easily, yet put enough of it together and it will create an unstoppable force. It washes away earth and fire, and easily pushes air out of the way.$B$BWe are that unstoppable force, $N, not those that have poisoned Bloodmyst Isle!' WHERE `entry`=9504;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You say that you\'ve found one of our crew and that she is injured? I will send one of my crewmen to your village immediately!' WHERE `entry`=9505;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re a resourceful one! With our navigation gear, we can figure out just how far we\'ve veered off course.$B$BBut wait, what\'s this? There\'s something rolled up in the map. Let me see...$B$BThese are orders from Mogul Razdunk of the Venture Company. According to these plans, they\'re here to strip-mine the island of the crystal wreckage, then hijack our ships once they\'re finished.$B$BBy Bronzebeard\'s bushy brow! This is why they forced us to land? How could they know of our plans?$B$BI smell a traitor...' WHERE `entry`=9506;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is done then!  The crisis is averted and you have put in motion the restoration of the water on Bloodmyst Isle. Over time, the water, in conjunction with the other elements, will heal itself.$B$BIt is unfortunate that the blood elves cannot see that by contaminating their surroundings they\'re killing themselves off as well!' WHERE `entry`=9508;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have comported yourself with wisdom beyond your years, $N. I can sense that the water element is pleased with your actions. It will be my great honor to take the pure water that you bear and combine its essence into your new water totem.$B$BRemember well the lessons of water as you go forward and you will gain an even greater understanding and mastery of the element.' WHERE `entry`=9509;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Bless yer heart. stranger. This\'ll go a long ways in liftin\' the morale o\' the crew.' WHERE `entry`=9512;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Elune be praised! The restless spirits may find tranquility after all.' WHERE `entry`=9513;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I can\'t read these runes but I know someone who can...' WHERE `entry`=9514;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='With Warlord Sriss\'tiz dead, the possibility of a naga invasion is now only a distant memory. We are safe, for the time being...$N$NI must admit, I was wrong to think badly of you, $N. You have shown that you are nothing like the filth that was Archimonde. Accept this as a gift from the night elves.' WHERE `entry`=9515;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have my respect and thanks, $C. Perhaps we\'ll be able to create a new home here without having to worry about the Burning Legion yet again.' WHERE `entry`=9516;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Wood cut with orcs\' crude blades is warped as surely as that exposed to elemental extremes. Nothing sound can be built with it, but I shall purify it and return it to Architect Nemos and his men for their use. Some good will come from this tragedy, after all.' WHERE `entry`=9517;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='At last we have sent a message that the orcs won\'t dare ignore. Any overseer or foreman who sets foot within the camp to replace Gorthak will feel my wrath!$B$BWe must press our advantage, $N, and never rest until the Warsong Lumber Camp is a distant memory and a glade of trees stands upon that ground.' WHERE `entry`=9518;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent work, $N. There is certainly a latent power here, one that not even constant exposure to the corruption of the satyr can dim. Do you see how it still shines, after all these years?' WHERE `entry`=9519;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='By the Seven Crystals of Ata\'mal, this cannot be!  They plan to attack us here at Forest Song?!$B$BNot on my watch!$B$B<Vindicator Vedaar crumples the demon-scrawled plans in his fist.>$B$BNo. We will not allow this to happen!' WHERE `entry`=9520;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for delivering this report, $C. From what Sentinel Luciel writes, it seems our worst fears have come to pass. With each advance we make, the Horde appears more determined to do as much damage as possible.$B$BWe can\'t afford to back down; the fate of our ancestral lands hangs in the balance. With more people like you on the frontlines, I\'m certain we could triumph. Will you join our fight?' WHERE `entry`=9521;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Never again will the Burning Legion threaten us here! You have delivered us from a fight we very likely would have lost, $C.$B$BI give you thanks and the deepest gratitude of the Hand of Argus. It honors me to have you at our side.' WHERE `entry`=9522;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='My pappy would be proud! His boy strikes it big at the first set of night elf ruins he comes across... With your help, of course. Yes, don\'t worry, I won\'t leave you out of the discovery. You\'re a $R, right? Right, sure... $R. They\'ll learn all about you in Ironforge.' WHERE `entry`=9523;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I thank you, $N. I must admit I didn\'t expect a rescue party to be on its way.$B$BI will round up the remaining prisoners and lead them back to Honor Hold.' WHERE `entry`=9524;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve brightened my day, $C. When I die, I will make sure it\'s in the battlefield... covered in the blood of my opponents and taking them down with me.' WHERE `entry`=9525;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good. Though it may take a great deal of your years for the seedlings to grow into ancients, in the fullness of time they will aid us in our fight against the demons at Felfire Hill.$B$BGo in peace, little $Gbrother:sister;.' WHERE `entry`=9526;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, $N. Their spirits will be at peace now.' WHERE `entry`=9527;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Tears of joy stream down Cowlen\'s face.>$B$BHow can I ever repay you for this, $N? Please, take this heirloom. It symbolizes a sacred bond of friendship, trust and love amongst night elves. You are a $Gbrother:sister; to me - from this day until the end of time...' WHERE `entry`=9528;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Hail, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9528;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='As you gaze into the stone, your vision begins to swirl...' WHERE `entry`=9529;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I must warn you, what I ask of you next will be dangerous. I won\'t think less of you if you decide not to help me out, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9530;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I hope you can see I am deep under cover... at least I was.' WHERE `entry`=9532;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s good to see another new arrival here at Forest Song.$B$BVindicator Palanaar is sending as much help as she can muster and each set of hands is appreciated.$B$BTake a look around, $C. It may not be much now, but with time and help from our night elf allies, we\'ll build a settlement worthy of calling home. There is much to be done here and any help you can provide would be welcome.' WHERE `entry`=9533;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That\'s better!  There\'s nothing quite like ridding our world of a demon. And they make for worthy opponents as well, unlike the weak races of the Alliance.' WHERE `entry`=9534;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Dreadlords!  They plan to attack us here at Splintertree Post?!$B$BNot while I still draw breath!$B$B<Valusha crumples the demon-scrawled plans in her fist.>$B$BNo. We will not allow this to happen!  They are a blight upon our world!' WHERE `entry`=9535;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Kill Gorgannon and Diathorus the Seeker, and then return to Velusha at Splintertree Post in Ashenvale.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Never again will the Burning Legion make slaves of the orcs, or any other race of the Horde!$B$BBravely fought, $C! You have the true heart of the Horde beating inside of you! You give us much honor!' WHERE `entry`=9536;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Incredible! This was all part of their master plan!$B$BThis information must reach the king and your own leaders. The implications are staggering.' WHERE `entry`=9537;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The totem has various primal markings. You see owls, bears, wolves and stags carved into the surface.$B$BYou note a strange collection of symbols that makes your mouth form the word A-K-I-D-A.' WHERE `entry`=9538;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The totem has various primal markings. You see owls, bears, wolves and stags carved into the surface of the totem.$B$BYou note a strange collection of symbols that makes your mouth form the word C-O-O.' WHERE `entry`=9539;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The totem has various primal markings. You see owls, bears, wolves and stags carved into the surface of the totem.$B$BYou note a strange collection of symbols that makes your mouth form the word T-I-K-T-I.' WHERE `entry`=9540;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The totem has various primal markings. You see owls, bears, wolves and stags carved into the surface of the totem.$B$BYou note a strange collection of symbols that makes your mouth form the word Y-O-R.' WHERE `entry`=9541;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='As you read the totem, your mouth forms the word V-A-R-K. You understand this to mean justice.' WHERE `entry`=9542;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Can I offer you any assistance, $N? You sound troubled.' WHERE `entry`=9543;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The prophecy spoke of one that would rise and deliver us from the oppressive grasp of Bristlelimb -- that the spirits themselves would herald the arrival of this hero.$B$BAnd now, you have come.$B$BI humble myself before you, great one.' WHERE `entry`=9544;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I hope the vision you witnessed helped you gain some perspective on Sedai\'s death. The relic showed you a likely series of events leading up to the present. The truth may have been different, we\'ll never know for sure.$B$BWould you act differently knowing what you know now?$B$BWho can say whether our conflict with the orcs will continue?  What\'s important is to remain open to the possibilities.' WHERE `entry`=9545;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='And finally we come to it, the last of the four great elements: air. Do you think yourself wise enough to continue, $N?' WHERE `entry`=9547;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is fantastic! The theft of my equipment has given me more insight into the nature of these murlocs than I could have possibly gained in weeks of observations!$B$BI know what I\'m going to say in my report already.$B$B\'When faced with the products of a technologically superior culture, the Blacksilt displayed none of the curiosity characteristic of emerging cultures in humanoid species.\'$B$BIt\'s brilliant! The gentlemen in Ironforge are going to love it! I can\'t thank you enough, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9548;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Astounding, simply astounding! These are perfect, $N. I can already see them under the glass in the museum in Ironforge. The text for the display is virtually writing itself in my head!$B$BYour help has been invaluable in getting my studies back on track. How do you spell your name? I\'ll make sure it appears in my report as co-author.$B$BOne of the chaps on the ship gave me this \'treasure map\' to cover a gambling debt, but mythology isn\'t my area of study. Superstitious lot, sailors.' WHERE `entry`=9549;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Examining the book carefully, you conclude that it must be a journal. Its pages are filled with an elegant script differing from that of the map. The text of many of the pages is obscured by drawings and writing in the mapmaker\'s hand.$B$BIt\'s nearly impossible to make out the text beneath the mapmaker\'s tales of drunken carousing during shore leave.' WHERE `entry`=9550;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='And finally we come to it, the last of the four great elements: air. Do you think yourself wise enough to continue, $N?' WHERE `entry`=9551;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It was whispered to me on the winds that you would be coming, $C.$B$BFarseer Nobundo thinks very highly of you, and from what I have heard of your travels, so do I.' WHERE `entry`=9552;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I have been awaiting your arrival, $C. You come seeking wisdom, and something else I sense.$B$BVery well, let us begin.' WHERE `entry`=9553;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I am proud of you, $N. You have persevered where others falter, and in the process you\'ve gained a greater understanding of the elements and yourself. Remember their lessons as you go through life and you will be the wiser for it.$B$BNow, hand me the whorl from Susurrus so that I may imbue it into your air totem. As with the other totems, it will serve as both a focus and a reminder of the connection that you have forged with the elements.' WHERE `entry`=9554;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Greetings. It is always heartening to meet a $R who is open to the way of shamanism. There are so few.$B$BYou have learned not to judge the flame for its outward appearance, just as you should not judge mine.$B$BYou are here because you are ready to create your fire totem.' WHERE `entry`=9555;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hmm... this is most intriguing. Yes, I should be able to make out what the original author wrote in the pages of this book.$B$BI should have everything I need for the process. This should only take a moment.' WHERE `entry`=9557;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='How\'d you find us, $C?  No matter, I imagine you were sent here to give us a hand. Let\'s get to work then!' WHERE `entry`=9558;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='For centuries, we lived in relative peace with the creatures of the land. Several months ago, Kurz began to see dark omens. The peace that we enjoyed for so long was to be lost. The extent of the catastrophe could not be known!$B$BSo it would be that the gods would shatter our land - turning both friend and foe against us. But there was something else... Amidst the chaos, a hero would rise: A hero not of Stillpine blood. The Promised One would deliver us from devastation.$B$BThat prophesied hero was you.' WHERE `entry`=9559;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Not only is the prophecy true, this armor is also amazing! Surely it is armor fit for a champion! And I will sell it to you at discounted prices, furless one.$B$BI jest... The first piece is complimentary.' WHERE `entry`=9560;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Grasses and shrubs cover an unnatural bulge in the earth.$B$BA few minutes spent digging reveals an old box, almost certainly the one mentioned in Nolkai\'s journal.' WHERE `entry`=9561;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Mmmmm... Delicious grain... Parkat will be delighted!' WHERE `entry`=9562;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Why. yes! You seem to be quite an OK $R. I suppose I can trust you.' WHERE `entry`=9563;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Gurf spits on the clump of fur and tries to affix it to the hairless patch on his backside.>$B$BThis will have to do for now! Hopefully one of the $C will be able to repair the damage.' WHERE `entry`=9564;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The blood crystal radiates a sickly aura that seeps into the water of the cave.' WHERE `entry`=9565;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These blood crystals that you saw; my scouts have seen many more to the north.$B$BI thank you for aid but now ask that you leave me to confer with the elders. I will call for you once I have spoken with the other elders of the village.' WHERE `entry`=9566;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. Let me see what I can learn from this glyph, so we can plan our next move.' WHERE `entry`=9567;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Without their leader, and with the recovery of the corrupted crystals underway, we can safely keep the satyr in check. Light knows how many more of these wretched creatures are out there.$B$BHarbinger Mikolaas and I are grateful for the help you\'ve provided in dealing with the satyr before they could become a larger threat. Your work stands as a reminder that vigilance is the key to victory against the Legion and its minions.' WHERE `entry`=9569;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Promised One has emerged victorious!$B$BThe prophecy is nearly complete. Now about that hide...' WHERE `entry`=9570;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is the strongest armor I\'ve ever made! Make good use of it, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9571;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s a good start. With those three dead their forces should be in disarray. And with their artillery up there silenced we\'ll have an easier time getting close enough to take the citadel!$B$BBut there\'s more to this than meets the eye - I can feel it - so I\'m going to have something else for you to do.$B$BFor the time being, though, you\'ve done well. Take your pick of any of these from the Thrallmar armory.' WHERE `entry`=9572;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This may very well be the opportunity that we needed! I will send an attack at once! The Stillpine thank you for your service, $N!' WHERE `entry`=9573;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='There\'s more than enough here for my research. Thank you, $N. If you find any other evidence that the crystals are corrupting Bloodmyst\'s native creatures, let me know right away.' WHERE `entry`=9574;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Do you know what I hate worse than being wrong? Losing gold on a bet that you couldn\'t pull it off, sweetheart.$B$BOutstanding! With those three dead their forces should be in disarray. And with their artillery up there silenced we\'ll have an easier time getting close enough to take the citadel!$B$BI have a feeling there\'s more to this than meets the eye, though' WHERE `entry`=9575;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is most curious, $C. I don\'t believe we\'ve ever seen the murlocs wearing any kind of adornment before.$B$BGiven the corrupting influence that the crystal shards are known to have, the murloc that wore this pendant must have believed it granted him power over his fellows. I wouldn\'t be surprised if he had rapidly outgrown his fellow murlocs and gained in strength.' WHERE `entry`=9576;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The corpse appears to be dressed in the manner of an Exodar technician, but the pendant described by Morae is absent.' WHERE `entry`=9578;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<You tell Morae of your findings in the wreckage of the Cryo-Core.>$B$BSo... he\'s...$B$BI guess I knew on some level, but just wouldn\'t let myself believe it. It\'s not the news I was hoping for, but you have my deepest thanks for finding Galaen.' WHERE `entry`=9579;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This will keep us supplied for quite a while, and preparing it for consumption will certainly keep me busy. Thank you for your help, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9580;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This crystal shard will give our researchers a baseline to compare against samples from other parts of the island, since it comes from one of Bloodmyst\'s less corrupted regions.$B$BI won\'t be able to send it off until we have a full set of samples, but this is a great start. If you\'re willing to help gather the other samples, I\'ll see to it that you\'re rewarded for your efforts.' WHERE `entry`=9581;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Ruada nods solemnly.>$B$BThen it is done.$B$BYou are ready for your next lesson, $N, but I will not be the one to teach it to you.' WHERE `entry`=9582;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Harbinger Mikolaas examines the crystal shard.>$B$BThis shard is much different from the initial sample.$B$B<Harbinger Mikolaas holds the crystal up to catch the light.>$B$BDo you see how it pulsates like that? That\'s worrisome. I\'ll make a note in my report of the alterations the blood elves appear to have made to this crystal. Thank you again for your help, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9584;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Harbinger Mikolaas accepts the last crystal from you.>$B$BThat rounds out the set. All that remains to be done is to box them and send them to the Exodar.$B$B<The harbinger seems glad to be done with the task.>$B$BDon\'t get me wrong, $N, I\'m sure the research is valuable, but we\'re faced with a number of other pressing problems out here.' WHERE `entry`=9585;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for helping Tavara. So many are unfamiliar with these lands and find trouble where they least expect.$B$BIt would honor me if you were to wear these robes. They mark you as one of the protectors of Azure Watch and a devout follower of the Light.' WHERE `entry`=9586;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s signed by Illidan you say?! Let me have that.$B$B<The commander reads the letter, and then again a second time, thinking a moment before going on.>$B$BThis news that you bring is ominous indeed. Knowing this, we must accelerate our plans against Hellfire Citadel and this Blood Furnace. Because you have shown that you can get the job done, I want you to head up those plans.$B$BGunny will give you your next mission, though I suspect it will be far deadlier than your first.$B$BLight be with you, $N!' WHERE `entry`=9587;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s signed by Illidan you say?! Let me have that.$B$B<Nazgrel reads the letter, and then again a second time, thinking a moment before going on.>$B$BThis news that you bring is ominous indeed. Knowing this, we must accelerate our plans against Hellfire Citadel and this Blood Furnace. Because you have shown that you can get the job done, I want you to head up those plans!$B$BCenturion Caza\'rez will give you your next mission, though I suspect it will be far deadlier than your first.$B$BLok\'tar ogar, $N!' WHERE `entry`=9588;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Out-frikkin-standing!  As of right now Private $N, you are my favorite person on the sorry remains of this sorry planet!$B$BI\'m sure that the eggheads are going to wet themselves when I hand that blood over to them for study. Who knows, maybe we\'ll find a new weapon in the fight against those damned fel orcs?' WHERE `entry`=9589;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I am impressed with your abilities, $N. Not once, but twice now you have infiltrated Hellfire Citadel for us and accomplished what was asked of you.$B$BI will see to it that this blood is delivered to those who can unlock its mysteries. Who knows, perhaps we can find a way to reverse the process?' WHERE `entry`=9590;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I\'m sure the first thing you learned was how unsympathetic the crawler was during the bonding process. It\'s all claws until they know you aren\'t there to throw them into a boiling pot.' WHERE `entry`=9591;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Were you able to harness the magic of the totem to befriend a barbed crawler?  They are feisty little creatures!' WHERE `entry`=9591;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Looks like the timberstrider didn\'t peck your eyes out.$B$B<Kella looks away for a moment.>$B$BNot that I thought that would happen, of course!' WHERE `entry`=9592;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='The timberstrider is a powerful bird, often misjudged by predators with dire results.' WHERE `entry`=9592;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I must say, $N, you have learned far more quickly than I first imagined. Looks like we won\'t need to use this last taming totem. And honestly, I\'m not even sure what it is. It appears to be some sort of monstrous lizard with wings and a long tail. Oh well, perhaps another time!$B$BYou\'ve experienced enough to try it on your own now, without the aid of a taming totem. Good luck!' WHERE `entry`=9593;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='The nightstalker is basically a big kitty with razor sharp claws and an appetite for flesh...' WHERE `entry`=9593;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well in bringing this to me, $N. This is, without a doubt, an armor fragment from a felguard.$B$BThen, it is as I feared. The Nazzivus satyr are renewing their contacts with the Burning Legion. If we don\'t stop them, the satyrs and their demonic allies will overrun us. I will notify Harbinger Mikolaas right away.' WHERE `entry`=9594;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='With every spell you must steel yourself against its seductive lure, using it only as needed for the purposes of good. Hopefully the wraith granted a glimpse of what you might turn into should you become careless--a mindless slave to magic.' WHERE `entry`=9595;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `title_loc6`='<UNUSED>' WHERE `entry`=9597;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve spent time reading the book, I hope?$B$BThen you should be prepared to have yourself tested. There are always tasks to be done in the wake of the Exodar\'s crash throughout these new lands: acts of compassion and understanding...people who need help...creatures to slay...$B$BBy proving you have the patience to help others, especially those who are less fortunate, you prove that you are a servant of the Light and of sound mind.' WHERE `entry`=9598;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `title_loc6`='<UNUSED>',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you $N! I am glad that Young Furbolg Shaman is fine.$B$BYou truly are blessed with the Light! Therefore, you shall use it to brign back the light in everyone!' WHERE `entry`=9599;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='who.....who are you? .....Jol? Yes! Praise the Light! We are ok thanks to the forces Jol sent us to help in our battles. Yes I am fine...although I cannot say the same about my brothers....' WHERE `entry`=9600;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ahh... it seems it is time.$B$B<Mehlar nods knowingly.>' WHERE `entry`=9601;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Exarch Menelaous takes the letter from you and begins to read it.>$B$BDamn them... Damn them all to the Nether. They\'ve had a spy watching everything that we\'ve done! And for how long?$B$BI will notify Velen at once!$B$BYou\'ve done us a great service, $N. Be on guard as I will be contacting you once the Prophet has given me instruction as to what to do.' WHERE `entry`=9602;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you need to go to the Exodar?$B$BThat\'s going to be a long trip, but don\'t worry, I have a way to get you there very quickly.' WHERE `entry`=9603;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you\'ve brought Topher\'s list. Excellent! I was hoping to receive this today. Let\'s see what he needs.$B$B<Nurguni reads over the list and begins placing various items in a box.>$B$BThat\'s most of what he requested. The pieces for the beds are simply too large to be delivered by hippogryph, but I\'ll make arrangements to have them sent by wagon.' WHERE `entry`=9604;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you\'re headed back to Blood Watch with this package? No problem at all, $C. Just speak with me again and we\'ll get you on your way with those supplies.' WHERE `entry`=9605;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='If I remember correctly, Azure Watch\'s hippogryph master is Zaldaan. If you\'ve spoken to him before, then you can take one of my hippogryphs to him.$B$BThat\'s a good lesson to know: hippogryphs are always trained to fly to their capital city, but they\'ll only take you to a remote hippogryph master after you\'ve already been there.$B$BSince you arrived on one of Zaldaan\'s hippogryphs, you can also use that route to return to Azure Watch with the caregiver\'s supplies.',`objectives_loc6`='Speak with Stephanos to purchase a hippogryph ride back to Azure Watch. Once you have arrived, deliver Nurguni\'s Supplies to Caregiver Chellan.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`=' Splendid! Now, I\'ll finally be able to set up some beds and a first aid station so that we can better treat the wounded and any survivors we encounter. I can\'t thank you enough for your help, $N. You have my thanks and that of the Azure Watch\'s vindicators.' WHERE `entry`=9606;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='THEY HAVE A PIT LORD?!$B$B<The force commander looks around at the stares of the others and then lowers his voice to a whisper.>$B$BThat seals it. They must be using the blood from this pit lord to create new fel orcs that are somehow not aligned with the Burning Legion. And if they can do this to the brown orcs, they can do it to the green ones too. With all of the new Horde orcs streaming in through the Dark Portal, that\'s not good!$B$BWe must strike at the heart of their military might, and soon!' WHERE `entry`=9607;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Private, report! Have you scouted all of the Blood Furnace yet?' WHERE `entry`=9607;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='THEY HAVE A PIT LORD?!$B$B<Nazgrel notices the glances of the others assembled and lowers his voice to a whisper.>$B$BThat seals it. They must be using the blood from this pit lord to create new fel orcs that are somehow not aligned with the Burning Legion. And if they can do this to the Mag\'har brown orcs, they can do it to us!$B$BWe\'ll have to strike at the heart of their military might, and soon!' WHERE `entry`=9608;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Have you scouted all of the Blood Furnace yet? What do you have to tell me?' WHERE `entry`=9608;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What?  A draenei sent you here from the Harborage?  How odd.$B$BWell, I\'m not one to turn down assistance. Thanks for coming, $C!' WHERE `entry`=9609;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I thank you, $C. The study of these artifacts should keep me occupied for some time. How else are we Broken and draenei to fit in if we do not come to understand the history of your world?' WHERE `entry`=9610;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. Well done indeed! You are turning out to be a special $R - a cut above the others of your age. Take this as a reward!' WHERE `entry`=9612;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='By the beardless, geometric head of O\'ros! It is good you brought this to me, $N. These blood elves are out for... well, blood. Velen will be informed at once! Take this as a reward.' WHERE `entry`=9616;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='$N, it is good you have come. Our list of allies grows thin, and even those who share our cause are not completely trusted. It is because of this that we, the rangers, turn to nature for aid.$B$BIn the allies of the forest we find a deep bond that does not know deceit.' WHERE `entry`=9617;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='All of these reports are from Keltus?  He\'s been quite busy, that\'s for sure.$B$BKeltus is a $C among rogues--he rarely follows orders to the letter, and often takes matters into his own hands!  Don\'t take that wrong, however, as he is one of my most trusted spies and we would be lost without him.$B$BYou\'ve done an exemplary job today. Please accept this blade and guide it into our enemy\'s back.' WHERE `entry`=9618;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I\'m impressed you are standing here, $N. Many an apprentice has perished to the voidwalker, or even the voidstone itself.$B$BThe voidwalker is now yours to command. Use your new servant well.' WHERE `entry`=9619;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The bodies of the $R survey team are scattered all over the ground here, pierced by naga weaponry. The area is littered with the remains of their supplies and survey equipment, but their data crystals are nowhere to be seen.' WHERE `entry`=9620;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is done then. The foul traitor got what he deserved.$B$BYou did this yourself?  An impressive feat that proves that your race remains worthy, $N.$B$BI see that Lor\'themar has additional news that will greatly improve his relations with Thrall.' WHERE `entry`=9621;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Visions you say? Interesting... And this prophecy has come to pass?$B$BBut you say they saw the power core of the Exodar? And O\'ros was also in the vision? What can it mean?' WHERE `entry`=9622;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Torallius sighs.>$B$BAlright, let me have a look at those orders.' WHERE `entry`=9623;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Did you have a difficult time finding enough? It\'s been taking me longer with each trip.$B$BSoon, I\'ll have to stop altogether since I won\'t be able to spare the time. Thank you for gathering the pears for me, $N. It gives me a chance to make a last pie or two before the season\'s out.' WHERE `entry`=9624;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well ya made it this far! Let\'s put ya to work before you get too bloodied up.' WHERE `entry`=9625;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Thrall begins to read the letter.>$B$BSylvanas is a persistent one. So she\'s sent one of Silvermoon\'s own champions... how does this change anything?' WHERE `entry`=9626;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Your work has helped advance our race\'s cause a tremendous deal. Not only does Thrall believe we\'re capable of handling ourselves in the face of the enemy, he also believes he can use our link with Outland as a means to reach his people.$B$BNot exactly the truth, but not a lie either.$B$BBrace yourself for great changes, $N. We are now officially part of the Horde.' WHERE `entry`=9627;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<You tell Harbinger Mikolaas of the survey team\'s fate. He accepts the crystal from you, but remains silent for a long moment.>$B$BThey were good men, $N, and they knew their mission would be dangerous. I\'m grateful for your help in locating the team and recovering the crystal.$B$B<The harbinger\'s fists clench.>$B$BWe\'ve lost too many good men already, and our mission has only just begun.' WHERE `entry`=9628;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. I was worried that the marking device might malfunction, but it seems like everything went according to plan.' WHERE `entry`=9629;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Archmage Alturus at Deadwind Pass wants you go into Karazhan and speak to Wravien.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='A vast wealth of information... I could spend years here!  I\'m sure Dalaran will understand...' WHERE `entry`=9630;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Alturus wants to raise a whole dragon back from the dead? Not an easy task by any stretch of the imagination.$B$BLet us discuss how we can be of mutual assistance, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9631;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Take the Letter of Introduction to Huntress Kella Nightbow.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='I can help you get to Auberdine. Fortunately, it\'s only a short boat trip away!' WHERE `entry`=9632;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Thundris accepts the letter from you and reads it quickly, nodding.>$B$BThe isles the $R call Azuremyst and Bloodmyst were inhabited long ago by my people. Some of the threats faced by Anchorite Paetheus and his brethren are ancient enemies of the night elves.$B$BI am certain that the people of Auberdine are willing to provide what aid we can to our new allies. As soon as I have spoken with the townspeople and the sentinels, I will send word to Paetheus.' WHERE `entry`=9633;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. The ravager population will bear watching for some time to come, but we\'ve made a good start.' WHERE `entry`=9634;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Alright!  Now if we only had a stretchy loop, a parchment clamp, a guzzle tube and some sticky duck ribbon. Then we could really make something!$B$BOk, ok, I guess you\'ve earned this, $N. Have fun!' WHERE `entry`=9635;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Shiny!  And really, what engineer ever has enough spare parts just hanging around?  Ooh, maybe I could sell off the extra and buy me some of that Tigule and Foror\'s Strawberry Ice Cream?!  I just love strawberries!  Do you think they have any around here?$B$BOk, ok, I guess you\'ve earned this, $N. Have fun!' WHERE `entry`=9636;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent, $N. I\'ve been trying to attempt these books for a very long time. It is fortunate that we were able to be of mutual assistance.' WHERE `entry`=9637;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Can\'t you see I\'m in the middle of something here? What do you want?' WHERE `entry`=9638;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The journal you speak of... I was sent here to look for it wasn\'t I?' WHERE `entry`=9639;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Did you find what you were looking for? You were looking for something, weren\'t you?' WHERE `entry`=9640;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done. These will provide the raw materials for another batch of enhancement crystals.$B$BYou\'re welcome to choose from among the three kinds of crystals I can make. I find each of them useful for stalking different kinds of prey.' WHERE `entry`=9641;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Very well, here are the crystals that I have, $N. Use them well.' WHERE `entry`=9642;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These seem sturdy enough to do the job. Thank you for your help, $N. Your contribution to Blood Watch\'s defense will not be forgotten.' WHERE `entry`=9643;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Our preparations are complete. I have put the materials you gathered into this urn. Take it to the Master\'s Terrace, where the fight took place, and set it on fire.$B$BThe energy released will bring life back to the charred remains of Arcanagos. Defeat the creature and retrieve its essence immediately!  You will need to take it to Alturus.$B$BShould you fail, the stars predict you will have let a great terror loose upon the skies.$B$BA terror known as Nightbane!',`objectives_loc6`='Go to the Master\'s Terrace in Karazhan and use Kalynna\'s Urn to summon Nightbane. Retrieve the Faint Arcane Essence from Nightbane\'s corpse and bring it to Archmage Alturus.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is astounding! Not only have you brought back Medivh\'s Journal, but you\'ve also retrieved a fragment of his very essence.$B$BAs faint as this lingering essence is, it will reveal to us vital information about Medivh. We will not forget this, $C.' WHERE `entry`=9644;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is a shame that the agents we sent succumbed to Karazhan\'s magic. At least you managed to obtain what they were after.' WHERE `entry`=9645;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='You\'ve returned! What news do you bring?' WHERE `entry`=9645;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done. From what I\'ve heard, it couldn\'t have been an easy fight. You\'ve more than earned your reward, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9646;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='In time, we\'ll have to devise a plan for returning the species to its native state, but for now, periodically culling their numbers is about the best we can hope for. Thank you for your help, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9647;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well, I did warn you - did I not? Hopefully this payment more than makes up for the mild discomfort that you may have suffered. Return to me when you have gained strength and perhaps I will have another job for you - mushrooms of course!' WHERE `entry`=9648;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I hope this wasn\'t too strenuous a task, $N. Once again you have proven yourself a competent and considerate $R. I offer my gratitude and a small bit of monetary compensation.' WHERE `entry`=9649;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='<TXT>' WHERE `entry`=9650;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='<TXT>' WHERE `entry`=9651;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. This was a difficult test of your abilities, but you have passed with flying colors. To become a soldier of the Hand of Argus, you must pass many such tests.' WHERE `entry`=9663;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Very good, $N. It will be important for us to hold these towers against future attacks, and for that we may need your assistance until reinforcements can be brought in to secure the area.' WHERE `entry`=9664;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Capture Northpass Tower',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Capture Plaguewood Tower' WHERE `entry`=9664;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is good news, $N. It will be a constant struggle here in the Plaguelands until we have fully driven back the forces of the Alliance.$B$BUntil that day, I hope that we will have your continued assistance.' WHERE `entry`=9665;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Capture Northpass Tower',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Capture Plaguewood Tower' WHERE `entry`=9665;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I am sorry that you had to do that, $N. Heavy-handed violence is not the $R way, but sometimes it is the only way.$B$BThis is one of life\'s truths that many do not understand until it is too late. So it was for our people, when we were slaughtered at the hands of the orcs.$B$BBecoming a Hand of Argus is a process of rebirth. And with birth comes pain...' WHERE `entry`=9666;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Is it done?' WHERE `entry`=9666;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Once again you have proven yourself to be all that was prophesied. You have the eternal gratitude of the high chief $N -- and these Stillpine relics to choose from...' WHERE `entry`=9667;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I had a feeling that you would make it this far, $C. If you are willing to go further, I am willing to teach you...' WHERE `entry`=9668;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Incredible! Did you find any survivors?$B$B<Achelus lowers his voice to a whisper.>$B$BI\'ll be honest, $N; nobody else was willing to take on this mission. You are a brave $C...' WHERE `entry`=9669;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You rescued over half the team! Word of your deed will definitely get back to Blood Watch and the exarch. Thanks again, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9670;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText1_loc6`='Expedition Researcher Freed' WHERE `entry`=9670;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Are you $N? It\'s about time! I\'d just about given up on finding you!$B$BThere\'s an urgent message waiting for you at the mailbox. The person that gave it to me was a human admiral from Azuremyst. Admiral Odesy-something... the name escapes me. He said you would know who he was.$B$B<Hermesius shrugs.>' WHERE `entry`=9671;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Have you heard of the bloodcurse, landlubber? No, of course you haven\'t. The bloodcurse is what sunk all these ships. The spoiled, desecrated part of the water here is known as Bloodcursed Reef - a part of the world you never want to visit. I\'ve been here myself for 20 years.$B$BScurvy my foot! I died on these wild shores as food for the dragons... Ah, but that\'s another story for another time. Right now, we have to help the poor souls that are trapped in that reef.' WHERE `entry`=9672;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you\'ve learned a bit, have you?$B$B<Halthenis looks at you carefully.>$B$BYou\'ll serve the city, and our greater cause, well with your newly-learned skills. Allow me a moment to show you how to train your pet to do some interesting tricks, like disemboweling your enemy, and you can be on your way.' WHERE `entry`=9673;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A good start, but there\'s much more to be done!' WHERE `entry`=9674;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Knowing how to feed and revive your pet from death is not just an extra "tidbit" as your last teacher so mildly put it. Even more so, training allows your pet to improve in ways they couldn\'t have on their own.$B$BI\'ve already learned much from the furbolgs, so pay attention and I\'ll pass the knowledge on to you.' WHERE `entry`=9675;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I am heartened by your initiative to speak with me. In the past I was responsible for the training of young paladins as they entered our order. This is a duty and privilege that I humbly take up once more. Your name has been mentioned as one who seeks to do good in the name of the Light. It would be my honor to guide you in your first steps as a $C.$B$BShall we begin?' WHERE `entry`=9676;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Welcome, young initiate. That you have answered my summons so promptly bodes well for you.$B$BLet us dispense with pleasantries, then, as they are best left to courtiers and their ilk.$B$BYour rapid progress has caught my attention, $N. We will see if you have taken your lessons to heart.' WHERE `entry`=9677;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I know what must be going through your mind.$B$BYes, I sent Stillblade to kill you.$B$BDo not take offense, $N; it was a necessary test. The Blood Knights are a brotherhood, but we must ensure that our brothers are alert and prepared at all times. Was it necessary to take Stillblade\'s life to make the point to you?$B$BYes, and that is as much a part of your training as any sword drill.' WHERE `entry`=9678;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText1_loc6`='Undergo the First Trial' WHERE `entry`=9678;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent! Though small in size, this fragment is teeming with energy, I can feel it!' WHERE `entry`=9680;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Welcome, young $C.$B$BThe power of the Blood Knights is taken from a being of immense power.$B$B<The magister gestures to the large, captive being in the center of the room.>$B$BIsn\'t it magnificent? \'Twas a gift from our beloved Prince Kael\'thas, and it is the foundation of the Blood Knights\' mastery of the Light. This creature begrudges us its power, so we have devised a method for claiming it on our own terms.' WHERE `entry`=9681;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have done the hopeless ones a great service, $N. There is but one final task: Destroy the leader of the Bloodcursed.' WHERE `entry`=9682;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did it! Hundreds of souls are grateful for all that you have done.$B$BAllow me to make an offering...' WHERE `entry`=9683;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Take this vessel, $N. The enchantment it bears will allow you to draw the last vestiges of the Light surrounding these magisters. They once tended the captive naaru and some of its energy yet remains within them.$B$BIt will be just enough to restore your comrade to life.$B$B.Do not worry about the magisters, $N. I have seen to their care, and Lord Solanar assures me that Lady Liadrin seeks a new source of power even now.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. The powers granted by the Light will never come \'naturally\' to the Blood Knights, but we are not so naive as to be thwarted by the will of a single being, however powerful.$B$BOur mastery of the arcane has unlocked this path and these powers for you, initiate. Few have the stomach or the aptitude to wield them, but I know you will not disappoint the order.' WHERE `entry`=9684;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Welcome back, initiate. Now that you know the truth about the source of our power and you have demonstrated your skill in wielding it, I will grant you the ability to resurrect the fallen in the field.$B$BStay true to the order and excel at your training and you will only continue to grow in power.' WHERE `entry`=9685;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N! You have proven yourself worthy of full membership in the Blood Knights and elevation to adept status. However, there are a few more tasks that remain before your induction can take place.' WHERE `entry`=9686;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='A Blood Knight would rather die than submit to the enemy. Remember that, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9686;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A ritual? The owlkin had lived in harmony with the land for thousands of years. Such a thing is an aberration!$B$BSuch a pity...' WHERE `entry`=9687;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='As reprehensible as your task was, it had to be done. Now you must look into the face of evil.' WHERE `entry`=9688;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='How long has it been? A thousand years? Ten-thousand perhaps? You have done me and the memory of my people a great service, $N. Please accept this item of power as a token of appreciation from Loreth\'Aran - in honor of your deeds.' WHERE `entry`=9689;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='When you are ready, I will tell you more about the trial you are to undergo. Make your preparations and speak to me again when you wish to begin.' WHERE `entry`=9690;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I knew you had the potential to pass the trial, $N. Your remaining duties are mostly ceremonial, but they are no less dangerous than staring down one of our champions with his weapon drawn. Listen closely, and I will tell you what else you must do to claim your new rank.' WHERE `entry`=9691;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent, $N. It\'s all here. All that remains is to forge the weapon.' WHERE `entry`=9692;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, $N... I\'ve heard about you. You\'re the one that made the Kessel Run in under 15 minutes, right? Bah, probably not.$B$BAre you ready to spill some blood in the name of the Light? For Velen? For Argus?$B$B<Boros laughs.>$B$BI\'ll slow down.' WHERE `entry`=9693;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have returned - and in one piece!$B$BI have some good news, $N. We have received some new information about the possible location of more survivors. A new crash site has been discovered! When I am done attending to those matters, I will call for you.' WHERE `entry`=9694;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Elysia reads from the document.>$B$BIf what this document says is true, the blood elves have opened a portal to the Outland! It would certainly explain their seemingly endless numbers...' WHERE `entry`=9696;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh, good... help finally!  There\'s just so much to do, and I need to stay here to organize it all.$B$BI hope that you\'re ready to get your hands dirty.' WHERE `entry`=9697;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Velen begins to read the document.>$B$BInteresting... This does indeed explain much.' WHERE `entry`=9698;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s a good plan, but a dangerous one. I\'m sure you\'ll be fine.' WHERE `entry`=9699;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='How many did you say you saw at the Warp Piston? Just how many times have they opened up this sun portal? This is very bad news...$B$BAlas, you have learned all that I am able to teach you, $N. Kuros will call for you when it is time.' WHERE `entry`=9700;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='I\'ve been hearing reports of strange creatures appearing in the area. Whether they are mutated indigenous animals or true void anomalies is something that you need to find out.' WHERE `entry`=9700;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What?!  The bog lords of Quagg Ridge are EATING the sporelings\' pods?  This isn\'t good!' WHERE `entry`=9701;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Back so soon? Your observation of the Sporeggar sporelings is critical to my research. I hope you aren\'t the type to rush things. Show patience and make certain that you have explored the entirety of the Spawning Glen before giving me your final report.' WHERE `entry`=9701;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is what you found?  That\'s odd. These husked mushroom remains are both unusual and somehow look familiar.$B$BI have to think on this a moment. Don\'t go anywhere!' WHERE `entry`=9702;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Just blood elves? No survivors? This is troubling. I\'ll need some time to think this through, $N. Perhaps Aesom or Boros have an assignment for you to complete.' WHERE `entry`=9703;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The outrunner\'s belongings have all been stolen with the exception of one package. It seems to match Alarion\'s description of Erona\'s package.' WHERE `entry`=9704;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='By the Sunwell!  That\'s the third outrunner we\'ve lost this month.$B$BI appreciate your courage in venturing into Dawning Street. The guards need to keep a closer eye on these blasted Wretched.' WHERE `entry`=9705;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Kuros\' face turns pale as he reads the journal; tears stream down his face.>$B$BSaruan was my master... my teacher... my mentor... I took his place among the Triumvirate only recently - after we had given up searching for him.$B$B<Kuros\' face contorts in anger.>$B$BMatis...' WHERE `entry`=9706;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It looks like you\'ve got everything I\'ll need. Let\'s get started!' WHERE `entry`=9707;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We definitely have a match here. And the presence of the ogres and what they were doing there explains everything. Now I get why it\'s called the Hewn Bog, duh!$B$BWe have to do something about this situation, but what?  We can\'t just wipe out all of those ogres; they have every bit as much a right to be here as any of the other creatures in the marsh!' WHERE `entry`=9708;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These are perfect!  Oh, thank you, $C!$B$BYou\'ve been ever so careful not to disturb the natural order of things, and we\'ve gathered so much information in such a short amount of time!$B$BNow, let\'s see if our little plan to grow a new food supply for the bog lords is going to work.' WHERE `entry`=9709;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Here it is, $N. Use it well in the service of Silvermoon and your order.' WHERE `entry`=9710;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Matis will be brought to justice, $N; and I want you to be the one to find him and bring him back to the Triumvirate.$B$BScour the island for this bastard. Should you find him, use this flare gun. When my trackers see the flare, they\'ll come and assist in capturing Matis. Return to me after he\'s been captured.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Triumvirate has decided to try Matis immediately. You have brought an arch-criminal to justice on this day, young $R.$B$BYou have performed admirably for two of three; only Aesom remains.' WHERE `entry`=9711;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We can still use more of the sanguine hibiscus from the shamblers, bog giants and underbats of the Underbog at Coilfang Reservoir. Bring them to me in bunches of five and I will be most grateful.' WHERE `entry`=9714;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These will do nicely, but we can always use more. Perhaps you will find yourself in the Underbog again soon?' WHERE `entry`=9715;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The naga are behind this!  But why?  From what you describe, that steam pump must be part of the cause for the water levels dropping in the marsh!$B$BNo matter - this explains their open hostility towards us. Let\'s not waste any time, I need you to perform another task for us.' WHERE `entry`=9716;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Did you discover anything, $N?' WHERE `entry`=9716;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The sporeling makes a sound that is vaguely reminiscent of snorting laughter.>$B$BPerfect! No doubt the morale of the spore giants will be at an all time low once they realize what you\'ve done.$B$BEither that, or they\'ll be so incensed that they\'ll attack us again soon.$B$B<T\'shu makes a shrugging motion.>' WHERE `entry`=9717;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is as I suspected. The naga have set up pumping stations at all the major lakes in Zangarmarsh. $B$BThey must be stopped if the marsh is to have a future.' WHERE `entry`=9718;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Hail, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9718;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Black Stalker is dead! Normally I would not revel in such butchery, but the pain that the great mother and her brood have put my people through over the centuries is unspeakable.$B$BIt is unfortunate that now another of her progeny will transform to replace her, but that will take time and give us some breathing room so that we will not have to worry about the marsh walkers for a while.' WHERE `entry`=9719;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is done, then. The marsh has been saved for now.$B$BDon\'t think for a second that this will be the last we hear of the naga. We must remain vigilant of our enemy as we continue with our mission in Outland.' WHERE `entry`=9720;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Serpent Lake Controls Disabled',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Lagoon Controls Disabled' WHERE `entry`=9720;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We will discuss the purpose for your visit soon. First. let me say that I am indeed impressed by your service and your skill in wielding the Light.' WHERE `entry`=9721;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That you have chosen to accept my offer speaks well of you, $N. I wish you luck in the tasks I am about to set for you, but I\'m certain you\'ll prove yourself more than capable.$B$BI will present the tasks in order from easiest to most difficult and we may begin when you are prepared.' WHERE `entry`=9722;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent. It appears everything is here.$B$BDon\'t worry. your next task will include plenty of opportunities to wield your weapon again, I promise.$B$BI\'ll have an initiate bring it all to Magister Astalor. There\'s no need to send you on such a trivial errand when there are more important things to be done.' WHERE `entry`=9723;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The news you bring about the naga activity in Zangarmarsh is dire. Ysiel was wise in sending word to us. She hasn\'t forgotten that the Expedition cannot exist without the Circle\'s support.' WHERE `entry`=9724;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have done well in demonstrating your loyalty to your homeland and dedication to the needs of the order, $N. I have one last task for you before you may lay claim to the title of master.' WHERE `entry`=9725;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Gzhun\'tt nods to you.>$B$BWe are pleased that you have affirmed our friendship, $N. Perhaps the naga heathens will think twice about harassing us in the future now that we have such a powerful ally?' WHERE `entry`=9726;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Gzhun\'tt nods to you.>$B$BWe are pleased that you have reaffirmed our friendship, $N. Surely now that you have made our point clear multiple times, their senseless attacks upon our people will cease?' WHERE `entry`=9727;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good job, $N. You\'d do well to shed any feelings of remorse you might harbor. These naga are vicious creatures - even more so than the Azerothian ones.' WHERE `entry`=9728;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Fhwoor\'s a good giant. We saved him from the naga a while ago and he\'s stayed here helping us with things ever since.$B$BWe can only hope that the naga will take the hint and realize that if we can infiltrate their village and steal their most prized possession, we can do much worse. Perhaps now they will return to their reservoir and leave us in peace?' WHERE `entry`=9729;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Is Fwhoor alright? Have you recovered the ark?' WHERE `entry`=9729;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I didn\'t like the naga in Azeroth and I like them less here. It\'s a real shame our mission could not remain a peaceful one, but you won\'t see me shedding tears for dead naga.$B$BHere\'s your reward for taking care of the Darkcrest leader, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9730;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Search Serpent Lake for signs of a drain. Return to Ysiel Windsinger at Cenarion Refuge with news of your discovery.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='The naga have turned Serpent Lake into a giant water sink for the rest of Zangarmarsh. What could they possibly be doing?$B$BYou\'ve done well in bringing this news to us, $N. We will send a team to investigate this drain you\'ve discovered. I have a different task for you in the meanwhile.' WHERE `entry`=9731;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='What news do you bring, $N?' WHERE `entry`=9731;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You are a welcome sight, $N. Matters at the Cenarion Refuge have only gotten worse since you left.' WHERE `entry`=9732;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hmm... this is a rather small amount. but if we\'re careful. it should be sufficient. You see. the Scarlet Crusade believes itself dedicated to the Light. I suppose they still are, in a twisted sort of way, and that\'s exactly what I\'m hoping to capitalize on.$B$BTheir misguided zeal has even tainted the blessing spoken over this water, making it ideal for my purpose.' WHERE `entry`=9735;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Now that we have all the reagents, I can prepare the mixture.$B$B<A slow smile spreads across Lady Liadrin\'s face.>$B$BIt\'s all coming together perfectly, $N. When this is finished, I\'ll give you the details about what remains to be done.' WHERE `entry`=9736;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. All who would oppose us would do well to heed the warning you delivered. Our foes should know that they are in peril, from the lowest foot soldier to the mightiest $Ghero:heroine;.$B$BYou have earned your place in the ranks of the masters. Your dedication and prowess serve as an example for all Blood Knights. As a symbol of your new status, I grant you the ability to summon and command the thalassian charger.' WHERE `entry`=9737;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I\'m glad that some of my friends yet live, but it breaks my heart to hear of the fate of others. <sigh>$B$BAt least they died doing what they loved most in life. You have my eternal gratitude for helping me with this, $N.$B$BPlease, take one of these as a sign of gratitude.' WHERE `entry`=9738;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Weeder Greenthumb Discovered',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Windcaller Claw Discovered' WHERE `entry`=9738;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done it!  You have my people\'s thanks.$B$BI hope you understand... this is where our young ones come from. We can\'t let these beasts devour the sacs!' WHERE `entry`=9739;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Smashing! We\'ve cut off their supply line. Now all that we need to do is finish them off!' WHERE `entry`=9740;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s a real mess up there, eh? You\'ve done well, $N. I\'ll send some anchorites out to help Loryi and Jorli.' WHERE `entry`=9741;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Yes! You\'ve saved more spore sacs.$B$BYou\'re different than the other outsiders. I\'ll let my people know about your deeds!$B$B<This quest is repeatable up to friendly reputation.>' WHERE `entry`=9742;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You made it back alive!  I\'ll let the other sporelings know about you!  $N, the giant slayer!' WHERE `entry`=9743;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Unbelievable!  It would take hundreds of sporelings to slay as many giants as you have. I will make sure to let everyone know of your feats!$B$B<This quest is repeatable up to friendly reputation.>' WHERE `entry`=9744;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This will surely soften up their defenses and make them think twice before rushing foolishly into our ranks!' WHERE `entry`=9746;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, $N. I will finally sleep comfortably at night. Were I not so old and weakened I would deal with my own enemies.$B$BTake this gold. It is not much, but your kindness cannot go unpaid.' WHERE `entry`=9747;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='As I suspected, the water has turned red due to contamination from leaking core fluid.$B$BI hope you didn\'t swim in any of that contaminated water.' WHERE `entry`=9748;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Have you heard of the bloodcurse, landlubber? No, of course you haven\'t. The bloodcurse is what sunk all these ships. The spoiled, desecrated part of the water here is known as Bloodcursed Reef - a part of the world you never want to visit. I\'ve been here myself for 20 years.$B$BScurvy my foot! I died on these wild shores as food for the dragons... Ah, but that\'s another story for another time. Right now, we have to help the poor souls that are trapped in that reef.' WHERE `entry`=9751;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You rescued one of my druids. We could never repay you, $N.$B$BYou have my thanks as well as that of the expedition.' WHERE `entry`=9752;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I am in need of your services, $N. I have a plan to topple the entire Sunhawk army, but before we can progress, we need to gather some vital information.$B$BWe need to identify the weaknesses in their primary defense. Unfortunately, we have been unable to get close enough to the Vector Coil to gauge their defenses. If we could get the prisoner to talk, we could get the information that we needed to break through the line and destroy the Vector Coil.$B$BYou heard me, I want to blow the damned thing up.' WHERE `entry`=9753;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A-ha! Well done, $N. Well done, indeed. Are you ready to eradicate the blood elf menace from our island forever?' WHERE `entry`=9756;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Let\'s begin our lesson at once!' WHERE `entry`=9757;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh good, there you are! And just in time... there is much to be done!' WHERE `entry`=9758;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have saved the whole of Bloodmyst and Azuremyst, securing the $R way of life on Azeroth, $N! For this, there can be no amount of thanks, no reward, nothing large enough in scope to truly express our appreciation.$B$BYet, there are still so many that were left behind on Draenor who cannot be here for this historic event. You must find your way back. Find your way back to the Outland, Hero of Argus. Bring our people home. Home to the land that you saved. Home to Azeroth...' WHERE `entry`=9759;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Perhaps you will be the one to deliver our people into a new age of prosperity and peace.' WHERE `entry`=9760;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hopefully a hero arrives before they are able to call forth reinforcements to guard the area you just secured.' WHERE `entry`=9761;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These islands will serve as the home to thousands. Most of these people will remain here their entire lives. If you so desired, you could do the same. But that\'s not what you want, is it, $N?$B$B<Velen nods.>$B$BYou will do many more great things before you pass. You must embrace your destiny and meet it head on!$B$BBefore you leave, I present you with two gifts: This tabard is worn by only the most revered of the Hand of Argus and this signet ring worn by our wisest sages. Wear them both with pride, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9762;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Our biggest enemy in the region is finally dead. You\'ve done the expedition a great favor, $N.$B$BWe shall be forever in your debt.' WHERE `entry`=9763;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Vashj!$B$BThis is much more than we bargained for. Our small victories here and there against the naga mean nothing.$B$BIf Lady Vashj is involved in this, then forces much greater than us are at work.$B$BYou\'ve done well in bringing this to us, $N. Now, we must prepare for war.' WHERE `entry`=9764;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These will do perfectly, $N. Bring any more armaments you find. Our need is great and our resources are scarce.' WHERE `entry`=9765;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent work, $N. The naga will learn not to underestimate us.' WHERE `entry`=9766;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These be fine ones, $N. Here\'s your payment.$B$B<Magasha bends one of the wings and holds it up to her head.>$B$BNope, not my thing, but who\'m I to complain?$B$B<Magasha shrugs.>$B$BCoin speaks.' WHERE `entry`=9769;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Had your fill already?$B$B<Reavij laughs.>$B$BThere\'s a reason why our visitors don\'t stay long.$B$BIf I had a choice, I\'d find a more agreeable spot for the post, but I\'ll take marshfangs over Denjai\'s temper any day.' WHERE `entry`=9770;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Search for Scout Jyoba.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='The battered corpse matches Zurai\'s description perfectly. Whatever killed the scout appears to have taken him by surprise, as his weapon is sheathed and the contents of a small inkwell stain the nearby ground.' WHERE `entry`=9771;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Zurai accepts the report from you and glances over it.>$B$BMuch of this is information we already know. Everything in the area seems to be dried or wilting, but here\'s something new.$B$BHe says the fungal giants seem to have gone berserk from the lack of moisture. From your description, that must be what killed him.$B$BI\'ll instruct my men to avoid the area. We can\'t afford any more casualties.' WHERE `entry`=9772;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Finally, a break from the monotony of mushrooms! If you didn\'t smell like fish, I\'d hug you.$B$BLet\'s see how jealous the others get when they smell the meat cooking over the fire.' WHERE `entry`=9773;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, $N. Every little bit helps.$B$BI\'ve still got a long way to go, but let\'s face it, what else am I going to do between patrols?' WHERE `entry`=9774;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Bring Zurai\'s Report to Shadow Hunter Denjai in Zabra\'jin',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Why didn\'t you say you had a report from Zurai? I\'ve been waiting to hear from him.$B$BI sent him out there to give us a presence on the eastern border, not sit on his hands. Let\'s see what he has to say.' WHERE `entry`=9775;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Speak to Ikuti at the Orebor Harborage.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='If Anchorite Ahuurn counts you a friend, then you may prove trustworthy. Please forgive my wariness, $R, but it is often all that stands between my people and death. You are welcome to shelter among us, and perhaps our mutual trust will grow.' WHERE `entry`=9776;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These are good spores and they should keep us going for quite some time. Thank you for helping us to replenish our supplies, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9777;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ysiel sent you? Of course I can use someone like you! We\'re always in need of a little muscle.' WHERE `entry`=9778;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Vindicator Boros eyes the document.>$B$BThis is in Thalassian. Fortunately, I know just the person that can translate it...' WHERE `entry`=9779;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for your help, $N. Your generosity will not be forgotten. As a token of my gratitude, I\'ve prepared a hot drink for you.' WHERE `entry`=9780;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done. That should ease the demand on the food supply around here for the immediate future, although we\'re going to need to find new sources of food. Fish and mushrooms suffice, but variety can never be underestimated.' WHERE `entry`=9781;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hmm... The soil seems to be depleted, so it can\'t be the cause of the problem, as I\'d thought. What\'s the common link here? Why is everything suddenly dying?' WHERE `entry`=9782;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for helping with this difficult task, $N. Our work in the Dead Mire is not yet done, but now our efforts will focus on doing what we can to restore balance to the area.' WHERE `entry`=9783;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent. Keep bringing me more plant parts if you find any.$B$B<This quest is repeatable up to Honored reputation.>' WHERE `entry`=9784;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve returned. Did you receive the ancients\' blessings?' WHERE `entry`=9785;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So, the Feralfen Lost Ones have taken over the ruins? Most intriguing. They must remember something of their heritage and the significance of the site. We must learn more, $N. This temple could hold the key to redeeming the Lost Ones and reuniting the many threads of draenei.' WHERE `entry`=9786;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Have you examined the Boha\'mu Ruins? Can you imagine what they were like in their full splendor?' WHERE `entry`=9786;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These should be more than sufficient, $N. They seem to be fixated on birds, which is odd, because there aren\'t any bird species native to Zangarmarsh. What could this mean?$B$BCould they have encountered the arakkoa? To a shamanistic people, they might seem like the embodiment of a powerful bird spirit.' WHERE `entry`=9787;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='My things!  They\'re all here!$B$BI thank you, $N. As promised, I\'ll let you pick one of the items for yourself. I don\'t have much to offer, but my people have always shared what little we have.' WHERE `entry`=9788;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Hunt down 30 Clefthoof and return to Hemet Nesingwary at Nesingwary\'s Safari in Nagrand to prove yourself.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='A fair start. But that\'s just the beginning.$B$BThe lesser clefthoof prove nothing. Let\'s move you up to a bigger challenge' WHERE `entry`=9789;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, $N.$B$B<Haalrun smiles sympathetically.>$B$BAt least you don\'t have to clean them. That\'s the worst job of the lot, but once it\'s done, you\'d never know they were attached to a giant insect.' WHERE `entry`=9790;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for your help in clearing out some of the marshfang rippers, $N. If they had any intelligence, perhaps they\'d learn that it\'s best to live and let live.$B$B<Noraani shrugs.>$B$BGiant, overgrown bugs with intelligence. I wonder what that would be like...' WHERE `entry`=9791;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I\'m flattered that your Broken friend considers me a scholar of his people\'s relics, but to be honest, I haven\'t had much chance to study them since my arrival here. It was certainly my intent, but when I arrived, I found that there were other matters that required my attention.' WHERE `entry`=9792;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hmm... I remember hearing our scouts speak of the ruins of a draenei settlement in the forest\'s northern reaches. I don\'t know much about the ruins, personally, but you\'re welcome to talk to some of the scouts.' WHERE `entry`=9793;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you\'ve brought Timothy\'s response?$B$B<Kialon pauses a moment to read the letter, then laughs.>$B$BHe\'s got everything under control, he says. Doesn\'t need help, he says. I could\'ve predicted that!$B$BSome people never change. Look, he even took the time to correct my spelling.$B$B<Kialon lets out a half-hearted sigh.>$B$BI shouldn\'t have sent the letter. I forgot. The specialist always has the situation under control. Always.' WHERE `entry`=9794;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Denjai seeks help? I\'d send him reinforcements, but we\'re spread thin here as it is. We\'ve got trouble of our own with the ogres up here.$B$BWhen I can, I\'ll give him what information we have on the local ogre tribes and their tactics. Perhaps if he can survive long enough, we\'ll be able to launch a two-pronged assault on the vile scum.' WHERE `entry`=9795;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s about time he got that outpost up and running. We\'ve lost far too many runners to Alliance outriders.' WHERE `entry`=9796;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Even though he endeavors to hide it, a look of relief spreads over Kroghan\'s face.>$B$BIt\'s about time you got here! Granted, you\'re not an army, but any able-bodied $R than can wield a weapon or chant a spell is welcome here. The people of Garadar are kin to all the Horde and we are proud to shed our blood in their defense.' WHERE `entry`=9797;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Here, let me read those plans.$B$BThe blood elves have followed us here?  They are evil to the core and should be wiped from existence!$B$B<The vindicator takes a moment to regain his composure.>$B$BI apologize, that was uncalled for. We are indebted to you for uncovering this information, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9798;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These look like fine specimens. Thank you for performing the field work. Once I can find the time to analyze these, I should be able to tell what it will take to restore the fields.' WHERE `entry`=9799;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Elementalist Lo\'ap at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand wants you to bring him 15 Digested Caracoli.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Please do not wash yourself in the sacred waters of the Throne.$B$B<Elementalist Lo\'ap holds a prepared caracoli tablet up.>$B$BYou place this under your tongue and allow it ample time to dissolve. Once it has dissolved, you will be able to breathe water as if it were air.' WHERE `entry`=9800;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Anchorite Ahuurn at Telredor wants you to bring him 4 Spore Bat Eyes and 4 Fen Strider Tentacles.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='These will do quite nicely. Allow me a moment to mix up the potion.' WHERE `entry`=9801;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The decrease in native species is certainly a cause for concern. The increase in invasive species could be related to the recent disturbance in the ecosystem. I don\'t have enough information to make a conclusion, yet.$B$B<Lauranna jots down some notes on a journal as she goes through the plant parts.>$B$BTake these, $N. They might be of some use to you.$B$BBring me any other plant parts you find. I\'ll incorporate them into my statistics.' WHERE `entry`=9802;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='They refused? They are welcome to choose their own path, of course, but their choice surprises me. I would think that all the draenei, including the Broken and Lost Ones, would still remember that we\'re all a part of the same people.$B$BI suppose he is right about the folly of deceiving them, but still, could he not see that our intentions were friendly?' WHERE `entry`=9803;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Elementalist Lo\'ap at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand wants you to destroy 12 Lake Spirits.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Elementalist Lo\'ap kneels in the water and says a prayer.>$B$BThe Earthen Ring takes no pride in what was done. We do what we must to heal the land.' WHERE `entry`=9804;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Your efforts have stifled the spread of pollution but other troubles have surfaced.' WHERE `entry`=9805;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Southern Hut Destroyed',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Eastern Hut Destroyed' WHERE `entry`=9805;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These are great spores, $N!  Tallstalks are vital to rebuilding our town. And after all the bog lord attacks we\'ve suffered, we\'re in quite the short supply.' WHERE `entry`=9806;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Your help is appreciated, $N. You will keep it up, yes?' WHERE `entry`=9807;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This will help us trade with other sporelings for food and supplies. Sporeggar thanks you, $N!' WHERE `entry`=9808;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, $N. As Sporeggar\'s elder, I must ensure my people have adequate supplies. You make my task that much easier.' WHERE `entry`=9809;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Elementalist Lo\'ap at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand wants you to destroy Watoosun\'s Polluted Essence and 10 Lake Surgers.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='The elements sang of your victory the moment the disturbed essence was destroyed! The Earthen Ring thanks you and wishes for you to choose a reward.' WHERE `entry`=9810;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you killed Dar\'Khan, $R?  Impressive. I\'ve a feeling my people and yours will soon get to be very good friends.' WHERE `entry`=9811;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is done then. The foul traitor got what he deserved.$B$BYou\'ve been of great service to the blood elves and to the Horde. Dar\'khan was Thrall\'s excuse to deny them entry into our alliance. You\'ve cleared the way for a new Horde, $C.$B$BI also see that Lor\'themar has additional news that will greatly improve his relations with Thrall. Excellent!' WHERE `entry`=9812;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Thrall begins to read the letter.>So the blood elves finally took care of their little problem. Never mind that it took your help as well as that of an entire Forsaken regiment to get the job done.<Thrall breaks into laughter.>I suppose there\'s no stopping this. In the end we need them just as much as they need us. Welcome to the horde Blood Elf.' WHERE `entry`=9813;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These be excellent, mon!$B$BI\'ll tell you what. Since you been a good sport and helped with the mushrooms, I\'ll let you in on the fun!' WHERE `entry`=9814;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Earthen Ring thanks you, $N. The elements also give their thanks. Your continued efforts in cleansing our world are appreciated and noted.' WHERE `entry`=9815;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent work, mon! I do hope they had a good time!' WHERE `entry`=9816;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I\'ll bet the Bloodscale will think twice about attacking expedition scouts again. Take this as a reward, $N. You\'ve earned it.' WHERE `entry`=9817;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Gordawg appears to be nodding at you.>$B$BSit.' WHERE `entry`=9818;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Gordawg at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand has asked that you destroy 15 Tortured Earth Spirits.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Gordawg nods in approval.>$B$BGood. Spirits sleep now.' WHERE `entry`=9819;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. The presence of these ogres so close to our outpost does have me worried, though. It seems like they\'ve been filtering down from the northern mountains for some time.' WHERE `entry`=9820;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Gordawg at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand has asked that you bring him 15 Enraged Crusher Cores.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Gordawg spits out the chewed up rock, pelting you with a hail of rubble.>$B$BPoison. These rocks are not Nagrand. These rocks are from poison. You destroy poison rock. You find usurper.' WHERE `entry`=9821;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Shadow Hunter Denjai examines the plans.>$B$BI knew it! The stench of ogres always carries an implicit threat. Now that we have proof of their intentions, we must act before they do.' WHERE `entry`=9822;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Your victory over the Ango\'rosh is to be celebrated, $N. I wonder how long it will be before those ogre brutes find themselves another bloodthirsty chieftain.$B$BNo matter, we\'ll be ready for them.' WHERE `entry`=9823;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These readings do not bode well, $N. Karazhan should be emanating all manner of arcane currents... instead it has become a huge energy vacuum. No signals. Nothing. Except for a very faint demonic echo.$B$BThis is bad news, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9824;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Fascinating. I will study these essences, $N. I thank you for your help.' WHERE `entry`=9825;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='These signs do not bode well for us, $N. I\'ve never been one for secrecy so I will tell you a bit about my organization, the Violet Eye.$B$BWe are agents of the Kirin Tor, the Magus Senate of Dalaran. We were assigned to keep an eye on Karazhan and Medivh, in case things got out of hand.$B$BWhich they did... very quickly, after Medivh disappeared.$B$BThis report details my findings. Take it to Archmage Cedric, also from the Violet Eye; you will find him in the outskirts of Dalaran.',`objectives_loc6`='Bring Alturus\'s Report to Archmage Cedric in the outskirts of Dalaran.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='You know of the Violet Eye? You do not look familiar.' WHERE `entry`=9826;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Take the Withered Basidium to Ruam in Telredor.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='It looks like the basidium of a bog giant. but I haven\'t seen one in this condition before. I\'d heard that the giants in the Dead Mire had begun to wither. but it\'s far more advanced than I expected.$B$BThe Dead Mire was once a lake like the others in the marsh, and it served as the spawning ground for the giants. With the waters receding, it seems the changes are preventing the giants from sporing. If this continues, the giants may disappear entirely.' WHERE `entry`=9827;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Bring the Withered Basidium to Reavij at Swamprat Post.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='It looks like the basidium of a boglord, but I haven\'t seen one in this condition before. I\'d heard that the giants in the Dead Mire had begun to wither, but it\'s far more advanced than I expected.$B$BThe Dead Mire was once a lake like the others in the marsh, and it served as the spawning ground for the giants. With the waters receding, it seems the changes are preventing the giants from sporing. If this continues, the giants may disappear entirely.' WHERE `entry`=9828;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Violet Eye? You don\'t say.$B$BShow me this report you speak of.' WHERE `entry`=9829;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for bringing this venom, $N. It will go a long way toward making my demonstration possible without depleting my personal stores.' WHERE `entry`=9830;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well, $N. I wasn\'t sure you would succeed.$B$BThe containers are enchanted with a potent spell that masks their presence from unworthy eyes. I\'m glad to see they did not elude you.' WHERE `entry`=9831;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have the fragments. This is most impressive, $N. You\'re certainly worthy of holding the key to Karazhan.$B A small problem remains.' WHERE `entry`=9832;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That\'s excellent news. The way is still far from perfectly safe, but the messengers are clever and resourceful.' WHERE `entry`=9833;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These are good hides, Maktu thinks. They will make very good armor.$B$BWho knows? There might even be enough left over for Maktu to make some armor for the draenei.' WHERE `entry`=9834;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Ango\'rosh threat is contained for the moment, but I\'m certain they won\'t give up that easily. I\'ve forgotten many things since the end of my life as a draenei, but the stubbornness of the ogres is an enduring memory.' WHERE `entry`=9835;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That key, I recognize it. That is Kadghar\'s key... of course I haven\'t given it to him yet.' WHERE `entry`=9836;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Who are you and what do you want?' WHERE `entry`=9836;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='His own key? That\'s incredible!$B$BI do not sense any disturbances in our timeline, so I suppose it was meant to occur all along. There\'s no turning back now, $N. The key is yours and only yours.' WHERE `entry`=9837;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I sent you to deliver a report and you come back with a key to this place? There must be more to you than meets the eye, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9838;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='At last! You have our thanks for your help in securing our position at the Orebor Harborage. I will send word of your deeds to the Kurenai city of Telaar in Nagrand. There will be many more opportunities for our peoples to work together.' WHERE `entry`=9839;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Koren looks at you with an uncertain look.>$B$BI know nothing of this Violet Eye you speak of. A blacksmith is all I am.' WHERE `entry`=9840;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I thought so. I can hear the difference already. I\'ll finally be able to get back to work, thanks to you. If you ever find yourself in need of tradeskill supplies, don\'t forget ol\' Gambarinka!' WHERE `entry`=9841;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These should keep me supplied for some time to come! I think some of the others have begun to take notice. I\'ve had several offers to buy my blades already. Selling them on the side might provide better business than my customary goods.' WHERE `entry`=9842;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You found the log. I sure hope the information we need is in here, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9843;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did it! Yes, the readings are becoming normal once again!$B$BWe must give this news to Cedric. He\'s going to be very impressed with your achievement.' WHERE `entry`=9844;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I can\'t wait to return to fishing! Now I\'ll be able to return to town with some real fish in my bucket and Gambarinka won\'t be able to make fun of me anymore!' WHERE `entry`=9845;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hmm... They seem to be divided between images of a serpent spirit and a bird spirit. No self-respecting Darkspear troll engages in bird worship. Their spirits are weak, capricious, and best left to the Amani.$B$BBut the serpent, $N, the serpent wields considerable power and this is the spirit I shall study.' WHERE `entry`=9846;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<You tell Seer Janidi about what happened when you used the totem.>$B$BThe spirit attacked you? It must have a higher affinity for those Lost Ones than I\'d thought. There\'s no way to compel it to serve me without expending considerable effort. I\'ll have to search for a new source of power in this wretched world.' WHERE `entry`=9847;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Timothy leafs through the manual.>$B$BThey\'re using ragveil as a base for the poison? No, that can\'t be right. Ragveil has no toxic properties.$B$BIncluding ragveil in a poison is like a rogue wielding two maces. Sure, you can do it, but it isn\'t true to the essence of your calling! I just can\'t understand...$B$B<Timothy clears his throat.>$B$BI mean, thank you for fetching these for me. I\'ll try out the poison as soon as time permits.' WHERE `entry`=9848;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='GUROK! Gurok betrayed the elements!' WHERE `entry`=9849;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='You\'ve proved to me that you can find and take down a regular clefthoof, but far more dangerous are the clefthoof bulls.$B$BBag yourself thirty of those. Then you can talk to me of your hunting prowess.$B$BLook for them all along the middle region of Nagrand to the west and south.',`objectives_loc6`='Kill 30 Clefthoof Bulls and then speak to Hemet Nesingwary at Nesingwary\'s Safari in Nagrand about your prowess.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Impressive. Most impressive.$B$BYou\'ve got potential, kid. Now I\'m going to give you the chance to have some real fun!' WHERE `entry`=9850;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did it! You took down Banthar! I never had a doubt, $N.$B$BHere, I think you\'ve more than earned this.' WHERE `entry`=9851;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='$N! You bring joy to this old dwarf\'s heart.$B$BYou have now proven yourself; you\'ve joined the ranks of the elite! Others ran away in fear, or died, trampled under the foot of the beast. You used your mind, your cunning, your determination to prove your mastery of the hunt.$B$BTake this and know that you are always welcome to hunt at my side!' WHERE `entry`=9852;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Gordawg chomps down hard on Gurok\'s earthen head, nearly disintegrating the stone formation.>$B$BGurok\'s reign has come to an end. The earthen elements are free. All sleep now. Champion gets reward!' WHERE `entry`=9853;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Kill 30 Windrocs and then return to Fitz at the Nesingwary Safari in Nagrand.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Every day is a gift. Make the most of it. For tomorrow we shall stride swifter over the plains than today. We will spread our arms further and strain to achieve that which tonight we can only dream of, though it may ever elude us.' WHERE `entry`=9854;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Hunt down 30 Ravenous Windrocs and then return to Fitz at the Nesingwary Safari in Nagrand.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have proven your skill once more, $C. Now you must go on to stalk the fiercest of the windrocs.' WHERE `entry`=9855;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Her eye looks as if it is still alive. Do you think that she can still see into your soul?$B$B$N, you can now count yourself as one of the elite safari hunters. And you are another step closer to stalking the ultimate prey of this land, Tusker!$B$BYou\'ve earned the right to have this. May it serve you well.' WHERE `entry`=9856;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Kill 30 Talbuk Stags and then return to Harold Lane at the Nesingwary Safari in Nagrand.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='That\'s a good tale... <cough>...of how you bagged all of those stags, $C. But I think that you can do better. I\'ve got something else in mind for you.' WHERE `entry`=9857;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Hunt down 30 Talbuk Thorngrazers and then return to Harold Lane at the Nesingwary Safari in Nagrand.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='<cough>, <cough>... $N! You did it. There\'s only...<cough>... one thing left to...<cough>... do then.' WHERE `entry`=9858;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Wow! You did it! That\'s really Bach\'lor\'s hoof!$B$BUm, I\'m starting to feel much better it would seem. Here, let me give you something in celebration of your proven hunting prowess!' WHERE `entry`=9859;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Speak to Archmage Cedric in the Outskirts of Dalaran.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Alturus told me all about what happened, $N. This is not the end of it, however. With Karazhan remaining sealed to outsiders, it\'s only a matter of time until the Legion renews its attacks while we stand powerless in the sidelines.$B$BUnless you accept the responsibility that fate has bestowed upon you, that is.$B$B<Cedric extends an open palm towards you, holding a badge with the Violet Eye\'s symbol on it.>$B$BWhat do you say, $N?' WHERE `entry`=9860;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is a distress call, $R. An outside force is attempting to subvert the elements.' WHERE `entry`=9861;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Elementalist Morgh at the Throne of the Elements in Nagrand wants you to slay 8 Murkblood Putrifiers.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='You saw them controlling the elements? The wind bent to their will?$B$B<Morgh is lost in thought for a moment.>$B$BThis is troubling, $N. I must consult with the others.$B$BWe thank you for your efforts, $N. Perhaps you should return to your village and see if they have any other information about the Murkbloods and their nefarious goals.' WHERE `entry`=9862;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Farseer Kurkush at Garadar in Nagrand wants you to bring him 20 Murkblood Idols.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have given the Lightning Sons hope, $N. If our leader will not protect us, perhaps there are others that are capable - like you.' WHERE `entry`=9863;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I have been told stories of my people. They say that once, we were warriors...' WHERE `entry`=9864;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Kill 40 Murkblood Scavengers and 20 Murkblood Raiders.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Saurfang turns to face you.>$B$BIs it blood that I smell? I regret being unable to lend assistance. How proud you must be. My chest swells just knowing what you have done.$B$BAre there others like you? Where you come from, do more heroes exist?' WHERE `entry`=9865;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Farseer Corhuk stares at the ground, lost in contemplation. He nods his head affirmatively.>$B$B<Farseer Corhuk wipes a tear away.>$B$BThe son is the father... May the spirits have mercy on those that stand in his way.' WHERE `entry`=9866;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So, this is the face of our enemy? I will have this put upon a pike and placed outside of Garadar, near the gates. Should they think to attack us again, they will see the consequences for their actions looking down upon them...' WHERE `entry`=9867;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What does it matter? The Greatmother is dying. Life is not worth living...' WHERE `entry`=9868;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='<Garrosh barely acknowledges your presence. He appears deeply depressed.>' WHERE `entry`=9868;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, thank you for the message. Perhaps you would not mind helping out the Earthen Ring? The elements are in flux. We can use all of the assistance that we can get.' WHERE `entry`=9869;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, thank you for the message. Perhaps you would not mind helping out the Earthen Ring? The elements are in flux. We can use all of the assistance that we can get.' WHERE `entry`=9870;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Take the Murkblood Invasion Plans to Arechron.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Arechron slams his fist into his hand.>Ortor... Treacherous bastard!' WHERE `entry`=9871;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Garrosh crumples up the map and throws it into the fire.>$B$BWhat\'s the use? They\'ve been attacking us for weeks. This is nothing new.$B$BDon\'t you understand? We\'re done for... Greatmother Geyah is dying.' WHERE `entry`=9872;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A thousand dead orcs you say? What could have triggered such an audacious advance into orc lands? It is good that he is dead but there is more to this than what meets the tentacle.' WHERE `entry`=9873;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Otonbu sighs.>$B$BThis will set back any chance of peace with the orcs another 10 years. At least we will be around to see those years as opposed to what could have happened had those corpses been allowed to rot.' WHERE `entry`=9874;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A new species! Are you sure?$B$B<Lauranna flips through pages of notes and diagrams.>$B$BNice job, $N. We\'ll have to add this one to our list. How does "Purple Leafed Aelarathrium" sound to you?  It does have a ring to it.' WHERE `entry`=9875;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Ysiel Windsinger wants you to look for signs of Cenarion Expedition Druids near the entrance to Coilfang Reservoir.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank Cenarius you showed up. My injuries prevented me from going back to the outside for help.' WHERE `entry`=9876;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Janeda\'s sending you to rescue the Deatholme prisoners? She must think very highly of you, $N.' WHERE `entry`=9877;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Poli\'lukluk the Wiser at Telaar in Nagrand wants you to kill 20 Murkblood Scavengers and 10 Murkblood Raiders.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='It is doubtful that the orcs will understand or appreciate what you just did but Nagrand is better off for the deed. Thank you, problem solver...' WHERE `entry`=9878;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Yes, I know of the totem... but there is much more to this story. Alas, I lack the authority to reveal this information to you. Only the chosen may be privy to such knowledge.' WHERE `entry`=9879;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Color me impressed. These are in excellent condition, for the most part.$B$BI will make sure to put in a good word for you with our people.' WHERE `entry`=9882;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Keep the crystal fragments coming, $N. We cannot let these thieves take our property.$B$BEven if it\'s not ours just quite yet. A technicality, of course.' WHERE `entry`=9883;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Consortium is well known for taking good care of its friends. At the beginning of each month I\'ll have some gems ready for you as payment for your services.$B$BThe quality of the gems you get will depend on how loyal you\'ve been to us. Here\'s to hoping you do the smart thing and stay with us.' WHERE `entry`=9884;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Consortium is well known for taking good care of its friends. At the beginning of each month I\'ll have some gems ready for you as payment for your services.$B$BThe quality of the gems you get will depend on how loyal you\'ve been to us. Here\'s to hoping you do the smart thing and stay with us.' WHERE `entry`=9885;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Consortium is well known for taking good care of its friends. At the beginning of each month I\'ll have some gems ready for you as payment for your services.$B$BThe quality of the gems you get will depend on how loyal you\'ve been to us. Here\'s to hoping you do the smart thing and stay with us.' WHERE `entry`=9886;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Consortium is well known for taking good care of its friends. At the beginning of each month I\'ll have some gems ready for you as payment for your services.$B$BThe quality of the gems you get will depend on how loyal you\'ve been to us. Here\'s to hoping you do the smart thing and stay with us.' WHERE `entry`=9887;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Kilrath speaks in a hushed tone.>$B$BThese ogres are extremely peculiar. They are also extremely stupid. Look how the fat one makes the, um, lesser fat ones dance. It\'s mesmerizing.' WHERE `entry`=9888;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Let me live and I\'ll tell you whatever you want to know!' WHERE `entry`=9889;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='I submit! I submit!' WHERE `entry`=9889;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Slow down, $N. I am but a lowly rogue. I have no idea what to do with such information.' WHERE `entry`=9890;
