UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Here now. Ye hear that? There be sounds in them hills. Those\'re the wolpertingers! Wily beasts, they are, attracted by the smells o\' Brewfest. I\'ve a mind to catch me some, but I knocked me shin and can\'t outrun the buggers. Ye can help me, though!$B$BTake this net and cast it over the little blighters. Bring me a good five of \'em and I\'ll make it worth yer while! Oh, and one more thing - in order to even see these critters, ye need t\' be blitzed! Load up on the booze!',`objectives_loc6`='Goldark Snipehunter has asked you to capture 5 Stunned Wolpertingers using the Wolpertinger Net. He mentioned that you must be intoxicated to see them.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well, lookee there! Ye\'ve got yerself a right bushel o\' wolpertingers, ye do!$B$B<He takes a deep drink from his tankard.>$B$BI\'ll tell ye what I\'m gonna do. Since ye\'re such a spot-on $C, I\'ll let ye keep one\'a these fer yer very own!' WHERE `entry`=11117;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Getting drunk is a time-honored tradition at Brewfest -- it\'s damn near required! Thing is, I\'m getting reports across Azeroth saying the celebration\'s plagued by hallucinations!  We can\'t have that!$B$BThese elekks can\'t be harmed by normal weapons -- they pass right through \'em -- so take this fabulous piece of gnomish machinery, visit the other beer gardens, and zap \'em to oblivion. Remember, you have to be drunk to see \'em!',`objectives_loc6`='Visit the beer gardens outside of Stormwind, Darnassus, and the Exodar, zap three elekks at each location, and return to Goldark Snipehunter. You must be drunk to see the pink elekks.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good work! Pink elekks... what a preposterous notion!' WHERE `entry`=11118;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Sky Commander Keller has asked you to speak with the Aether-tech Apprentice at the Skyguard Outpost in the Blade\'s Edge Mountains.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Despite how Keller cares to characterize it, I prefer to think of our missions as research-oriented.$B$BBut yes, we do resupply the Skyguard while we\'re there. That is if we can stay long enough to do so.$B$BYou look like you\'d be willing to keep the ethereals off of our backs. If you can manage to for long enough, we\'ll sell you surplus items that we create at the crystalforge, so bring your apexis shards and crystals!$B$BWe leave in 2 hours.' WHERE `entry`=11119;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Look. We\'re running a business here. People being drunk? It\'s good business. But I\'ll tell ya one thing that puts a cramp in the profits - hallucinations. Wouldn\'t ya know it, the boys are reporting that the sot- er, the loyal customers are seeing pink elekks everywhere.$B$BI don\'t need my customers unsettled. Look, take this ray and travel to the other beer gardens to take care of \'em for me, would ya? And be sure to get drunk!',`objectives_loc6`='Visit the beer gardens outside of Silvermoon, Thunder Bluff, and the Undercity, zap three elekks at each location, and return to Glodrak Huntsniper. You must be drunk to see the pink elekks.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ya did good, kid. Here, take this as payment for the job ya did.' WHERE `entry`=11120;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thanks a lot for your help! As long as Brewfest is going and the Dark Iron Dwarves are attacking, I\'ll need some help shipping kegs. So if you want to work for more tickets, talk to me every day.$B$BBut enough about that, I need to pay you for the job you just did. Here are your tickets, have fun at Brewfest!' WHERE `entry`=11122;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s good to see that Captain Vimes is finally assigning others to this investigation.$B$BI\'ve used a reflective powder to dust the area. It will reveal suspicious objects and markings, helping you to focus your efforts. Look over anything the dust illuminates.' WHERE `entry`=11123;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The inspector regards you with what can only be distrust.>$B$BI\'ve been told that you\'re to... aid in this investigation. Very well, then.$B$BI\'ve been using this powder to search the ruins for clues that might help identify the attackers. It will illuminate anything that might have been involved in the attack. Don\'t hesitate to examine anything that looks suspicious.' WHERE `entry`=11124;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N. I think we managed to catch them off guard. Their agents probably thought themselves safe within the city walls.$B$BGiven time, the agitators will return and spread their lies again. We\'ll use the time you\'ve bought to shut out the deserters further.' WHERE `entry`=11126;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The SI:7 agent nods in approval.>$B$BExcellent. All that remains is to discredit the deserters so that they\'ll never gain a foothold in Theramore again, and I have just the plan to do it.' WHERE `entry`=11128;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Fantastic work, $N! Kyle came home as soon as he ate and went straight to bed. Thank you for your help.' WHERE `entry`=11129;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Budd reads the note.>$B$BAhh! A friend of Griftah? Welcome!$B$BYou have impeccable timing, friend. As fate would have it, I recently lost my latest partners. Tragic, truly, but great rewards often have a high price. Best not to dwell on the negative!$B$BYou\'ve doubtlessly heard of my countless exploits and discoveries. Well, all of that was nothing compared to this! Truth is, we\'re close to making history here at Zul\'Aman and, by fate\'s decree, you\'re in on the ground floor!' WHERE `entry`=11130;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh, thank you! May the Light bless your good works, kind $Glord:lady;. The shadow of the Dark Horseman yet looms, but at least, for now, the village is safe from his flames.' WHERE `entry`=11131;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='$N, you promised to save the children!' WHERE `entry`=11131;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Budd looks a bit shocked.>$B$BOh? You\'ve found it?$B$BAhem, I mean, of course you have! Well done, $C.$B$BLet me see if I can find you a little something nice... ahh yes, this should do.' WHERE `entry`=11132;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Calia chuckles as you describe the guards\' reactions to the propaganda.>$B$BJust as I\'d hoped! I think it\'s safe to say any deserter agents who try to infiltrate Theramore will be laughed right out of town!' WHERE `entry`=11133;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Gavis\' request isn\'t as outlandish as it might sound. With the proper handling, Lady Jaina can return the deserters to the fold, but that is her decision, of course.$B$BIt\'s been a pleasure working with you, $N. Without your help, I doubt the operation would\'ve gone so smoothly. When I make my report in Stormwind, it will name you as the $C who ended the deserter threat.' WHERE `entry`=11134;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='The Headless Horseman is driven away, but he will return as long as Hallow\'s End looms. $N, end our misery, and the insane lament of the Horseman. Face him when he is joined with his head, and destroy it!$B$BHe rests in the Forlorn Cloister of the Scarlet Monastery, in Tirisfal Glade. Find his pumpkin shrine and say this:$B$B  Horseman, rise$B  Your time is nigh$B  You felt death once$B  Now, know demise!$B$BGo, $N. And may the Light go with you.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='The origin of this shrine is unknown, but there is no doubt to whom it pays homage...' WHERE `entry`=11135;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The captain makes no effort to hide that he\'s assessing your abilities.>$B$BSo you\'ve heard about the recent shipwreck off the coast? Good, I could use some help confirming my suspicions about the survivors. Welcome aboard, $N.' WHERE `entry`=11136;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Captain Wymor accepts the orders from you and reads over them.>$B$BWhat in the world could \'precious cargo\' refer to? The Defias have done some small time smuggling back in lands of Stormwind, but this seems out of their league. The language of these orders suggests a wealthy or noble patron.' WHERE `entry`=11137;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Renn looks over the orders.>$B$BSo there was valuable cargo on board! We have to locate it before the Defias recover it. These guys are no divers, but we\'re going to need some of their gear if you\'re to help me find the cargo.' WHERE `entry`=11138;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Wow, this is in worse shape than I\'d thought, and these tools...$B$BWell, I said I\'d get this back into working condition for you, so I\'d better get to work.' WHERE `entry`=11139;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Renn rifles through the contents of the strongboxes you recovered.>$B$BGood work. Now, let\'s see if our \'precious cargo\' is in here....' WHERE `entry`=11140;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You and Renn have done excellent work in bringing this information to light and reporting it immediately. Now, we must confirm your findings. The implications are too great if we are wrong.' WHERE `entry`=11141;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Lady Jaina listens intently as you report the results of your aerial survey.>$B$BA rune circle, dragonkin? The Defias have allied themselves with HER? The traitor?$B$B<Lady Jaina composes herself and prepares to explain.>' WHERE `entry`=11142;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Captain Vimes thinks the Grimtotems are behind the destruction of the Shady Rest Inn? They wouldn\'t have been first on my list of suspects, but if Captain Vimes sent you here to follow up on a lead, he must have his reasons. Regardless, the Grimtotems have been a thorn in our side for some time and we\'re always glad to have the extra help.' WHERE `entry`=11143;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Captain Darill glances at the battle plan.>$B$BI\'d say it doesn\'t get any clearer than this. They\'ve taken it upon themselves to fight back against human settlements in the area and I have little doubt Theramore is next on their list.' WHERE `entry`=11144;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The freed captives have already begun returning from Blackhoof Village. The information the captain is receiving from the prisoners will give us an advantage in our next battle against the Grimtotems.$B$BYou have my thanks and that of the men.' WHERE `entry`=11145;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You look a little scratched up, but nothing major. You\'re certainly in a lot better shape than the Grimtotems will be when our new raptor friends get done with them.' WHERE `entry`=11146;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The sergeant doesn\'t bother to hide his grin.>$B$BGood. That ought to forestall a raid or two.' WHERE `entry`=11147;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Captain Darill inspects the armaments you\'ve brought from Blackhoof Village.>$B$BThere\'s no doubt about it. These match the description exactly, but there\'s just one problem -- these have never been used in battle. Blackhoof Village must not be the only Grimtotem post in the marsh.' WHERE `entry`=11148;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you want me to scry for Grimtotems, eh? And what will you say when I tell you there\'s no need?' WHERE `entry`=11149;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I hope the Grimtotems got the message. Any attempt to return will be met with far worse than a mere torch. My apprentices and I will see to that.' WHERE `entry`=11150;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The captain listens to your report intently.>$B$BWe have avenged James and his family, but not even that can restore what was destroyed.' WHERE `entry`=11151;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Captain Vimes smiles slightly as you relate the events you witnessed at the Hyal family grave.>$B$BIt\'s good to know that they understand. You didn\'t tell them about James, did you?$B$BI\'ll deliver his wife\'s message to him, but I doubt he\'ll understand.' WHERE `entry`=11152;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That\'s what I wanted to hear!  You\'ve got the stuff, $N, that\'s for sure!$B$BYou think maybe you could come back again tomorrow when we\'ve made more cluster bombs?  I\'d have you back out there right now, but my assistant, Feknut, isn\'t back from collecting more bat guano for them.$B$BI wonder what\'s taking him so long?' WHERE `entry`=11153;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ugh, what\'s that smell? Ack, it\'s you! Well, I guess I did send you on a smelly job!$B$BThank you, $C. Don\'t worry, I\'ll get this stuff back to Petrov as soon as we get out of here.$B$B<Feknut yells out loud to the explorers.>$B$BYou hear that guys? Lets get the hell out of here!!!' WHERE `entry`=11154;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This will make a fine meal for the men.$B$B<The chef leans in closer to whisper in your ear.>$B$BHere, deary, take some for yourself. You look like you could use some more meat on your bones!' WHERE `entry`=11155;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Apprentice Morlann nods.>$B$BGood. Can\'t say I\'ll miss the company, if you can call it that. You\'d think at least in the middle of the swamp you\'d get some privacy, you know?' WHERE `entry`=11156;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good work! With any luck at all, the destruction of their egg clutches and whelps should drive off those fiery beasts and prevent that magical blaze from spreading.$B$BWait... what\'s that sound? It sounds like the beating of wings.' WHERE `entry`=11157;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Brogg accepts the feathers.>$B$BBrogg pleased with these feathers. Very strong magic. Brogg not know what raptors do to give feathers power, but raptor feathers always best for ritual.' WHERE `entry`=11158;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Brogg thanks you for your help, although he knows Overlord Mok\'Morokk never will. At least surviving Stonemaul can finally focus on problems with the living and leave dead where they belong. Only one thing remains for Brogg to do.' WHERE `entry`=11159;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have Brogg\'s thanks, $N. Brogg has big plans for clan banner.' WHERE `entry`=11160;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have Brogg\'s thanks, $N. Once Brogg adds their magic to the totem, it will be able to redeem the spirits of Brogg\'s fallen friends.' WHERE `entry`=11161;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Brogg listens as you recount your experience at the entrance to Onyxia\'s lair.>$B$BBrogg suspected Onyxia would be too much of a coward to confront you. Just like black dragonflight to attack when victory is guaranteed.$B$BBrogg is grateful for your help, $N, and he will never forget what you have done for him. Brogg will never give up his quest to bring Stonemaul back where they belong.' WHERE `entry`=11162;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ahh yeah, these be just what I be needin\'!$B$BHere be the payment I promised ya, $C.' WHERE `entry`=11164;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I be free!$B$BDey took most everyting when dey nabbed me, but here - take the last of my coin fer your troubles.$B$BAnd the least I can be doin\' is stickin\' around to offer my services....' WHERE `entry`=11165;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Budd struggles to maintain his composure.>$B$BErr - So, $N - it\'s, uhhh, about time you returned. Yes - in fact you\'re holding up the entire operation.$B$BNow then, let\'s get to filling in this map....' WHERE `entry`=11166;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s good that you\'re back in one piece. The danger of becoming infected from handling these containers is not non-existent. I suppose I should\'ve warned you about that earlier.' WHERE `entry`=11167;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You continue to prove your competence, $N. Hopefully this toxin will be enough to boost our plague to the levels that we need to.$B$BAt the very least it should help weaken the recipient and make them more susceptible to infection.' WHERE `entry`=11168;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The apprentice listens as you describe your experiment.>$B$BA haze and some lightning? That\'s it? There\'s got to be more to the totem than just that! The Grimtotems aren\'t likely to bring something like this to the battlefield unless it has some kind of utility.' WHERE `entry`=11169;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hmmphh.... the reports from the field are.... not encouraging!' WHERE `entry`=11170;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Finally! Now that the light work is done, I can at last make yet another mark on history. But first, there\'s one small matter to attend to - You....$B$BI\'m afraid, $N, that the time has come for me to let you go. I feel that your potential has been reached here, if not far exceeded.$B$BDon\'t feel bad, though. After all, it takes an exceptional type of individual to participate in such extraordinary events and not lose their wits. And look here, I have a little something for you to remember me by.' WHERE `entry`=11171;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So those hermit mages sent you? How can I be sure that I can trust you?$B$BI suppose I can use the help. There\'s not much here a mage would be interested in, anyway.' WHERE `entry`=11172;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Apprentice Garion inspects the venom.>$B$BThis is absolutely perfect! He\'ll never know the difference.' WHERE `entry`=11173;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well, it does look a little cleaner out there...$B$BI suppose it\'s time to get down to the business of salvaging this wreckage.' WHERE `entry`=11174;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Grrr. I knew it! He\'s sooooo over-protective! This is just embarassing.$B$BNot that I\'m not happy to see you... I am! We all are. We can use your help!' WHERE `entry`=11175;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Irena sent you over, did she? Good, we\'ve got work for you then!' WHERE `entry`=11176;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Get off my lawn... unless, that is, you want to help old "Swamp Eye" with a little bit of cooking. Whad\'ya say?' WHERE `entry`=11177;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Th-the Blood of Zul\'jin himself you say?$B$B<Gathering himself, Budd continues>$B$BWell, I appreciate the gesture, $C, but I could\'ve taken him down with ease. There\'s no way he was as fearful as the legends say. These things have a way of being utterly overstated, as you\'ll learn in time. More likely, the pitiful old cretin was overcome with arthritis!$B$BAnyway, I suppose it was the least you could do as payment for the kindness I\'ve shown you here.$B$BNow off with you - I must dispose of this vile vial!' WHERE `entry`=11178;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Mordant produces a small sheet of paper and a pen, beginning to scribble down notes on your findings.>$B$BFrom your findings, the spirits in this place must amount to everyone who ever lived on this land, not just the previous occupants.$B$BSomething has been corrupting and killing them. Those who follow don\'t learn the truth until it\'s too late. We have to put an end to this, $N!' WHERE `entry`=11180;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Mordant accepts the bunch of herbs from you.>$B$BThese match the description exactly! I prepared the torch while you were out. All that remains is to fasten the herbs to the end here.' WHERE `entry`=11181;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Unfortunate that one predator must be used to put down another, but that is the natural order of things.$B$BPerhaps now the proto-drakes and their whelps can go back to living peacefully. Somehow I doubt it with the reawakening of the vrykul.' WHERE `entry`=11182;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It worked?$B$B<Mordant clears his throat.>$B$BI mean... it worked! Jarl and I are in your debt, $N. Now the only remaining problem is my friend\'s taste in furniture, and I\'m afraid that won\'t be solved as easily.' WHERE `entry`=11183;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank goodness someone\'s finally taken me up on that offer. I was just thinking that I might need to triple the reward to get that stupid raptor killed, and our budget couldn\'t afford that!' WHERE `entry`=11184;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Andello reads the letter, shocked at its contents.>$B$BWe\'ve long had misgivings about the cooperation between the Horde and the Forsaken, and this only confirms those suspicions. With the backing for Forsaken magic and arms, the Grimtotems would become an even more fearsome enemy. The balance of power in Kalimdor could shift considerably.' WHERE `entry`=11185;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='If this is what it appears to be, the Forsaken have some explaining to do!$B$BThe antics of the Grimtotems have long tried the Warchief\'s patience. We have traditionally treated it as a matter to be settled among the tauren people, but this letter may change it.$B$BIt will take time to investigate these suspicions, but do not speak to anyone of what you have seen this day.' WHERE `entry`=11186;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Malister beckons you closer and speaks in whispered tones.>$B$BI was worried that something like this might happen. I tried to dissuade the captain from this course of action, but he is a dwarf of action with a definite outlook on how things should proceed.$B$BLet us speak of the options left to us.' WHERE `entry`=11187;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The mage-lieutenant sighs.>$B$BUnfortunate business to be certain. Well, what\'s done is done. With any luck the new whelps that grow to be drakes at Ember Clutch will not retain a memory of our shameful actions therein.$B$BAnd with a bit more luck, the boundaries of that magical forest will not continue to spread.$B$BHere, $N, please take this pittance from the treasury for all of your troubles. It\'s the least that we can do.' WHERE `entry`=11188;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh, bless ya, $N, bless ya!$B$BJust set \'em down right where yer standin\'. I\'ll have one o\' the boys come load \'em up soon enough and we can stop worryin\' \'bout runnin\' out o\' balls ta shoot at Skorn.' WHERE `entry`=11190;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good. I can use all the help you can offer. My first priority is to get that lamp re-lit.' WHERE `entry`=11191;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well, I have my doubts, but this is the only solution available right now. Once we have it up and running, I\'m sure there will be time to look at other ways to fuel the lamp.' WHERE `entry`=11192;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well, now, that was thoughtful o\' Babs to send that over. I don\'t know if you\'ve leafed through it or not, but there\'s a lot of truth to the tales in that book. Sailors didn\'t just make it all up, you know.' WHERE `entry`=11193;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you want to know about sea monsters? Hmm... well, I\'ll make you a deal, but it\'s going to involve a lot of alcohol and some embarrassment on your part.' WHERE `entry`=11194;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hey now, where ya be gettin\' this?$B$BNo, no, don\'t tell me - this be comin\' from the Hex-Lord himself! It all be clear now. Strong mojo! The bearer of this relic, no matter how many disgraces he be sufferin\', be always honored by his peers. Incredible!$B$B<As Griftah holds the doll in the air, a small, rusty charm falls from around its neck. The troll begins to discard it, but then turns toward you with a gleam in his eye.>$B$BI gots no coins right now, mon, but ya be welcome to this here...' WHERE `entry`=11195;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Da Amani been rebuildin\' their forces and dey raised up a new warlord to lead dem, $N. He be called Daakara da Invincible, but we be seein\' whether he lives up to the name or not.$B$BYa must first defeat all his lieutenants to clear da way before ya can face this Daakara. Defeat him and put an end to da ambitions of da Zandalari and da Amani!',`objectives_loc6`='Defeat the new Amani warlord, Daakara.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Victory be ours, $N. Da Zandalari be fleein\' and without da warlord\'s leadership, da Amani will soon be reduced to fighting among demselves.' WHERE `entry`=11196;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N! I\'ll admit, when I caught my first glimpse of that beast, I had doubts about our ability to defend the docks, but you held together the defenders brilliantly!' WHERE `entry`=11198;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Make your report.' WHERE `entry`=11198;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh good, help, and just in time!' WHERE `entry`=11199;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Krog inspects the weapons and armor you\'ve brought from Blackhoof Village.>$B$BThis is unmistakably the work of Mosarn. Questioning him further may draw too much attention, but we have a bit more freedom in dealing with the Grimtotems.' WHERE `entry`=11200;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Krog reads over the battle plan.>$B$BThere\'s no doubt in my mind that the Grimtotems are moving against the humans. What I don\'t understand is what their intentions are toward us. The actions of the Grimtotems have caused tension within the Horde in the past, but the Warchief has always diffused it.' WHERE `entry`=11201;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Nice!$B$BBut what\'s this about the stuff you found inside those tanks? Are you saying that the Forsaken are spraying a plague upon the vrykul down there?' WHERE `entry`=11202;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Northeast Plague Tank Destroyed',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Southeast Plague Tank Destroyed' WHERE `entry`=11202;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Tabetha smiles slightly.>$B$BKrog wishes me to scry for the Grimtotems, eh? Well, I have no need of magic in this case.$B$BIt seems we have a mutual enemy. The Grimtotems have built an outpost nearby and are a constant thorn in the side of me and my students.' WHERE `entry`=11203;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='He actually said that the Grimtotems are his biggest customers? Mosarn gave us more help than he knows. With this much pointing toward the Grimtotems, I think we just found our first suspects.' WHERE `entry`=11204;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Grimtotems should have no trouble understanding our latest message.$B$BAs for you, your contact at Brackenwall Village will want to know of your success. I know the destruction of the Shady Rest Inn could be a source of tensions between the Horde and Alliance. If I encounter any investigators from Theramore, I will gladly tell them the Grimtotems acted on their own.' WHERE `entry`=11205;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Krog listens to your report.>$B$BI\'m impressed, $N. I would\'ve thought that the Grimtotem criminals would\'ve been more difficult to locate. $B$BTabetha\'s warnings have not fallen on deaf ears, but it is not my place to chastise the Grimtotems. I will, of course, mention it in my report to the Warchief. Do not speak of it to anyone until Thrall has dealt with the Grimtotems. You have done well in solving the mystery of the Shady Rest and sparing us from the suspicion of Theramore.' WHERE `entry`=11206;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Wow! You certainly found a lot more than I expected would be out there. I\'m not sure how much Drazzit thought we were going to find out here, but he\'s going to have to be happy with this for now.' WHERE `entry`=11207;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Drazzit accepts the cargo from you.>$B$BI\'m so hungry, I could eat a dragon! Thank goodness Moxie finally got some of that cargo down here. We\'ve been reduced to playing dice against the ogre for whatever he\'s managed to kill on his hunting trips!' WHERE `entry`=11208;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Not bad at all, but you know, I think I\'d get a bath in as soon as possible, if I was you.$B$BNow, about your sea monster...$B$BHelp yourself to a brew or two in the meantime.' WHERE `entry`=11209;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<You recount your experiences with Nat Pagle, carefully omitting the portion about the \'bait test.\'>$B$BWell, it sounds like we\'ve got our work cut out for us. I\'ll make the preparations.' WHERE `entry`=11210;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s good of Tabetha to send you down here. I\'d prevail upon her for some food until the wreckage from the zeppelin is taken care of, but I know she\'s got none to spare at the moment. If you\'re feeling adventurous, I\'ve posted a bounty for the death of a particularly nasty raptor.' WHERE `entry`=11211;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s good of Theramore to send someone. Your guard friend\'s suspicions were correct. We\'ve got some new neighbors, and they aren\'t the kind you\'d bring a casserole.' WHERE `entry`=11212;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s fortunate Nazeer thought to send someone. We\'ve got some new neighbors and they\'ve been nothing but pests since they set up camp.' WHERE `entry`=11213;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So Theramore is interested in doing business? Well, that\'s not an offer I\'d turn down. Supplies are pretty scarce here right now, so we need all the business contacts we can get!' WHERE `entry`=11214;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I won\'t turn down any help! We\'re in the process of setting up here and trying to make the most of what we\'ve got, until those supplies from the zeppelin arrive.' WHERE `entry`=11215;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='I was sent here by my mentor to look for assistance, but unfortunately I\'m not allowed outside of Lower City and the individuals that frequent this establishment tend to be less than helpful.$B$BYou do seem different, more like the adventurous type. If you\'re interested in aiding our cause, speak to Archmagae Alturus outside of Medivh\'s old dwelling, Karazhan.$B$BIn the meantime, I\'m going to see about gaining access to the rest of the city. One of our old associates is rumored to be here.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='I thank you for taking the time to come to our aid. We\'ve important work ahead of us.' WHERE `entry`=11216;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you! This will help keep our guys going out in the field until Moxie returns with the rest of the supplies from the zeppelin crash.' WHERE `entry`=11217;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The ore gave you a strange feeling? Maybe we wnon\'t use that stuff after all.$B$B<Steelring looks at the stuff and takes a step back, changing the subject.>$B$BThose gems look really nice! I wonder what I can get for them? Of course, there are always repairs, and new stuff to be made.$B$BYou know, I\'ve really found working with you to be profitable. Take this... it\'s the least that I can do!' WHERE `entry`=11218;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The fires are out! You and your fire brigade were victorious! Hah!$B$BThe Headless Horseman\'s attack has failed, but until he and his head are destroyed together, He will return.$B$BUntil then, however, let\'s take comfort in the safety you brought our children. I am honored to have watched your brave work today.' WHERE `entry`=11219;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='The Horde\'s children need you! Do not abandon them!' WHERE `entry`=11219;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Until the head of the Headless Horseman is destroyed, his rampage will not end.$B$BThe Horseman rests within the Forlorn Cloister of the Scarlet Monastery, in Tirisfal Glade. Go to his pumpkin shrine and speak these words:$B$B  Horseman, rise$B  Your time is nigh$B  You felt death once$B  Now, know demise!$B$BThis will rouse the fiend. Destroy the head of the Horseman\'s and he will plague us no longer.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='The origin of this shrine is unknown, but there is no doubt to whom it pays homage...' WHERE `entry`=11220;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Cannons are holding us back? I\'ll show them cannons.' WHERE `entry`=11221;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Highlord Bolvar listens while you deliver Jaina\'s message.>$B$BAre you certain? This is a very serious charge...' WHERE `entry`=11222;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That is excellent news, $N! I was worried the highlord might question the veracity of our information, but I see now my concern was misplaced.$B$BYou are to be well rewarded for your efforts on behalf of Theramore and the Alliance.' WHERE `entry`=11223;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I\'m indebted to you, $C. At least with most of the mules and equipment recovered, we can hope to rebuild our numbers soon.$B$BPlease, take this.' WHERE `entry`=11224;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Have you come here to spy on me? No?$B$BPerhaps you have an appreciation for fine cuisine, then? Good, you can help!' WHERE `entry`=11225;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Did you hunt down some crows, $Gboy:girl;? Good $Gboy:girl;, good $Gboy:girl;!$B$BAh, these hounds remind me of my days raising purebreds in Tirisfal... those were good times!' WHERE `entry`=11227;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The dwarf speaks the truth. We can\'t afford to lose this port. It\'s one of two safe harbors that the Alliance has on this chunk of frozen hell - the other being a few hundred miles west of here on the coast of the Borean Tundra.' WHERE `entry`=11228;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I hope you\'re ready to fight, $N. The Queen\'s fleet needs you!' WHERE `entry`=11229;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Nice work paring those mongrels down to size. My men will be able to clean up the rest.' WHERE `entry`=11230;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Bless you child! With your help, the Light shines even in the darkest of places.$B$BPlease, take this as just compensation for your good deeds. I shall see to the salvation of those you freed; at least, those truly within the Light, and the Alliance, who returned here to the keep.' WHERE `entry`=11231;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent. I will signal our ground troops to make their move.' WHERE `entry`=11232;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This marks undisputable victory for our forces. Anselm will be most glad to hear about this.' WHERE `entry`=11233;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It was about time. The Alliance has been a thorn in our side for a long time now.$B$BThere\'s no time to celebrate, however. Look to the west, it appears we have visitors.' WHERE `entry`=11234;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good work, $N, and good riddance.$B$BBut, what you say about that place troubles me still, and I think our culling is not quite at an end!' WHERE `entry`=11235;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The captain breathes a sigh of relief.>$B$BWell, that should take some of the pressure off of us.$B$B$N, time and again you have proven yourself invaluable to Westguard Keep and the Alliance at large. Pick something from the treasury, $G boy : girl;! It\'s the least we can do!' WHERE `entry`=11236;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='$N, we can\'t let this come to pass!' WHERE `entry`=11237;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Wow, that horn is cold!$B$BOnce again you\'ve saved Westguard Keep from certain doom. What a curious $G man : woman; you are, $N. If only there were more of you.$B$BWell, this certainly calls for a reward. Which do you prefer?' WHERE `entry`=11238;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The priest quietly mouths a benediction for you.>$B$BBless you, $N, you have answered my prayers. Stand proudly in the Light, chin held high with the knowledge that your actions were most holy!$B$BI\'m certain that the church\'s coffers can yield up something of use to you.' WHERE `entry`=11239;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The sapper grumbles as if he wishes that you hadn\'t succeeded.>$B$BThe captain will be pleased to hear of your success.$B$BYou know, since you\'ve been such a good sport in dealing with this Whisper Gulch business, why don\'t you take your pick of one of these?' WHERE `entry`=11240;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Apothecary Hanes is alive? You burned the Alliance supplies to the ground? He must\'ve gotten a real kick out of that.$B$BAt any rate, the Royal Apothecary Society is in your debt, $N. We thank you from the bottom of our black, black hearts.' WHERE `entry`=11241;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What is this? The tome of Thomas Thomson? But that is the name of the Horseman before he was cursed! Does this mean that he is finally free? Does this mean he will no longer torment the good people of Azeroth?$B$BWhat a joyous day! $N, your feat will live long with us. The children, and their children, will sing your name!' WHERE `entry`=11242;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You gave our defenders the extra support they needed, $N. Morale is higher than ever now, thanks to you. I think they\'ll be able to handle the remaining onslaught on their own. I\'ve got bigger plans for you...' WHERE `entry`=11243;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What the vrykul did to our scouts was a gruesome display of savagery. It was a scare tactic, meant to weaken our resolve... to send us running in fear for our lives.$B$BIt failed.$B$BWe are going to show those monsters what it means to wage war against the Alliance!' WHERE `entry`=11244;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent targeting, $G sir : ma\'am;! I\'ll have to remember to buy a round for the cannoneers back at the keep.' WHERE `entry`=11245;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Southwest Tower Targeted',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Southeast Tower Targeted' WHERE `entry`=11245;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well, $G sir : ma\'am;, I have to say that you went about that particular business with a bit of zeal.$B$B<The sergeant looks at you warily.>$B$BAnyway, if you don\'t mind, I\'ll be taking my machete back now. It looks dull and we wouldn\'t want you to accidentally slip and carve me up, too.' WHERE `entry`=11246;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Very good, $G sir : ma\'am;. That couldn\'t have been done without your help.$B$BI\'m sure that the captain will be pleased with my report on the matter once we\'re done here.' WHERE `entry`=11247;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A pleasure to meet you, $G sir : ma\'am;! I look forward to working with you.$B$BSpeaking of which, we have a great deal to do.' WHERE `entry`=11248;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Yes, $G my son : my daughter;, that is ominous-looking, and you obviously had the right of it.$B$BThank you for bringing this scroll to me. I am very keen to study its implications. If I were to hazard a guess, I would say that these vrykul have a way to transcend death; at least those that are worthy.$B$BBy defeating the Winterskorn thane, you proved him unworthy. The Light only knows what he would have become, and what terror he might have rained down upon us, had you not slain him.' WHERE `entry`=11249;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That\'s unbelievably good news! I knew that you could pull it off, $N!$B$BAt least someone around here can produce results!$B$BWell, this calls for a reward. Go ahead, take your pick; the treasury is open to you.' WHERE `entry`=11250;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Late though ye may be, it\'s good to see a friendly face.$B$BNow stop standin\' around with yer thumb up yer nose. there\'s work to be done!' WHERE `entry`=11251;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Outstanding!$B$BThis could be the turn of luck we\'ve all been hoping for.$B$BWell done, $N!' WHERE `entry`=11252;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This scaly scroll is covered in stark painted images. You\'ve a feeling this is the sort of thing the kennel keeper had in mind when he asked you to look for clues.' WHERE `entry`=11253;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The high executor looks at the map intently, occasionally looking up at landmarks around the Fjord.>$B$BHere\'s the eastern coastline over here. The Dragonflayer and Winterskorn villages are here and here... and this must be us over here, marked for death.' WHERE `entry`=11254;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Those soldiers you rescued had a good bit of information for us. These monsters call themselves \'vrykul.\' The tribe that\'s taken up residence in Wyrmskull Village is led by a mystic named Yanis who himself is an underling of another vrykul known as Ingvar the Plunderer.' WHERE `entry`=11255;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It will be interesting to learn about your people, $C, while fighting alongside you.$B$BShall we proceed?' WHERE `entry`=11256;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Have you done that before? Your skill with my machete seemed practiced.$B$B<The brave looks at you warily.>$B$BI\'ll take it back from you now, $C.' WHERE `entry`=11257;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The brave nods at you in clear approval of your handling of the torch>$B$BLet these vrykul feel the heat of the land. Let them know the fear they would instill in others!' WHERE `entry`=11258;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have a strong arm, $N.$B$BIt looks as if those wind riders finally made themselves useful instead of just standing around and drinking all day.' WHERE `entry`=11259;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Southwest Tower Targeted',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Southeast Tower Targeted' WHERE `entry`=11259;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Yes, that is ominous-looking, and you obviously had the right of it.$B$BThank you for bringing this scroll to me. I will study its implications. If I were to hazard a guess, I would say that these vrykul have a way to transcend death; at least those that are worthy.$B$BBy defeating the Winterskorn thane, you proved him unworthy. Who knows what he would have become, and what terror he might have rained down upon us, had you not slain him?' WHERE `entry`=11260;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That is good news indeed! You have given us some breathing room to further our preparations for leaving.$B$BPlease, take one of these as a sign of our appreciation.' WHERE `entry`=11261;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent work, $N. With their leader removed, our efforts against these vrykul should be more successful.$B$BService such as this cannot go unrewarded!' WHERE `entry`=11262;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have my thanks, $N. I know that you do not have any duty to me or my people.$B$BWhat you say about that place troubles me still, and I sense that our culling is not quite at an end.' WHERE `entry`=11263;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Chieftain Ashtotem breathes a sigh of relief.>$B$BThat should take some of the pressure off.$B$B$N, time and again you have proven your value to the taunka of Camp Winterhoof. Please, choose something from our bounty. I insist.' WHERE `entry`=11264;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A great stone is lifted from my shoulders to hear of your success. And I smile to know that some you freed were taunka.$B$BPlease, take this as a gift for what you have done. I shall see to the health of those you freed.' WHERE `entry`=11265;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='$N, we cannot let this come to pass!' WHERE `entry`=11266;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This horn is as cold as the land... perhaps even colder!$B$BYou have saved Camp Winterhoof from certain doom, not that we\'ll be staying here much longer. What a curious $Gman:woman; you are, $N. Perhaps you $R-types from over the ocean are not so bad after all.$B$BThis calls for a reward. Which do you prefer?' WHERE `entry`=11267;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The greatmother nods her approval of your actions.>$B$BThank you, $N, you have done what is right and you have bought us a little more time to finish our preparations for leaving. We will soon make the journey north.$B$BI am too old; when we go, I will not be able to carry everything with me. Would you like to take one of these?' WHERE `entry`=11268;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank goodness! This should be enough to finish the order in time. Of course, I won\'t sleep until the troops arrive, but that\'s far better than risking Captain Adams\' wrath.$B$BI\'ve heard the stories they tell about him!' WHERE `entry`=11269;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I\'m glad you\'ve proven you can follow orders. If I had a copper piece for every arrogant fool in shiny armor to come here and think they\'re above the chain of command... well, I\'d have a few gold.$B$BNow that you\'ve demonstrated a measure of discipline, I have other tasks more suitable for someone of your caliber.' WHERE `entry`=11270;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='With your contribution, we\'ll be well prepared for the journey. I haven\'t much to offer you for your help, but I will give you a choice of some of my spare combat gear.' WHERE `entry`=11271;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Revenge feels good. To think that this is but a taste of what\'s to come.$B$BArthas will get what he deserves soon enough. Then and only then will I die a happy man.' WHERE `entry`=11272;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve found Pulroy. A bit too late it seems.$B$BWhile looking over the corpse you see a journal clenched tightly in Pulroy\'s death grip. Upon examining the journal you read what appears to be the scribbling of a dying dwarf.' WHERE `entry`=11273;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve found Zedd. You\'re no doctor but the prognosis for Zedd is most assuredly negative.$B$BIt looks as if they were preparing to feed him to the worgs. Gruesome...' WHERE `entry`=11274;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These are all fine horns, $N. Let me examine them and select the one I will use in the hunt.$B$BI\'ll give the rest to the craftsmen for use in their carvings.' WHERE `entry`=11275;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='About bloody time! Pulroy and Zedd are dead.$B$BAnd Daegarn...$B$B<Glorenfeld shakes his head.>$B$BTaken by the Dragonflayer chieftain into the depths of these catacombs. I overheard that oversized mongrel mention something \'bout a sacrifice to the "Dread King."$B$BThe cipher is hidden away in Daegarn\'s grimy beard.$B$BWhat? Dwarves hide things in their beards all the time!' WHERE `entry`=11276;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well, mate. Now that we\'ve secured the tablets we can try and save Daegarn\'s life and recover the cipher that will help us decode the meaning behind these ancient relics!$B$BI\'ll hold on to these tablets, you rescue Daegarn.' WHERE `entry`=11277;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Sorting these tablets out is going to take some time. All I can gather from a precursory study is that whatever used to be here was an ancestor of the humans. Those vrykul things probably killed \'em all off. Anyhow, we\'ll know more once I get these relics set up.' WHERE `entry`=11278;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What?! No, this can\'t be right.$B$BCURSES!$B$BThis batch of the plague doesn\'t seem to have had any real effect on the proto-whelps at all other than to make them glow green!$B$BMy dream of using the plague upon anything we come into contact with seems to have gone up in smoke!' WHERE `entry`=11279;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='NOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO!!!$B$B<The plaguebringer begins to cry.>$B$BAll of my hopes... all of my dreams, ruined!$B$BLeave me, $N. Leave me to my despair. I\'m nothing.$B$BHere, you might as well take all of my worldly possessions. When the rest of the apothecaries hear of my failure, I\'ll be done for and won\'t need them anyway.' WHERE `entry`=11280;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Nokoma listens to your report from the test.>$B$BI\'m relieved that the horn worked so well... maybe too well if what you\'re saying was true. You\'re sure the beast spoke? I don\'t know if I can go on with the hunt if that\'s true. I\'ll have to speak with Chief Ashtotem about it.$B$BThis horn may end up being merely decorative, but that won\'t diminish its worth. Thank you for all your help, $N.' WHERE `entry`=11281;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You do some good killings over there. I see vrykul men fall and get stabbed with Sylvanas flag. Our side doing good!' WHERE `entry`=11282;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You must have lots of practice with doing killings. You almost as good as Gorth!' WHERE `entry`=11283;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='You done with the killings yet? Winterskorn town right across from here!' WHERE `entry`=11283;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done it? By the Light, you\'re a walking miracle! I was beginning to think I\'d personally have to explain to Captain Adams why his men\'s weapons weren\'t ready in time!' WHERE `entry`=11284;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I guess you burned everything. I see couple of spots not burning... but is close enough for Gorth.' WHERE `entry`=11285;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Winterskorn Bridge Burned',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Winterskorn Barracks Burned' WHERE `entry`=11285;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The sage grunts his approval at your actions on his behalf.>$B$BPerhaps I will be able to find the time soon to study these artifacts and come to an understanding of their significance.$B$BBut now there are more pressing matters to attend to.' WHERE `entry`=11286;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='My mother should not concern herself with my safety. But, I thank you for coming, stranger.$B$BSince you are here, perhaps you will help me with a few things?' WHERE `entry`=11287;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You feel compelled to place the sacred blade next to the body of Ares.$B$BUpon doing this you are once again blinded by light.' WHERE `entry`=11288;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Many men and women died to recover this blade. $N, I fear valiant Ares will not be the last.$B$BBut you do the Light\'s work, hero. This sacred blade will be wielded by Lord Tirion Fordring himself. Even now the Argent Crusade works toward Icecrown. Lord Fordring has vowed that he will tear down the walls of the cursed place himself! And with the blade, he just might stand a chance against the Lich King.$B$BLord Fordring remains our greatest hope.' WHERE `entry`=11289;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Vice Admiral Keller glances over the plans.>$B$BOutstanding! By the looks of things, there are many more vrykul villages in the fjord. A different tribe of vrykul is preparing an assault on Westguard Keep. Hell, for all I know it may already be too late. We haven\'t heard from Westguard in days. Either way, we must alert Westguard!' WHERE `entry`=11290;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Captain Adams takes the plans from you.>$B$BI\'m glad you decided to come over. My advisors and I will need some time to study these plans. In the meantime, we can use all the help we can get!' WHERE `entry`=11291;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Trapper Jethan inspects the creatures you\'ve brought him.>$B$BNicely done. Some of these will fetch a better price than others, but I should have plenty to trade with the locals.' WHERE `entry`=11292;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done!  That kinda shouting is sure to bring business our way.$B$BAnd we promised you a reward, here it is. The Barleybrews keep their word.$B$BOh, and come back any other day if you want to help spread the good name of Barleybrew.' WHERE `entry`=11293;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Bark in the Hall of Explorers',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Bark in the Mystic Ward' WHERE `entry`=11293;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good job! That\'ll show those arrogant Barleybrews.$B$BWell we promised you a reward and here it is. We Thunderbrew reward you with prizes, the Barleybrew reward you with foul odors and false promises.$B$BYou chose wisely.$B$BIf you want to keep making the right choice, stop by another day and help us spread the word.' WHERE `entry`=11294;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Bark in the Hall of Explorers',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Bark in the Mystic Ward' WHERE `entry`=11294;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You come to help? Good... good...$B$BGorth was getting tired of killing vrykuls all day. Help is welcome!' WHERE `entry`=11295;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That was a very brave act, $C. I did not know that your people were capable of such selflessness.$B$BNext time I will heed the warnings of my elders and steer clear of the Rivenwood. I advise you to do the same.' WHERE `entry`=11296;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ah, yes, the reclusive bison-men of the north. I\'ve seen them skulking about, believing themselves unseen. I suppose they fancy this land theirs? Well, that\'s but one of many things that will change shortly.$B$BI wasn\'t expecting any company, but while you\'re here on that fool\'s errand, you might as well make yourself useful.' WHERE `entry`=11297;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The apothecary pours out a tankard of the beverage for himself.>$B$BWell, here I go!' WHERE `entry`=11298;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Yep. You found me. Woopedy-do!$B$BAnd no, I don\'t have the cipher. My beard was the first thing those beasts checked! Oluf\'s the one that\'s got it now. He\'s the chieftain of the gladiators.' WHERE `entry`=11299;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Fascinating tale! Something is actually judgin\' these things? To what end?! For what purpose?$B$BWell, never mind that nonsense. Someone else can figure out that stuff. We got the cipher and the tablets back - and only two fatalities in the whole ordeal.' WHERE `entry`=11300;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These brains are beautiful! Gorgeous, even! They\'re exactly what I need.$B$BThank you for your help, $N. Now I\'ll show Malthus the truth his beer goggles couldn\'t reveal.' WHERE `entry`=11301;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Lurielle listens as you introduce yourself.>$B$BIt is good to finally meet you, $N. We have long hoped that you and the other newcomers might send representatives. We don\'t often venture beyond the borders of our glades, especially amid the changes the land is going through.' WHERE `entry`=11302;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We all showed up to the party, but the guest of honor stayed at home.' WHERE `entry`=11303;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This strain is far from worthless, my friend! Those fools at Vengeance Landing have had all the answers right under their own noses!' WHERE `entry`=11304;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This will do. It\'s time for some real apothecary work now, $N!' WHERE `entry`=11305;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent! You are an apt pupil, $N.$B$BNow comes the fun part. Deployment!' WHERE `entry`=11306;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The plague didn\'t disintegrate our subjects? Are you certain, $N??!$B$BThere must be an external factor we\'re not accounting for... perhaps the low temperatures of this climate? Perhaps... a mutation in the strain!' WHERE `entry`=11307;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What do you want? Can\'t you see I\'m in the middle of something?' WHERE `entry`=11308;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent! Yes, yes, these will do just fine!' WHERE `entry`=11309;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Great job, $N. Say, you wouldn\'t be looking for something more... permanent, would ya? I could sure use some help around these parts!' WHERE `entry`=11310;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The influence of the elemental spirits has receded, but it will return. We\'ve bought ourselves the time we need to complete our tasks here and take our leave.' WHERE `entry`=11311;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Lurielle listens as you introduce yourself.>$B$BIt is good to meet you, $C. My sisters have often watched the taunka search the forests for us, but we are forbidden by our queen from interacting with outsiders. You only see us now because the land has become unsettled and many of my sisters are in danger.' WHERE `entry`=11312;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Lurielle accepts the cores from you quietly.>$B$BThank you, $N.$B$B<Lurielle glances at the icy cores sadly.>$B$BI promise, my friends, I will do all I can to restore you.' WHERE `entry`=11313;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So there is hope for my sisters?$B$B<Lurielle looks away from you, then down at the ground.>$B$BI feel guilty for not thinking of the pendant sooner. We might have saved even more of the sisters.' WHERE `entry`=11314;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you for your help, $N. The Vibrant Glade was once a beautiful place, and when we return to it, we shall make it so again.' WHERE `entry`=11315;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have done well, $N. If we\'d had allies like you when the land first began to change, perhaps we might have been able to preserve some of what we\'ve lost.' WHERE `entry`=11316;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Already I can sense the change within you.$B$BAre you ready for what comes next?' WHERE `entry`=11317;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Nice work there! It takes time to get the hang of controlling your ram. But once you do, you\'ll wish every ram was a racing ram.$B$BWhat\'s that? "Where\'s my reward?" Ha Ha Ha... you got to ride the fastest ram around! You want more? Well how about this...$B$BYou\'ve been rewarded with the chance to help other people around Brewfest. There\'s plenty of work, and rewards, for an eager, young, ram racer.' WHERE `entry`=11318;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The ice core worked well for you? I\'ll have to remember that. I\'m certain the keepers will not stop just because we\'ve destroyed their work once.' WHERE `entry`=11319;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Log Descritpion' WHERE `entry`=11320;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Aww, it\'s just a stein voucher... Maybe you\'re just playing hard to get. So here\'s this years stein for you.$B$BBut I suspect I\'ll be seeing a lot more of you. After all, if you want any Brewfest tickets redeemed, I\'m your girl...$B$Bor maybe I\'m his girl...$B$Booohhh.... or his...' WHERE `entry`=11321;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Already I can sense the change within you.$B$BAre you ready for what comes next?' WHERE `entry`=11322;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You look and smell different... you are not one of my pack. Tell me your story; I have nothing but time while I am trapped in here.' WHERE `entry`=11323;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Garwal was not a worg at all! I know of these creatures... they are called worgen.$B$BBut, Ulfang indicated that it came south from the Grizzly Hills? Odd. There aren\'t any worgen there.$B$BI thank you for helping to restore Ulfang to his proper place amongst his pack. Now we both will be able to sleep peacefully.$B$BPlease, you must accept this as a sign of gratitude.' WHERE `entry`=11324;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You look and smell different... you are not one of my pack. Tell me your story; I have nothing but time while I am trapped in here.' WHERE `entry`=11325;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Garwal was not a worg at all! The thing you describe him turning into sounds a lot like a worgen!$B$BBut, Ulfang said that it came south from the Grizzly Hills? Odd. There aren\'t any worgen there.$B$BI thank you for helping to restore Ulfang to his proper place amongst his pack. Now we both will be able to sleep peacefully.$B$BPlease, you must accept this as a sign of gratitude.' WHERE `entry`=11326;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Holy... what the hell?! Look at this stuff!$B$BWe need to get this back to the keep a.s.a.p.!' WHERE `entry`=11327;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh... hey, that\'sh different!$B$BOkay, let me shee that shtuff. I jusht love tinkering with alchemy!$B$BInteresting, interesting... here, I think I know jusht what to do. A little mixing of that with the jusht the right amount of thish.$B$BYou know, I think a little dash of this rotgut will help, too ...hic!' WHERE `entry`=11328;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well, these certainly are ugly enough, but I suppose I don\'t care if it actually works. I\'ll be relieved once the expedition has passed through and I can go back to simply fishing for my dinner.' WHERE `entry`=11329;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Huh? Well that sucks! Darn, I made thingsh worsh. In fact, I think I perfected their plague for them ...hic!$B$B<Peppy grimaces and takes a huge gulp of whatever noxious brew she\'s been drinking.>$B$BWell, I wash hoping that it wouldn\'t come down to thish, but it looks like there\'sh no alternative ...hic.' WHERE `entry`=11330;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Yes, $N, what is it now?$B$BWHAT?!! A Forsaken super plague that melts you in no time?$B$BYou oozed my vrykul prisoner?$B$B<The captain looks almost sad and spits in disgust.>$B$BAlright, I know what we need to do. Or rather, what YOU need to do!' WHERE `entry`=11331;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Nicely done, $N, nicely done!$B$B<The captain seems beside himself with glee.>$B$BThat\'ll show those good-for-nothing Forsaken to think about messing with us!$B$BI\'d say you\'ve earned yourself something from the treasury!' WHERE `entry`=11332;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A bit worse for the wear but still functional.$B$B<Thoralius reaches into the pouch and removes some odd looking roots.>$B$BNow to place them in the fire and inhale!$B$B<Thoralius throws the roots into the smoldering incense burner.>$B$B<Thoralius inhales deeply. His body begins to quiver.>$B$BWha... What... It cannot be... I cannot...' WHERE `entry`=11333;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Win an Arathi Basin battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent news, $C! If our tactical deployments continue to be this successful, the Horde will be in full retreat before long.' WHERE `entry`=11335;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Tell me, $N. What news do you bring from the front?' WHERE `entry`=11335;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Win an Alterac Valley battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Just what I wanted to hear!  A victory in Alterac Valley - even a temporary one - is crucial to our overall strategy against the Horde.' WHERE `entry`=11336;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Tell me, $N. What news do you bring from the front?' WHERE `entry`=11336;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Win an Eye of the Storm battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='We\'ve come one step closer to achieving total victory over the Horde. We cannot allow the enemy to obtain a foothold in this world or any other.' WHERE `entry`=11337;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Tell me, $N. What news do you bring from the front?' WHERE `entry`=11337;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Win a Warsong Gulch battleground match and return to an Alliance Brigadier General at any Alliance capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent work, $N. The integrity of our borders must be preserved at all costs!' WHERE `entry`=11338;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Tell me, $N. What news do you bring from the front?' WHERE `entry`=11338;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Win an Arathi Basin battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve brought great honor to the Horde, $N. Your victory today will ensure a thousand victories tomorrow!' WHERE `entry`=11339;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='You\'re back already. Do you bring news of victory?' WHERE `entry`=11339;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Win an Alterac Valley battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='There is no greater honor than driving invaders from Horde territories. We salute your great courage in aiding our forces today!' WHERE `entry`=11340;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='You\'re back!  Do you bring news of victory?' WHERE `entry`=11340;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Win an Eye of the Storm battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='You bring honor to us all, $N. We must show the enemy that we will fight them wherever we find them.' WHERE `entry`=11341;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='You\'re back already. Do you bring news of victory?' WHERE `entry`=11341;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Win a Warsong Gulch battleground match and return to a Horde Warbringer at any Horde capital city or Shattrath.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Horde is in your debt, $N. You\'ve made your people proud with your courage in defending our lands.' WHERE `entry`=11342;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='You\'re back already. Do you bring news of victory?' WHERE `entry`=11342;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I do not understand. The creatures that you saw looked like the vrykul that are attacking Valgarde?' WHERE `entry`=11343;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='What have you discovered?' WHERE `entry`=11343;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Human children born of vrykul? And Ymiron ordered the deaths of all human born offspring?$B$B<Thoralius goes silent for a moment.>$B$BAs much as I wish to deny what is so plainly presented to me, I cannot. There is no extinct "missing link" to humans as the Explorers\' League proposed. The vrykul are the missing link. They are the progenitors of humanity.' WHERE `entry`=11344;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='What have you discovered?' WHERE `entry`=11344;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Prospector Belvar browses the book of runes.>$B$BHmm... there\'s so much here. I\'m going to need some time to study it, and if we hope to understand these runes, we\'ll need to try to make our own.' WHERE `entry`=11346;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well in defeating Binder Murdis, but the Iron Dwarves won\'t give up easily.$B$BWe\'ve made a lot of progress in understanding how they manipulate runes. Perhaps next time we encounter them, our knowledge will give us an advantage.' WHERE `entry`=11348;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Belvar handles the tools carefully.>$B$BI\'m going to try these out. If we\'re to understand the Iron Dwarves\' motives and defeat them, I need to know exactly what the runes are doing.' WHERE `entry`=11349;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The longrunner browses the book of runes.>$B$BI\'m no loremaster, but I have some familiarity with the language of the Iron Dwarves. I think the runes they\'re carving on the giants are derived from their spoken language, but there are some differences.' WHERE `entry`=11350;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Pembe examines the tools.>$B$BThese are more delicate than I\'d thought. Allow me a moment to try them out.' WHERE `entry`=11351;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well in defeating Binder Murdis, but the Iron Dwarves won\'t give up easily.$B$BAs my people move north, I\'m certain we will encounter the Iron Dwarves again. Next time, we will be prepared to thwart them before they can dig in.' WHERE `entry`=11352;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Another soon-to-be satisfied customer. It looks like it\'s in fine condition. You are to be rewarded.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11354;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Researcher Aderan listens to your findings.>$B$BThe runes for "north" and "west" appeared multiple times? There\'s a highly reinforced command to move in that direction, but the runes are more than propulsion. Something is attracting them, but what?' WHERE `entry`=11355;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re here to visit the children!  Wonderful!  They have known such heartache in their short lives. It is good that they see real heroes like you. It really lifts their spirits!' WHERE `entry`=11356;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The children love to watch heroes at their work. It is my hope that, one day, each of these orphans will grow into a strong member of the Horde, and ultimately die in glorious battle!$B$BAh, thoughts of such a fine fate brings mist to my eyes...' WHERE `entry`=11357;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Aderan listens as you describe your findings.>$B$BOf course! This Megalith must be the key to the Iron Dwarves\' plans. We must destroy it before their plan comes to fruition!' WHERE `entry`=11358;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well in felling Megalith, but I wonder about his final words.$B$BYou\'re sure he said the Stoneforge?$B$BI know of no place with that name, but it sounds like a word with origins in the titans. What plans do the Iron Dwarves have for such a thing? This bears watching, $N, for we must find it before the Iron Dwarves\' plan comes to fruition.' WHERE `entry`=11359;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re wet and smudged with soot!  You must have been extinguishing fires!$B$BWell done!  As an honorary member of the Goldshire Fire Brigade, I beg you to return here if ever the village needs you!' WHERE `entry`=11360;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `objectives_loc6`='Toss buckets on 5 fires, then speak with the Masked Orphan Matron in Razor Hill.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well done, $N! Children, take a good look at this $C. Grow strong and brave like him and one day you too will fight for the Horde.' WHERE `entry`=11361;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Perhaps I will have new feathers tied onto it before shipping it on to the buyer. I\'m certain with so many arakkoa hereabouts it will not prove difficult. A small matter, and nothing to detract from your reward in any case.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11362;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Truly a daring acquisition that the bards should put pen to parchment for. Here, you have more than earned this.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11363;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Very well, you have earned your bounty.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11364;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The sage listens to your findings.>$B$BThe runes for "north" and "west" appeared over and over? I\'m not an expert in these runes, but the repetition of them suggests a strong command.$B$BThese carvings are more than passive directions, though. They seem to pull the giants toward something, but what?' WHERE `entry`=11365;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Edan listens as you describe your findings.>$B$BMegalith? A literal transcription from the tablet! This Megalith must be the centerpiece of the iron ones\' mysterious plans.' WHERE `entry`=11366;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve done well in felling Megalith, but I wonder about his final words.$B$BYou\'re sure he said the Stoneforge?$B$BIt is not a name our people know, but it sounds like it might be a creation of the "titans" the ousiders speak of. The Iron Dwarves have ever been a cunning and dangerous foe, $N. We must watch these giants and find this Stoneforge before they can carry out their plans.' WHERE `entry`=11367;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Now that I think of it, it\'s a pity I didn\'t ask you to return with the other two hearts as well. Perhaps next time. In any case, you\'ve earned your commission.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11368;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Is it not amazing to feel the life pulsing within the egg? I must hurry to deliver it to the purchaser. We wouldn\'t want it hatching here now would we?$B$BYour payment is ready.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11369;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Indeed, I fear my customer will not have time to peruse the entirety of this book. Nevertheless, that is not our concern. Here is your reward.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11370;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I trust that it was a fight worthy of your time? Certainly this bounty will be.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11371;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I am sure that these feathers will make a fine addition to the chieftain\'s headdress. You have earned your compensation, $C.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11372;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<You sense a deep level of satisfaction from the wind trader.>$B$BGood, I am glad to hear of his demise. And perhaps I will be able to unlock the secrets of his amulet for myself. If not, then I will sell it for a handsome price.$B$BI trust that this reward is sufficient.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11373;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re quite the heroine, $N. I am certain that my customer will find a way to free the spirit of their loved one from within the gem. For a job well done, your payment awaits.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11374;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I was worried that you might not return. I trust that you didn\'t go deaf from fighting Murmur?$B$BHere is your reward. The professor will be pleased no doubt, though I worry what he ultimately wishes to do with this thing.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11375;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I am satisfied. He who speaks through the nether shall be as well. Mah\'duun has your bounty prepared.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'deen.' WHERE `entry`=11376;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Oh, I do smell something tasty! I hope you gave that bird quite a good beating.$B$BPlease, help yourself to some of my extra stock. I\'m sure someone of your talent could put it to good use.' WHERE `entry`=11377;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I see you are returned to the present time intact.$B$B<The wind trader looks around.>$B$BIt doesn\'t appear that anything has changed. But then again, how would I know?$B$BThat\'s a nice cut; my customer will be pleased. Here is your reward.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11378;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Now look at that...$B$B<The Rokk takes a sip of the concoction and his face twists into a bizarre mask of pain and delight.>$B$BSweet A\'dal that\'s good! A cook with your potential shouldn\'t be without his proper materials. Take some of my extra stock and make me proud.' WHERE `entry`=11379;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Those are the juiciest mana berries I\'ve ever seen. I think I\'m getting smarter just by looking at them.$B$BSince I no longer need most of my meat and fish stock, why don\'t you take some? I\'m certain you could make something delicious.' WHERE `entry`=11380;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That is a fine batch of spiritual soup if I ever did smell one. Just a pinch of pepper and it\'s done.$B$BAs promised, here\'s your cut. And because you did such a fine job, I\'m going to throw in some of my extra stock.' WHERE `entry`=11381;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Odd that the sands in that thing are still falling upward. I think I will have it delivered to its new owner with all due haste.$B$BI thank you for a job well done, $C. You have certainly earned your commission.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11382;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You found your way back in time, and then back again. You must be a great $C, $R. The bounty is earned.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11383;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Aw, you did get it! It\'s so tiny. And yet, when the druids are done with it -- a process I am told will take a very long time -- Warp Splinter will be regrown anew.$B$BAnd here is your reward as promised.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11384;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='And now they are dead, channeling no longer. He who whispers upon the nether is satisfied and you have secured the bounty.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11385;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I\'m tempted to keep it for myself and return my client\'s money. It could certainly expand the reach of my business.$B$B<The wind trader sighs.>$B$BHowever, I have a reputation to uphold.$B$BSpeaking of my reputation, thank you for helping me to maintain it. Here is your commission.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11386;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Mah\'duun enjoys fighting constructs; they are less messy than organic beings.$B$BThe bounty is yours.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11387;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I dare not touch the scroll lest I too risk the notice of the Old Gods. I will have one of my assistants handle its delivery.$B$BYou have more than earned your reward, $C, and I wish you all the luck in the known worlds.$B$BCome back tomorrow and I will have another request for you to fulfill.' WHERE `entry`=11388;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='The sentinels within the Arcatraz have gone haywire. The prisoners run rampant and the guards attack those that would help.$B$BMah\'duun hears the speaker on the nether winds. The speaker says to destroy the sentinels$B$BAccomplish this and today\'s bounty is yours.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='With the sentinels destroyed, perhaps the naaru will ask the Consortium to replace them? Mah\'duun does not know and does not care.$B$BYou have earned the bounty.$B$BReturn again tomorrow and the winds will have whispered once more to Mah\'duun.' WHERE `entry`=11389;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good job, though I think ye might be wanting a refresher course in basic piloting.$B$BWell, no matter, one warm body\'s as good as another. Here\'s yer haul for the day.' WHERE `entry`=11390;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Nice shooting, ace.$B$BHere\'s your wages. Come back tomorrow for another round, ya hear?' WHERE `entry`=11391;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Will you lay the candle down and call the Headless Horseman from his doomed rest?' WHERE `entry`=11392;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The explorer beams a smile as you tell him who sent you. He continues in hushed tones.>$B$BIrena was concerned about me? She gets that from her father you know.' WHERE `entry`=11393;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Jaren seems very excited about your success, but motions you to keep your conversation to a whisper.>$B$BGreat job, $N! That\'s a lot of Scourge goo all over your stuff though. You might want to think about a quick dip in the strait. It\'s cold, but it\'ll get you cleaned up right quick.' WHERE `entry`=11394;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I know what this is! $N, it\'s a controlling device for those scourging crystals!$B$BI bet anything that it can be used to shut down their force fields. Hmmm.$B$B<The explorer looks thoughtful as he ponders the implications of you having the device.>' WHERE `entry`=11395;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Nice!$B$B<Jaren looks around quickly to make sure that nothing noticed his outburst.>$B$BAlright, you certainly earned your pick of one of these things I found while I was down here.$B$BAnd, $N, if you happen to find yourself back at Steel Gate, give Irena my love and let her know that I\'m okay.' WHERE `entry`=11396;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Anastasia ponders your success for a moment.>$B$BA satisfactory job to be certain, yet somehow I sense that there\'s something else we should be doing to stop the efforts of the Scourge on that beach.' WHERE `entry`=11397;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I can tell you what this is, $N. It\'s a controlling device for those scourging crystals down there!$B$BI bet anything that it can be used to shut down their force fields. Hmmm.$B$B<The apothecary looks thoughtful as she ponders the implications of you having the device.>' WHERE `entry`=11398;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Anastasia turns and smiles at her succubus.>$B$BVery well, $N, I concede that you have certainly earned a choice of one of these.' WHERE `entry`=11399;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good job, $N... you\'ve won the trust of the festival\'s brewers, earning the right to purchase a Brewfest riding ram.' WHERE `entry`=11400;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Will you lay the candle down and call the Headless Horseman from his doomed rest?' WHERE `entry`=11401;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `title_loc6`='Clayton\'s Quest: Extreme!!',`details_loc6`='Clayton wants you to find and slay twenty Evil Squirrels.' WHERE `entry`=11402;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What? This holy tome once belonged to an infamous paladin of the Alliance. Was he the Headless Horseman? Does this mean that the Horseman is defeated?$B$BThis is a glorious day, $N! Your legend will shine bright, and may it last for twice the years of the Horseman\'s reign of fear.' WHERE `entry`=11403;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Will you lay the candle down and call the Headless Horseman from his doomed rest?' WHERE `entry`=11404;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Will you lay the candle down and call the Headless Horseman from his doomed rest?' WHERE `entry`=11405;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So the quartermaster sent you?$B$B<Gil seems relieved.>$B$BTo be honest, we\'re running a bit behind here and we\'re going to need some help making our goals.$B$B<Gil shudders.>$B$BNone of the men want to brave the wrath of Captain Adams.' WHERE `entry`=11406;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You kept your word and let people know about our brewmasters. Thank you. We promised you these tickets, and gladly give them to you. I imagine the trolls are a bit more stingy with handing over their tickets...$B$BCome back another day to help us spread the word about Brewfest.' WHERE `entry`=11407;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Bark in the Valley of Wisdom',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Bark in the Valley of Spirits' WHERE `entry`=11407;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ya did it! We gotta get ready for the flood of customers that are sure to come our way! Thanks!$B$BOh, that\'s right, and we promised you a reward. Can\'t forget about that...$B$BFeel free to stop by again another day to help us spread the word some more.' WHERE `entry`=11408;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Bark in the Valley of Wisdom',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Bark in the Valley of Spirits' WHERE `entry`=11408;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hey, that wasn\'t too bad... are you sure you\'re not a dwarf?$B$BSo there\'s plenty more racing to be had and it\'s not just from me. All over the Brewfest grounds you\'ll find people in need of a decent ram racer. So go and make yourself useful.$B$BOh and don\'t forget, these rams were legally obtained. I just want to make sure we\'re clear.' WHERE `entry`=11409;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='At last, we can finally fish in peace! \'Course, by the time we catch anything, the expedition\'ll arrive and claim it all for themselves.$B$BYou have our thanks, $N. Don\'t be a stranger \'round here.' WHERE `entry`=11410;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<The chieftain listens as you introduce yourself.>$B$BI am Chieftain Ashtotem, and my people are the taunka, and I will speak truly, outsider. Among my people, trust is earned, not given. You have my leave to walk among them and offer your assistance. Time grows short and some of them may welcome even an outsider\'s help with their preparations.' WHERE `entry`=11411;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thanks for your help! As long as Brewfest is going and the Dark Iron Dwarves are attacking and our supplier is stuck in that canyon, I\'ll need some help shipping kegs. So if you want to work for more tickets, talk to me every day.$B$BHere are the tickets we promised you. Have fun!' WHERE `entry`=11412;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What\'s this? A stein voucher? So you like drinking? Great! After I give you this stein, go have a few drinks! Then a few more. Maybe have a few more after that... Then, now this is important, come see me.$B$BLook, I know you\'ll be back eventually. If you want your Brewfest tickets redeemed, or Keg Protector marks redeemed, you have to see me.$B$BAnyways, here\'s the stein, and remember to talk to me later.' WHERE `entry`=11413;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The smell of their blood upon your muzzle pleases me. Brothers should not turn on each other.' WHERE `entry`=11414;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The smell of their blood upon your muzzle pleases me. Brothers should not turn on each other.' WHERE `entry`=11415;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Ulfang howls loudly at your defeat of his great eagle enemy.>$B$BThe honor of the kill is yours. I wish that it had been my maw to finally close upon her neck.$B$BLet us not waste the sacrifice that she has made for us. Here, eat them!' WHERE `entry`=11416;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Ulfang howls loudly at your defeat of his great eagle enemy.>$B$BThe honor of the kill is yours. I wish that it had been my maw to finally close upon her neck.$B$BLet us not waste the sacrifice that she has made for us. Here, eat them!' WHERE `entry`=11417;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You saw a nest, with hatchlings? Hmm... so our "he" is actually a "she," eh?$B$BI guess that settles it. I suppose I wouldn\'t want to move a nest full of hatchlings just because of a new neighbor, either.$B$B<Gil favors Trapper Jethan with a mock glare.>$B$BI\'m sure we\'d get along just fine if ol\' Jethan would stop trying to make a trophy of her.' WHERE `entry`=11418;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good job, $N... you\'ve won the trust of the festival\'s brewers, earning the right to purchase a Brewfest riding ram.' WHERE `entry`=11419;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Zorek flips through the manual.>$B$BHrm, interesting...$B$BAccording to the manual, the vrykul have a special tool that allows them to control the harpoon guns with deadly accuracy. It looks a bit like the wheel of one of our ships. Furthermore, it\'s portable and seems to plug into the harpoon guns like a key. We need to get our hands on one of those!' WHERE `entry`=11420;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Excellent work, $N! You took out a good chunk of their dragon riders and really pissed off their leadership.$B$BAre you ready to head back to Valgarde and report the good news to Zorek? If so, I\'ve got a crazy idea!' WHERE `entry`=11421;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText3_loc6`='Dragonflayer Dockhouse Destroyed',`ObjectiveText4_loc6`='Dragonflayer Storage Facility Destroyed' WHERE `entry`=11421;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Reaching out to take his son\'s trident from you, Old Icefin\'s hand shakes a little. Could it be that the aged murloc is grieving?>$B$B<Is that just extra moisture pooling at the base of his eye?>' WHERE `entry`=11422;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This is of tremendous value, $N. I must renew my efforts in salvaging and translating vrykul texts.$B$BDon\'t get me wrong. Our enemies need to be destroyed... their ancient knowledge doesn\'t.' WHERE `entry`=11423;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hmmmmph... these will do for now. There seems to be some oddness to them.$B$BI tell ya - I\'ve handled body parts for years now and never have I had such a weird feeling in my stomach. Anyway, a deal is a deal. Here\'s your payment.' WHERE `entry`=11424;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Outstanding! Those overgrown apes will soon know what it means to mess with the Alliance!' WHERE `entry`=11426;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Lieutenant Icehammer takes the harpoon control mechanism from you.>$B$BAh, you come bearing gifts!' WHERE `entry`=11427;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='My heart broke when I learned the keepers had turned against us. Once, we considered them our brothers and our closest friends.$B$BI grieve for the brothers and sisters we have lost, but without your help, there would be no hope for our future. You will always be welcome among us, $N.' WHERE `entry`=11428;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='For the Alliance! You\'re a strong one, $N. Strong enough to crack some vrykul skull at Nifflevar.' WHERE `entry`=11429;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Still alive, I see. Clearly you\'re not trying hard enough.',`ObjectiveText1_loc6`='Alliance Banner Placed' WHERE `entry`=11429;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'ll take them a while to find a replacement for Yavus. Now is the perfect time to unleash Zorek\'s plan! While they\'re scurrying to regain control of Nifflevar, you\'re going to use their own harpoon guns against them!' WHERE `entry`=11430;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `details_loc6`='Hey there!  I\'m a crazy dwarf!  We dwarves believe when you get enough brew together, invisible creatures show up. In fact they are probably wandering around the Brewfest grounds right now! But you can only see them if you are really drunk.$B$BWe dwarves will come up with any excuse to drink.$B$BI bet you want a reason to drink too... So here it is, bring me 5 of those wolpertingers with this net I got from a really drunk dwarf.$B$BIf you can\'t see them, you\'re probably not drunk enough.',`objectives_loc6`='The "dwarf," Glodrak Huntsniper, has asked you to capture 5 Stunned Wolpertingers using the Wolpertinger Net. He mentioned that you must be intoxicated to see them.',`offerrewardtext_loc6`='Well, lookee there! Ye\'ve got yerself a right bushel o\' wolpertingers, ye do!$B$B<He takes a deep drink from his tankard.>$B$BI\'ll tell ye what I\'m gonna do. Since ye\'re such a spot-on $C, I\'ll let ye keep one\'a these fer yer very own!' WHERE `entry`=11431;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did what had to be done. Though some might consider it dishonorable to slay the helpless, in this case you would have been a fool to have done otherwise.$B$BAnd we certainly couldn\'t have just left them standing there to be ritually wakened, now could we?$B$BIt was a brave thing you did for all of us down in those catacombs, $N.' WHERE `entry`=11432;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did what had to be done. The unwise might consider it dishonorable to slay the helpless while they awaken, but in this case you would have been a fool to have done otherwise.$B$BAnd we certainly couldn\'t have just left them standing there to be ritually wakened, now could we?$B$BIt was a brave thing you did for all of us down in those catacombs, $R.' WHERE `entry`=11433;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We\'re going to go places together, $N. With my good looks and your... can-do attitude, we\'re sure to make a killing.' WHERE `entry`=11434;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You are insane, $N! What kind of degenerate would actually launch themselves from a harpoon gun as a method of travel?$B$BBut I guess you need to be a little crazy to pull off what you did up there on the bluffs! Fantastic work! We\'ve gotten word that the Dragonflayer leader, Ingvar, is furious! Maybe one day you\'ll be ready to stomp his face into the dirt - in the name of our beloved Alliance.' WHERE `entry`=11436;
