UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Groovy! You\'re my kind of $R.' WHERE `entry`=12836;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hand them over. I will sift through the useless ones and if there\'s anything actionable, I will call upon you.$B$BEither way, return tomorrow. It is well known that they change their plans on a daily basis.' WHERE `entry`=12838;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A note written by Westwind? Why didn\'t you say so?$B$B<Arete tears the letter from your hand to read it.>$B$BThe fool! He\'s actually here?!$B$B<The lord-commander laughs.>$B$BThis is new information. I wonder how he imagines that he\'s going to conquer the world once he\'s taken down the Lich King? Not that he could accomplish either task in his wildest imaginings.' WHERE `entry`=12839;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='They resurrected Landgren? He\'s the one that will know where the grand admiral is then!' WHERE `entry`=12840;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I wasn\'t sure you were coming back. I dread to think what will happen to me if I stay here for much longer.' WHERE `entry`=12841;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Remember these words, death knight: The Runeforge is a Scourge instrument. It exists only in Acherus, Naxxramas and the heart of Icecrown! You may only emblazon your weaponry at a Runeforge.$B$BReturn often and emblazon all of your weapons. A death knight must be prepared for all that would dare oppose $G him:her;!' WHERE `entry`=12842;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='Do not waste time, $N. We are on the brink of apocalypse!' WHERE `entry`=12842;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did it! Our boys are back!' WHERE `entry`=12843;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thanks, $N! We\'ll see what we can do to salvage these parts!' WHERE `entry`=12844;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re definitely not with the Hyldnir... so what are you here for? Ah... you must be looking for the new prisoner!' WHERE `entry`=12846;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hidden caves on the backside of the island. How very interesting.$B$BWell, at least now I know where all of my missing spies are.' WHERE `entry`=12847;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText2_loc6`='Arete\'s Gate summoned' WHERE `entry`=12847;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='As expected, my chosen knight has triumphed! You are ready, $N.' WHERE `entry`=12848;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Within the Hall of Command you will find the schools of blood, frost and unholy. Each school has a trainer that can provide you with knowledge in the various dark arts.$B$BI, Lord Thorval, am the headmaster of the school of blood. Lady Alistra reigns over unholy and the arch-lich, Amal\'thazad, holds dominion over frost.$B$BYou must return here whenever you gain power and train!' WHERE `entry`=12849;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The war has begun, death knight! I shall place you upon my finest gryphon and deliver you to Death\'s Breach. Chaos, death, destruction! You will herald in all of this and more!' WHERE `entry`=12850;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Perhaps you do have the heart of a warrior.$B$BTime will tell...' WHERE `entry`=12851;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='MAL\'GANIS?!!$B$B<The lord-commander laughs with abandon.>$B$BThe fools were taken in by the demons yet again and now they are destroyed!$B$BI trust that my favorite $C will stick around long enough to help us finish off the rest of them? Perhaps one of these would convince you?' WHERE `entry`=12852;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Welcome to K3!$B$BWe came here to make our way into those peaks and get our fair share of some of those amazing titan machines. Progress on that end has been somewhat minimal, though. Gnolls, snobolds, magnataur... there\'s no shortage of trouble to go around... not to mention, we can\'t seem to keep any fliers in the air without their motors freezing.$B$BThere\'s plenty of work to be done though - lend a hand, eh?' WHERE `entry`=12853;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Archaeologist Andorin looks at you expectantly.>$B$BYou were supposed to come back with Brann, not a piece of paper. What\'s going on here?' WHERE `entry`=12854;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You... you\'re not a member of the Explorers\' League, at least not one I remember. But, if you recovered the communicator, they must\'ve sent you. Good, that\'s almost what I was hoping for.' WHERE `entry`=12855;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText1_loc6`='Track down thief' WHERE `entry`=12855;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Your efforts appear to have been successful, $Gbrother:sister;.$B$BYou have brought glory to the Brunnhildar!' WHERE `entry`=12856;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Chief Rageclaw cries.>$B$BHad Ragemane since pup. Sad day for Rageclaw. First troll attack Rageclaw, then troll make Ragemane bad. Rageclaw never trade with troll again!' WHERE `entry`=12857;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Wonderful! Now that we have the disk, you must use it to open the Inventor\'s vault!' WHERE `entry`=12858;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It strange because I know you put fire out, but fire still burning. Maybe this thing not so good after all, eh? Still, Moky pay you for what you do! Hopefully troll burn too!' WHERE `entry`=12859;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Brann looks at the disk as you hold it up.>$B$BI can\'t tell if there\'s anything stored there or not! You have to tell me what happened.$B$B<You describe the data retrieval process.>$B$BSo it worked? At least we can count on Mimir to be systematic. Can\'t say that for the rest of these Keepers from what I\'ve been hearing...' WHERE `entry`=12860;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Rageclaw thank you, $N. Though Rageclaw Den probably lost forever and troll-Rageclaw friendship also lost forever... and also now I think of it, Ragemane lost forever too. Also brother-in-law. He gone. Hrm, have you seen Chief\'s mate? I think she gone too.$B$BMaybe you go now. Chief a little depressed.' WHERE `entry`=12861;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ow! That looked painful. It was a pretty grand entrance though, lad!$B$BWelcome to Frosthold! Are ya here to help us find a path into Icecrown?' WHERE `entry`=12862;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Medical supplies? Thank you! Not exactly sure what to do with them to be honest, but I\'m sure they\'ll be useful.$B$BIt\'s good to meet you... there\'s such a colorful variety among your peoples. We\'re not used to having visitors up this way very often - it\'s good to have some fresh company.' WHERE `entry`=12863;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='When a scout doesn\'t come back for this long... that\'s about the expected result. The harpies then?$B$BKing Stormheart has us train hard year round... he\'s turned us into amazing fighters. At times like this, I understand why it\'s necessary. He\'s the wisest and strongest leader I\'ve yet seen among our people... don\'t let his peachy skin fool ya.' WHERE `entry`=12864;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, kindly... and I\'m sure they\'re quite appreciative too. They make powerful allies; you\'ll be well off being on this side of their graces.' WHERE `entry`=12865;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s dirty work, I know, but we appreciate it. Now what was the name the scout mentioned... Sirana?' WHERE `entry`=12866;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good stuff, lad. You\'re making fast friends.$B$BIf you stop back by soon, I\'m sure we can find one that will let you ride... they should know that you\'re trustworthy now.' WHERE `entry`=12867;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s done then. Thank you.$B$BI\'ve spoken with Fjorlin - he said that his men will take charge of keeping the harpies down a bit. As long as we don\'t let up again, they won\'t find the courage to think they can attack our people.$B$BI know this wasn\'t the most tasteful work - take this as a token of my appreciation.' WHERE `entry`=12868;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I don\'t see the drakes being dissuaded so easily. Stop back by tomorrow if you think you can spare more time to help.' WHERE `entry`=12869;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Beaut! Yer a good one you are.$B$BTilt one back wi\' me! Let us celebrae\' this glorious find!' WHERE `entry`=12870;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='By Muradin\'s beard! Is that what I think it is?! Brann\'s really outdone himself this time... and you too for that matter! The boys back home are never going to believe this.' WHERE `entry`=12871;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That\'s it! That\'s the first half of Norgannon\'s keystone. Well done, $N. When I get back to Ironforge, I\'m going to have you inducted as an honorary member in the Explorers\' League!' WHERE `entry`=12872;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Norgannon\'s Core? Never heard of it. I might well know someone that has though.' WHERE `entry`=12873;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Ha! Grand tale lad... perhaps ye have a bit of frostborn blood in ye, eh? Yer not just talk anyway, and that\'s what I needed to hear.' WHERE `entry`=12874;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Drom coughts up a bit of blood.>$B$BNorgannon\'s Core, eh? I\'ve spent a fair number of days trying to find anything I could about it myself, but it seems to be one of the relics that\'s still guarded. With reason I suppose.$B$BIf King Stormheart sent you, he surely must see something noble in ye... and I\'m not one to refuse my king.' WHERE `entry`=12875;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Grim news, lad. Those Iron Dwarves seem to be increasing in numbers... we\'ve been seeing them all over the mountains. I smell war coming.$B$BThank you for dealing with this bunch... a little more time bought.' WHERE `entry`=12876;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Drom\'s ring? I am to assume Drom is not well if he did not introduce you directly. I am sorry to hear of that. Drom is a noble dwarf, if an inquisitive one.$B$BOn what business have you come then?' WHERE `entry`=12877;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<As the chest opens, air rushes out into the chamber, carrying with it the musty smell of something that has been here for countless years. Norgannon\'s Core rests in the bottom of the chest, undisturbed by the ages.>' WHERE `entry`=12878;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Someone is using the Forge of Wills to create this army... Ulduar is no longer safe.$B$B$R, I am pleased that you were able to reach the core before these abominations were.' WHERE `entry`=12879;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re brilliant, lad! Brilliant! This will be a glorious day indeed.$B$BQuickly, hand me the core before those iron dwarves make their way down here.' WHERE `entry`=12880;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These will do nicely! I am much obliged. Perhaps a drink for your troubles?' WHERE `entry`=12882;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='If this is the same Drakuru from Drak\'Tharon Keep we are going to need... outside assistance.$B$BDeath knights of Acherus are stationed nearby, undoubtedly following the same trail of Scourge destruction that lead the Argent Crusade here. As half of our army is tied up at the Argent Stand, battling crazed Drakkari trolls, we will have to join forces with the Knights of the Ebon Blade.$B$B<Lantinga mutters under his breath.>$B$BI was hoping I\'d never have to see those scoundrels again after Light\'s Hope...' WHERE `entry`=12883;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Stefan reads the missive, then crumples it up and tosses it into the fire.>$B$BOld news. The Argent Crusade is - once again - late to the party. we\'ve been tracking Drakuru since Grizzly Hills. He is slated for eradication.' WHERE `entry`=12884;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you know Brann Bronzebeard, then? He is our closest ally among those of the flesh. We are as brothers in the struggle against Loken and his followers, in the struggle for Ulduar.' WHERE `entry`=12885;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Sif... is that you?' WHERE `entry`=12886;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText1_loc6`='Hyldsmeet Drakerider Defeated' WHERE `entry`=12886;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Perhaps now we can really get something done. Don\'t be fooled though, the Lich King can still \'see\' through his Scourge minions.$B$BThat\'s why you\'re here.' WHERE `entry`=12887;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<You begin performing the repairs indicated by the access card. When the repairs are complete, you close the access panel and throw the power switch.>' WHERE `entry`=12888;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You examine the display on the repaired prototype console. At least one of Mimir\'s schematics seems to have survived the long period between maintenance cycles. From the diagrams and instructions displayed in the schematic\'s file, you could easily construct the mechagnome shown.' WHERE `entry`=12889;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Quickly, hand them to me and stay out of sight!$B$BThe rod, the hook, and the rope are all very self-evident in their usage when combined. I just need to infuse the result with the essences and we\'ll be ready to proceed.$B$BIt\'s all very mundane in its composition, but extraordinary in its application!' WHERE `entry`=12891;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Perhaps now we can really get something done. Don\'t be fooled though, the Lich King can still \'see\' through his Scourge minions.$B$BThat\'s why you\'re here.' WHERE `entry`=12892;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='We will put those three to good use once we finally take the vault.$B$BSpeaking of which....' WHERE `entry`=12893;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Everything was fine until the Scourge attacked. They took off with Dargath, Gerk and Burr and they also destroyed our ride. Guess who led that attack?$B$B<MacKellar nods.>$B$BNavarius...$B$BSeems this whole area is some type of factory for Scourge. We\'re in the middle of a damned undead mine field!' WHERE `entry`=12894;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Of course, with our luck, I probably could\'ve predicted this. Well, we\'re not going to let him get away that easily. Let\'s see what that note says.' WHERE `entry`=12895;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='General Lightsbane and his forces are defeated? The Shadow Vault is taken?' WHERE `entry`=12896;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='General Lightsbane and his forces are defeated? The Shadow Vault is taken?' WHERE `entry`=12897;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good of you to return. As you can see, we have our hands full here.' WHERE `entry`=12898;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Good of you to return. As you can see, we have our hands full here.' WHERE `entry`=12899;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These will do nicely. I\'ll have the harness ready for you in no time.' WHERE `entry`=12900;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What is this junk! Ah, damn it all! It\'s useless. Scourge metal isn\'t gonna do the trick. What are we going to do?' WHERE `entry`=12901;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='There is a scroll floating in the air above the strange altar. This must be what Crusader Lord Lantinga is looking for!' WHERE `entry`=12902;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It was a great sacrifice that those three made and it won\'t soon be forgotten. Their passing will not be in vain. We will be victorious!' WHERE `entry`=12903;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Gerk is dying.>$B$BTh... They say these Vargul are the... the ones that weren\'t found worthy by the Lich King. Can... Can you im... imagine it? Just th... think how powerful the... the... worthy must be...$B$BI\'ll say a prayer for you in the hereafter, hero... May you never have to face them in number.' WHERE `entry`=12904;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I was expecting a replacement for one of my overseers. It\'s about time you showed up.$B$BLet\'s put you to work.' WHERE `entry`=12905;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Not bad for a new overseer. I\'ve another task for you if you\'re feeling brave today.' WHERE `entry`=12906;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='If I had any reservations regarding your commitment when you first arrived, I no longer have any. With just a little more effort you could be a permanent member of my operation.' WHERE `entry`=12907;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I knew you\'d be back! Get me out of these shackles and I\'ll help you find the goblin.' WHERE `entry`=12908;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So Boktar has volunteered Frostbite for an errand, eh? Well, this had better be important. He knows better than to try to separate a hunter from her pet!' WHERE `entry`=12909;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<An image of a dwarf appears as you activate the communicator. It can only be Brann Bronzebeard.>$B$B<From the look on his face, Brann seems shocked to see you and begins gesturing furiously.>' WHERE `entry`=12910;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='A... A storm giant? I don\'t know about this, $N. That sounds risky. On the other hand, I don\'t think we have too many other options.$B$BIf I do this you have to promise me that you will get your giant friend to help us deal with Navarius and his cronies.' WHERE `entry`=12912;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Bartok will not be happy that you didn\'t find Brann, but at least you didn\'t come back empty-handed. Now, let\'s see what we can do about this babbling dwarf.' WHERE `entry`=12913;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thankfully we weren\'t in short supply of explosives. Putting together the jumbo seaforium charge should be no problem with the materials you brought me.' WHERE `entry`=12914;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So, it is done then.$B$BLet us hope it is enough.' WHERE `entry`=12915;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='FREEDOM!$B$BDo not be afraid, little one. Gymer is an honorable giant. Like you and your people, I too wish to see the Scourge driven away from this land and the Lich King destroyed. I will help you, as promised, to the best of my ability.' WHERE `entry`=12916;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You should be able to communicate with the dwarf now. Ask Boktar what he requires of you. There is little time to lose.' WHERE `entry`=12917;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These are perfect for replenishing my stock. Not only will I teach you the art of gemcutting perfection, but I cut one of them gems into its perfect form which you may have as a reward.' WHERE `entry`=12918;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Unbelievable! This will be a story for the ages, $N! One man rode upon the head of the king of storm giants and decimated an entire Scourge army!$B$BAnd I was there to see it all happen...' WHERE `entry`=12919;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Boktar listens as you describe your conversation with Brann.>$B$BThere\'s truth to the dwarf\'s words. Vor\'takh\'s plan is not the way of the Horde. If Brann Bronzebeard knows of a way to stop these iron dwarves and their patron, it serves us to help him.' WHERE `entry`=12920;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'re here -- good. I think I know where your goblin is.' WHERE `entry`=12921;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You place the metal on the anvil and immediately upon adding the sparks they work the ore furiously.$B$BWhen at last they burn out, you are left with a large piece of metal that gleams with a light of its own.' WHERE `entry`=12922;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It would seem that I have refined my technique considerably. That, or the legends surrounding this anvil are true.$B$BThis suit of armor is superior to the last, and took less material to create.$B$BWith the excess, I was able to fashion you a little something as payment for your assistance.' WHERE `entry`=12924;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You have our thanks, $Gbrother:sister;. We cannot allow our valiant traditions to be corrupted.' WHERE `entry`=12925;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That was quick! Now that we have the disk, we have to find out how to use it to unlock the first half of the archive key.' WHERE `entry`=12926;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Brann looks at the disk as you hold it up.>$B$BI can\'t tell if there\'s anything stored there or not, lad. You\'ll have to tell me what happened.$B$B<You describe the data retrieval process.>$B$BSo it worked? At least we can count on Keeper Mimir to be systematic.' WHERE `entry`=12927;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That\'s it! That\'s the first half of Norgannon\'s keystone. Well done, $N. I\'ve had Archaeologist Andorin on the lookout for clues to the shell\'s whereabouts for a long time. He\'s never going to believe me when I tell him it was an intrepid $R who found it instead.' WHERE `entry`=12928;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='So you know Brann Bronzebeard, then? He is our closest ally among those of the flesh. We are as brothers in the struggle against Loken and his followers, in the struggle for Ulduar.' WHERE `entry`=12929;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='This will allow us to patch up more of the fallen. Thank you, $N, on behalf of all who defend the refuge.' WHERE `entry`=12930;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You\'ve given the defenders something to cheer about. Seeing the enemy fall by your hand has reinvigorated them and bolstered their courage.' WHERE `entry`=12931;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Not bad, friend. You might make some gold out here - if you manage to stay alive.' WHERE `entry`=12932;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Wow! When I first saw Stinkbeard, I thought you were done for! Nice work!' WHERE `entry`=12933;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Unbelievable! I thought this whole place was going to explode when it first appeared! You really dominated that round!' WHERE `entry`=12934;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='I was worried for a while there, $N. When he busted out the seals and penguins... Well, I didn\'t know what to think to be honest. It looked pretty damn ridiculous.' WHERE `entry`=12935;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Damn, I remember Korrak from way back in my younger days when I used to work for the Frostwolf Clan. He would never shut up! I think you just did the world a great service, $N.' WHERE `entry`=12936;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The warriors that you\'ve healed will aid us in holding the line even longer. If we are to truly be free of the iron threat, we must find a way to strike at them behind the lines.' WHERE `entry`=12937;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='It\'s a pleasure to finally meet you, $N. We owe you a great deal, but we\'re not done with you yet.$B$BThere is a vrykul city just over the mountains to the west, a place called Jotunheim.$B$BThe vrykul there are in a constant state of challenge to \'ascend\'. The winners go to Ymirheim to serve as the Lich King\'s elite warrior caste, the Ymirjar, and the losers are reduced to scourged Vargul.$B$BYou are going to be my instrument to see to it that more Vargul than Ymirjar emerge.' WHERE `entry`=12938;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Already I\'m hearing reports of the prowess you displayed on the Savage Ledge. Excellent, $N... excellent!$B$B<The duke flashes his rictus smile again and you can almost hear the wheels in his head turning.>$B$BAnd now I think it\'s time to issue a decree to the thane of those vrykul that you so easily defeated.' WHERE `entry`=12939;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='The Val\'kyr are nothing but the Lich King\'s lapdogs. They will be put down like the scum they are. They\'ve made their choice, now they have to live with the consequences.' WHERE `entry`=12942;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='<Duke Lankral nods his approval at your report of success.>$B$BWe face a foe that dwarfs us, not only in stature, but also numerically. If we are to win the battle for Icecrown, we must outthink them!$B$BWith Ufrang dead, that gives us an advantage in Jotunheim. Let us see if we can capitalize on it.' WHERE `entry`=12943;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='You did it, $N! That was the most exciting fight yet! What are you going to do with your winnings? Me? I\'m going to Dalaran and blowing it all in the Underbelly. Lot of hot action going on down there!' WHERE `entry`=12948;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Thank you, $R. Just hand me the key, I\'ll take care of it myself.' WHERE `entry`=12949;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='What?! We can ill-afford to lose one death knight, let alone an entire contingent!!!' WHERE `entry`=12951;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='These will have to do. I can teach you the art of gemcutting perfection, and give you proof of my skills as well.' WHERE `entry`=12952;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Now that is what I call dedication! Those traitors might have a new master now, but they\'ll never forget their sisters\' parting gift.' WHERE `entry`=12953;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `ObjectiveText1_loc6`='Fires Started' WHERE `entry`=12953;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='Hey! I know you. Your victory at the Ring of Blood was talked about for months! Too bad you forfeited the championship when you failed to show up to defend your title! Easy come, easy go, eh? At least you\'re still alive.' WHERE `entry`=12954;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `RequestItemsText_loc6`='No payout until the fight\'s over, $G man:lady;.' WHERE `entry`=12954;
UPDATE `locales_quest` SET `offerrewardtext_loc6`='That was important, $N. By driving them off, you\'re keeping them from interfering with whatever we need you to do over there.' WHERE `entry`=12955;
